8//
9// This file performs vector type splitting and scalarization for LegalizeTypes.
10// Scalarization is the act of changing a computation in an illegal one-element
11// vector type to be a computation in its scalar element type. For example,
12// implementing <1 x f32> arithmetic in a scalar f32 register. This is needed
13// as a base case when scalarizing vector arithmetic like <4 x f32>, which
14// eventually decomposes to scalars if the target doesn't support v4f32 or v2f32
15// types.
16// Splitting is the act of changing a computation in an invalid vector type to
17// be a computation in two vectors of half the size. For example, implementing
18// <128 x f32> operations in terms of two <64 x f32> operations.
19//
20//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
21

23#include "llvm/Analysis/MemoryLocation.h"

25#include "llvm/Support/ErrorHandling.h"

32//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
33// Result Vector Scalarization: <1 x ty> -> ty.
34//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
35
36void DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVectorResult(SDNode *N, unsigned ResNo) {
37 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Scalarize node result " << ResNo << ": "; N->dump(&DAG);
38 dbgs() << "\n");
39 SDValue R = SDValue();
40
41 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
42 default:
43#ifndef NDEBUG
44 dbgs() << "ScalarizeVectorResult #" << ResNo << ": ";
45 N->dump(&DAG);
46 dbgs() << "\n";
47#endif
48 report_fatal_error("Do not know how to scalarize the result of this "
49 "operator!\n");
50
51 case ISD::MERGE_VALUES: R = ScalarizeVecRes_MERGE_VALUES(N, ResNo);break;
52 case ISD::BITCAST: R = ScalarizeVecRes_BITCAST(N); break;
53 case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR: R = ScalarizeVecRes_BUILD_VECTOR(N); break;
54 case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR: R = ScalarizeVecRes_EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR(N); break;
55 case ISD::FP_ROUND: R = ScalarizeVecRes_FP_ROUND(N); break;
56 case ISD::FPOWI: R = ScalarizeVecRes_FPOWI(N); break;
57 case ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT: R = ScalarizeVecRes_INSERT_VECTOR_ELT(N); break;
58 case ISD::LOAD: R = ScalarizeVecRes_LOAD(cast<LoadSDNode>(N));break;
59 case ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR: R = ScalarizeVecRes_SCALAR_TO_VECTOR(N); break;
60 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG: R = ScalarizeVecRes_InregOp(N); break;
61 case ISD::VSELECT: R = ScalarizeVecRes_VSELECT(N); break;
62 case ISD::SELECT: R = ScalarizeVecRes_SELECT(N); break;
63 case ISD::SELECT_CC: R = ScalarizeVecRes_SELECT_CC(N); break;
64 case ISD::SETCC: R = ScalarizeVecRes_SETCC(N); break;
65 case ISD::UNDEF: R = ScalarizeVecRes_UNDEF(N); break;
66 case ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE: R = ScalarizeVecRes_VECTOR_SHUFFLE(N); break;
67 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
68 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
69 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
70 R = ScalarizeVecRes_VecInregOp(N);
71 break;
72 case ISD::ABS:
73 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND:
74 case ISD::BITREVERSE:
75 case ISD::BSWAP:
76 case ISD::CTLZ:
77 case ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
78 case ISD::CTPOP:
79 case ISD::CTTZ:
80 case ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
81 case ISD::FABS:
82 case ISD::FCEIL:
83 case ISD::FCOS:
84 case ISD::FEXP:
85 case ISD::FEXP2:
86 case ISD::FFLOOR:
87 case ISD::FLOG:
88 case ISD::FLOG10:
89 case ISD::FLOG2:
90 case ISD::FNEARBYINT:
91 case ISD::FNEG:
92 case ISD::FREEZE:
93 case ISD::FP_EXTEND:
94 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT:
95 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT:
96 case ISD::FRINT:
97 case ISD::FROUND:
98 case ISD::FROUNDEVEN:
99 case ISD::FSIN:
100 case ISD::FSQRT:
101 case ISD::FTRUNC:
102 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
103 case ISD::SINT_TO_FP:
104 case ISD::TRUNCATE:
105 case ISD::UINT_TO_FP:
106 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
107 case ISD::FCANONICALIZE:
108 R = ScalarizeVecRes_UnaryOp(N);
109 break;
110
111 case ISD::ADD:
112 case ISD::AND:
113 case ISD::FADD:
114 case ISD::FCOPYSIGN:
115 case ISD::FDIV:
116 case ISD::FMUL:
117 case ISD::FMINNUM:
118 case ISD::FMAXNUM:
119 case ISD::FMINNUM_IEEE:
120 case ISD::FMAXNUM_IEEE:
121 case ISD::FMINIMUM:
122 case ISD::FMAXIMUM:
123 case ISD::SMIN:
124 case ISD::SMAX:
125 case ISD::UMIN:
126 case ISD::UMAX:
127
128 case ISD::SADDSAT:
129 case ISD::UADDSAT:
130 case ISD::SSUBSAT:
131 case ISD::USUBSAT:
132 case ISD::SSHLSAT:
133 case ISD::USHLSAT:
134
135 case ISD::FPOW:
136 case ISD::FREM:
137 case ISD::FSUB:
138 case ISD::MUL:
139 case ISD::OR:
140 case ISD::SDIV:
141 case ISD::SREM:
142 case ISD::SUB:
143 case ISD::UDIV:
144 case ISD::UREM:
145 case ISD::XOR:
146 case ISD::SHL:
147 case ISD::SRA:
148 case ISD::SRL:
149 case ISD::ROTL:
150 case ISD::ROTR:
151 R = ScalarizeVecRes_BinOp(N);
152 break;
153 case ISD::FMA:
154 case ISD::FSHL:
155 case ISD::FSHR:
156 R = ScalarizeVecRes_TernaryOp(N);
157 break;
158
159#define DAG_INSTRUCTION(NAME, NARG, ROUND_MODE, INTRINSIC, DAGN) \
160 case ISD::STRICT_##DAGN:
161#include "llvm/IR/ConstrainedOps.def"
162 R = ScalarizeVecRes_StrictFPOp(N);
163 break;
164
165 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT_SAT:
166 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT:
167 R = ScalarizeVecRes_FP_TO_XINT_SAT(N);
168 break;
169
170 case ISD::UADDO:
171 case ISD::SADDO:
172 case ISD::USUBO:
173 case ISD::SSUBO:
174 case ISD::UMULO:
175 case ISD::SMULO:
176 R = ScalarizeVecRes_OverflowOp(N, ResNo);
177 break;
178 case ISD::SMULFIX:
179 case ISD::SMULFIXSAT:
180 case ISD::UMULFIX:
181 case ISD::UMULFIXSAT:
182 case ISD::SDIVFIX:
183 case ISD::SDIVFIXSAT:
184 case ISD::UDIVFIX:
185 case ISD::UDIVFIXSAT:
186 R = ScalarizeVecRes_FIX(N);
187 break;
188 }
189
190 // If R is null, the sub-method took care of registering the result.
191 if (R.getNode())
192 SetScalarizedVector(SDValue(N, ResNo), R);
193}

195SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_BinOp(SDNode *N) {
196 SDValue LHS = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(0));
197 SDValue RHS = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(1));
198 return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), SDLoc(N),
199 LHS.getValueType(), LHS, RHS, N->getFlags());
200}
201
202SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_TernaryOp(SDNode *N) {
203 SDValue Op0 = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(0));
204 SDValue Op1 = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(1));
205 SDValue Op2 = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(2));
206 return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), SDLoc(N), Op0.getValueType(), Op0, Op1,
207 Op2, N->getFlags());
208}
209
210SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_FIX(SDNode *N) {
211 SDValue Op0 = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(0));
212 SDValue Op1 = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(1));
213 SDValue Op2 = N->getOperand(2);
214 return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), SDLoc(N), Op0.getValueType(), Op0, Op1,
215 Op2, N->getFlags());
216}
217
218SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_StrictFPOp(SDNode *N) {
219 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType();
220 unsigned NumOpers = N->getNumOperands();
221 SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0);
222 EVT ValueVTs[] = {VT, MVT::Other};
223 SDLoc dl(N);
224
225 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Opers(NumOpers);
226
227 // The Chain is the first operand.
228 Opers[0] = Chain;
229
230 // Now process the remaining operands.
231 for (unsigned i = 1; i < NumOpers; ++i) {
232 SDValue Oper = N->getOperand(i);
233
234 if (Oper.getValueType().isVector())
235 Oper = GetScalarizedVector(Oper);
236
237 Opers[i] = Oper;
238 }
239
240 SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, DAG.getVTList(ValueVTs),
241 Opers, N->getFlags());
242
243 // Legalize the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to
244 // use the new one.
245 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Result.getValue(1));
246 return Result;
247}
248
249SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_OverflowOp(SDNode *N,
250 unsigned ResNo) {
251 SDLoc DL(N);
252 EVT ResVT = N->getValueType(0);
253 EVT OvVT = N->getValueType(1);
254
255 SDValue ScalarLHS, ScalarRHS;
256 if (getTypeAction(ResVT) == TargetLowering::TypeScalarizeVector) {
257 ScalarLHS = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(0));
258 ScalarRHS = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(1));
259 } else {
260 SmallVector<SDValue, 1> ElemsLHS, ElemsRHS;
261 DAG.ExtractVectorElements(N->getOperand(0), ElemsLHS);
262 DAG.ExtractVectorElements(N->getOperand(1), ElemsRHS);
263 ScalarLHS = ElemsLHS[0];
264 ScalarRHS = ElemsRHS[0];
265 }
266
267 SDVTList ScalarVTs = DAG.getVTList(
268 ResVT.getVectorElementType(), OvVT.getVectorElementType());
269 SDNode *ScalarNode = DAG.getNode(
270 N->getOpcode(), DL, ScalarVTs, ScalarLHS, ScalarRHS).getNode();
271 ScalarNode->setFlags(N->getFlags());
272
273 // Replace the other vector result not being explicitly scalarized here.
274 unsigned OtherNo = 1 - ResNo;
275 EVT OtherVT = N->getValueType(OtherNo);
276 if (getTypeAction(OtherVT) == TargetLowering::TypeScalarizeVector) {
277 SetScalarizedVector(SDValue(N, OtherNo), SDValue(ScalarNode, OtherNo));
278 } else {
279 SDValue OtherVal = DAG.getNode(
280 ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, DL, OtherVT, SDValue(ScalarNode, OtherNo));
281 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, OtherNo), OtherVal);
282 }
283
284 return SDValue(ScalarNode, ResNo);
285}

287SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_MERGE_VALUES(SDNode *N,
288 unsigned ResNo) {
289 SDValue Op = DisintegrateMERGE_VALUES(N, ResNo);
290 return GetScalarizedVector(Op);
291}

293SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_BITCAST(SDNode *N) {
294 SDValue Op = N->getOperand(0);
295 if (Op.getValueType().isVector()
296 && Op.getValueType().getVectorNumElements() == 1
297 && !isSimpleLegalType(Op.getValueType()))
298 Op = GetScalarizedVector(Op);
299 EVT NewVT = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType();
300 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SDLoc(N),
301 NewVT, Op);
302}
303
304SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_BUILD_VECTOR(SDNode *N) {
305 EVT EltVT = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType();
306 SDValue InOp = N->getOperand(0);
307 // The BUILD_VECTOR operands may be of wider element types and
308 // we may need to truncate them back to the requested return type.
309 if (EltVT.isInteger())
310 return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SDLoc(N), EltVT, InOp);
311 return InOp;
312}

314SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR(SDNode *N) {
315 return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SDLoc(N),
316 N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType(),
317 N->getOperand(0), N->getOperand(1));
318}

320SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_FP_ROUND(SDNode *N) {
321 EVT NewVT = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType();
322 SDValue Op = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(0));
323 return DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_ROUND, SDLoc(N),
324 NewVT, Op, N->getOperand(1));
325}

327SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_FPOWI(SDNode *N) {
328 SDValue Op = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(0));
329 return DAG.getNode(ISD::FPOWI, SDLoc(N),
330 Op.getValueType(), Op, N->getOperand(1));
331}
332
333SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_INSERT_VECTOR_ELT(SDNode *N) {
334 // The value to insert may have a wider type than the vector element type,
335 // so be sure to truncate it to the element type if necessary.
336 SDValue Op = N->getOperand(1);
337 EVT EltVT = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType();
338 if (Op.getValueType() != EltVT)
339 // FIXME: Can this happen for floating point types?
340 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SDLoc(N), EltVT, Op);
341 return Op;
342}
343
344SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_LOAD(LoadSDNode *N) {
345 assert(N->isUnindexed() && "Indexed vector load?");
346
347 SDValue Result = DAG.getLoad(
348 ISD::UNINDEXED, N->getExtensionType(),
349 N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType(), SDLoc(N), N->getChain(),
350 N->getBasePtr(), DAG.getUNDEF(N->getBasePtr().getValueType()),
351 N->getPointerInfo(), N->getMemoryVT().getVectorElementType(),
352 N->getOriginalAlign(), N->getMemOperand()->getFlags(), N->getAAInfo());
353
354 // Legalize the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to
355 // use the new one.
356 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Result.getValue(1));
357 return Result;
358}
359
360SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_UnaryOp(SDNode *N) {
361 // Get the dest type - it doesn't always match the input type, e.g. int_to_fp.
362 EVT DestVT = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType();
363 SDValue Op = N->getOperand(0);
364 EVT OpVT = Op.getValueType();
365 SDLoc DL(N);
366 // The result needs scalarizing, but it's not a given that the source does.
367 // This is a workaround for targets where it's impossible to scalarize the
368 // result of a conversion, because the source type is legal.
369 // For instance, this happens on AArch64: v1i1 is illegal but v1i{8,16,32}
370 // are widened to v8i8, v4i16, and v2i32, which is legal, because v1i64 is
371 // legal and was not scalarized.
372 // See the similar logic in ScalarizeVecRes_SETCC
373 if (getTypeAction(OpVT) == TargetLowering::TypeScalarizeVector) {
374 Op = GetScalarizedVector(Op);
375 } else {
376 EVT VT = OpVT.getVectorElementType();
377 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, VT, Op,
378 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
379 }
380 return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), SDLoc(N), DestVT, Op, N->getFlags());
381}
382
383SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_InregOp(SDNode *N) {
384 EVT EltVT = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType();
385 EVT ExtVT = cast<VTSDNode>(N->getOperand(1))->getVT().getVectorElementType();
386 SDValue LHS = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(0));
387 return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), SDLoc(N), EltVT,
388 LHS, DAG.getValueType(ExtVT));
389}
390
391SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_VecInregOp(SDNode *N) {
392 SDLoc DL(N);
393 SDValue Op = N->getOperand(0);
394
395 EVT OpVT = Op.getValueType();
396 EVT OpEltVT = OpVT.getVectorElementType();
397 EVT EltVT = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType();
398
399 if (getTypeAction(OpVT) == TargetLowering::TypeScalarizeVector) {
400 Op = GetScalarizedVector(Op);
401 } else {
402 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, OpEltVT, Op,
403 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
404 }
405
406 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
407 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
408 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, EltVT, Op);
409 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
410 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, DL, EltVT, Op);
411 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
412 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, EltVT, Op);
413 }
414
415 llvm_unreachable("Illegal extend_vector_inreg opcode");
416}

418SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_SCALAR_TO_VECTOR(SDNode *N) {
419 // If the operand is wider than the vector element type then it is implicitly
420 // truncated. Make that explicit here.
421 EVT EltVT = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType();
422 SDValue InOp = N->getOperand(0);
423 if (InOp.getValueType() != EltVT)
424 return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SDLoc(N), EltVT, InOp);
425 return InOp;
426}
427
428SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_VSELECT(SDNode *N) {
429 SDValue Cond = N->getOperand(0);
430 EVT OpVT = Cond.getValueType();
431 SDLoc DL(N);
432 // The vselect result and true/value operands needs scalarizing, but it's
433 // not a given that the Cond does. For instance, in AVX512 v1i1 is legal.
434 // See the similar logic in ScalarizeVecRes_SETCC
435 if (getTypeAction(OpVT) == TargetLowering::TypeScalarizeVector) {
436 Cond = GetScalarizedVector(Cond);
437 } else {
438 EVT VT = OpVT.getVectorElementType();
439 Cond = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, VT, Cond,
440 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
441 }
442
443 SDValue LHS = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(1));
444 TargetLowering::BooleanContent ScalarBool =
445 TLI.getBooleanContents(false, false);
446 TargetLowering::BooleanContent VecBool = TLI.getBooleanContents(true, false);
447
448 // If integer and float booleans have different contents then we can't
449 // reliably optimize in all cases. There is a full explanation for this in
450 // DAGCombiner::visitSELECT() where the same issue affects folding
451 // (select C, 0, 1) to (xor C, 1).
452 if (TLI.getBooleanContents(false, false) !=
453 TLI.getBooleanContents(false, true)) {
454 // At least try the common case where the boolean is generated by a
455 // comparison.
456 if (Cond->getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC) {
457 EVT OpVT = Cond->getOperand(0).getValueType();
458 ScalarBool = TLI.getBooleanContents(OpVT.getScalarType());
459 VecBool = TLI.getBooleanContents(OpVT);
460 } else
461 ScalarBool = TargetLowering::UndefinedBooleanContent;
462 }
463
464 EVT CondVT = Cond.getValueType();
465 if (ScalarBool != VecBool) {
466 switch (ScalarBool) {
467 case TargetLowering::UndefinedBooleanContent:
468 break;
469 case TargetLowering::ZeroOrOneBooleanContent:
470 assert(VecBool == TargetLowering::UndefinedBooleanContent ||
471 VecBool == TargetLowering::ZeroOrNegativeOneBooleanContent);
472 // Vector read from all ones, scalar expects a single 1 so mask.
473 Cond = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, SDLoc(N), CondVT,
474 Cond, DAG.getConstant(1, SDLoc(N), CondVT));
475 break;
476 case TargetLowering::ZeroOrNegativeOneBooleanContent:
477 assert(VecBool == TargetLowering::UndefinedBooleanContent ||
478 VecBool == TargetLowering::ZeroOrOneBooleanContent);
479 // Vector reads from a one, scalar from all ones so sign extend.
480 Cond = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, SDLoc(N), CondVT,
481 Cond, DAG.getValueType(MVT::i1));
482 break;
483 }
484 }
485
486 // Truncate the condition if needed
487 auto BoolVT = getSetCCResultType(CondVT);
488 if (BoolVT.bitsLT(CondVT))
489 Cond = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SDLoc(N), BoolVT, Cond);
490
491 return DAG.getSelect(SDLoc(N),
492 LHS.getValueType(), Cond, LHS,
493 GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(2)));
494}
495
496SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_SELECT(SDNode *N) {
497 SDValue LHS = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(1));
498 return DAG.getSelect(SDLoc(N),
499 LHS.getValueType(), N->getOperand(0), LHS,
500 GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(2)));
501}

503SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_SELECT_CC(SDNode *N) {
504 SDValue LHS = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(2));
505 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT_CC, SDLoc(N), LHS.getValueType(),
506 N->getOperand(0), N->getOperand(1),
507 LHS, GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(3)),
508 N->getOperand(4));
509}

511SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_UNDEF(SDNode *N) {
512 return DAG.getUNDEF(N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType());

515SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_VECTOR_SHUFFLE(SDNode *N) {
516 // Figure out if the scalar is the LHS or RHS and return it.
517 SDValue Arg = N->getOperand(2).getOperand(0);
518 if (Arg.isUndef())
519 return DAG.getUNDEF(N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType());
520 unsigned Op = !cast<ConstantSDNode>(Arg)->isNullValue();
521 return GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(Op));
522}
523
524SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_FP_TO_XINT_SAT(SDNode *N) {
525 SDValue Src = N->getOperand(0);
526 EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType();
527 SDLoc dl(N);
528
529 // Handle case where result is scalarized but operand is not
530 if (getTypeAction(SrcVT) == TargetLowering::TypeScalarizeVector)
531 Src = GetScalarizedVector(Src);
532 else
533 Src = DAG.getNode(
534 ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, SrcVT.getVectorElementType(), Src,
535 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
536
537 EVT DstVT = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType();
538 return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, DstVT, Src, N->getOperand(1));
539}
540
541SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecRes_SETCC(SDNode *N) {
542 assert(N->getValueType(0).isVector() &&
543 N->getOperand(0).getValueType().isVector() &&
544 "Operand types must be vectors");
545 SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
546 SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
547 EVT OpVT = LHS.getValueType();
548 EVT NVT = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType();
549 SDLoc DL(N);
550
551 // The result needs scalarizing, but it's not a given that the source does.
552 if (getTypeAction(OpVT) == TargetLowering::TypeScalarizeVector) {
553 LHS = GetScalarizedVector(LHS);
554 RHS = GetScalarizedVector(RHS);
555 } else {
556 EVT VT = OpVT.getVectorElementType();
557 LHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, VT, LHS,
558 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
559 RHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, VT, RHS,
560 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
561 }
562
563 // Turn it into a scalar SETCC.
564 SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::SETCC, DL, MVT::i1, LHS, RHS,
565 N->getOperand(2));
566 // Vectors may have a different boolean contents to scalars. Promote the
567 // value appropriately.
568 ISD::NodeType ExtendCode =
569 TargetLowering::getExtendForContent(TLI.getBooleanContents(OpVT));
570 return DAG.getNode(ExtendCode, DL, NVT, Res);
571}
572
573
574//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
575// Operand Vector Scalarization <1 x ty> -> ty.
576//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
577
578bool DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVectorOperand(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
579 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Scalarize node operand " << OpNo << ": "; N->dump(&DAG);
580 dbgs() << "\n");
581 SDValue Res = SDValue();
582
583 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
584 default:
585#ifndef NDEBUG
586 dbgs() << "ScalarizeVectorOperand Op #" << OpNo << ": ";
587 N->dump(&DAG);
588 dbgs() << "\n";
589#endif
590 report_fatal_error("Do not know how to scalarize this operator's "
591 "operand!\n");
592 case ISD::BITCAST:
593 Res = ScalarizeVecOp_BITCAST(N);
594 break;
595 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND:
596 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
597 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
598 case ISD::TRUNCATE:
599 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT:
600 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT:
601 case ISD::SINT_TO_FP:
602 case ISD::UINT_TO_FP:
603 Res = ScalarizeVecOp_UnaryOp(N);
604 break;
605 case ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP:
606 case ISD::STRICT_UINT_TO_FP:
607 case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT:
608 case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_UINT:
609 Res = ScalarizeVecOp_UnaryOp_StrictFP(N);
610 break;
611 case ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS:
612 Res = ScalarizeVecOp_CONCAT_VECTORS(N);
613 break;
614 case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT:
615 Res = ScalarizeVecOp_EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(N);
616 break;
617 case ISD::VSELECT:
618 Res = ScalarizeVecOp_VSELECT(N);
619 break;
620 case ISD::SETCC:
621 Res = ScalarizeVecOp_VSETCC(N);
622 break;
623 case ISD::STORE:
624 Res = ScalarizeVecOp_STORE(cast<StoreSDNode>(N), OpNo);
625 break;
626 case ISD::STRICT_FP_ROUND:
627 Res = ScalarizeVecOp_STRICT_FP_ROUND(N, OpNo);
628 break;
629 case ISD::FP_ROUND:
630 Res = ScalarizeVecOp_FP_ROUND(N, OpNo);
631 break;
632 case ISD::STRICT_FP_EXTEND:
633 Res = ScalarizeVecOp_STRICT_FP_EXTEND(N);
634 break;
635 case ISD::FP_EXTEND:
636 Res = ScalarizeVecOp_FP_EXTEND(N);
637 break;
638 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FADD:
639 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMUL:
640 case ISD::VECREDUCE_ADD:
641 case ISD::VECREDUCE_MUL:
642 case ISD::VECREDUCE_AND:
643 case ISD::VECREDUCE_OR:
644 case ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR:
645 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX:
646 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN:
647 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX:
648 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN:
649 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMAX:
650 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMIN:
651 Res = ScalarizeVecOp_VECREDUCE(N);
652 break;
653 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SEQ_FADD:
654 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SEQ_FMUL:
655 Res = ScalarizeVecOp_VECREDUCE_SEQ(N);
656 break;
657 }
658
659 // If the result is null, the sub-method took care of registering results etc.
660 if (!Res.getNode()) return false;
661
662 // If the result is N, the sub-method updated N in place. Tell the legalizer
663 // core about this.
664 if (Res.getNode() == N)
665 return true;
666
667 assert(Res.getValueType() == N->getValueType(0) && N->getNumValues() == 1 &&
668 "Invalid operand expansion");
669
670 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 0), Res);
671 return false;
672}
673
674/// If the value to convert is a vector that needs to be scalarized, it must be
675/// <1 x ty>. Convert the element instead.
676SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecOp_BITCAST(SDNode *N) {
677 SDValue Elt = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(0));
678 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SDLoc(N),
679 N->getValueType(0), Elt);
680}
681
682/// If the input is a vector that needs to be scalarized, it must be <1 x ty>.
683/// Do the operation on the element instead.
684SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecOp_UnaryOp(SDNode *N) {
685 assert(N->getValueType(0).getVectorNumElements() == 1 &&
686 "Unexpected vector type!");
687 SDValue Elt = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(0));
688 SDValue Op = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), SDLoc(N),
689 N->getValueType(0).getScalarType(), Elt);
690 // Revectorize the result so the types line up with what the uses of this
691 // expression expect.
692 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0), Op);
693}
694
695/// If the input is a vector that needs to be scalarized, it must be <1 x ty>.
696/// Do the strict FP operation on the element instead.
697SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecOp_UnaryOp_StrictFP(SDNode *N) {
698 assert(N->getValueType(0).getVectorNumElements() == 1 &&
699 "Unexpected vector type!");
700 SDValue Elt = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(1));
701 SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), SDLoc(N),
702 { N->getValueType(0).getScalarType(), MVT::Other },
703 { N->getOperand(0), Elt });
704 // Legalize the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to
705 // use the new one.
706 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Res.getValue(1));
707 // Revectorize the result so the types line up with what the uses of this
708 // expression expect.
709 Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0), Res);
710
711 // Do our own replacement and return SDValue() to tell the caller that we
712 // handled all replacements since caller can only handle a single result.
713 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 0), Res);
714 return SDValue();
715}
716
717/// The vectors to concatenate have length one - use a BUILD_VECTOR instead.
718SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecOp_CONCAT_VECTORS(SDNode *N) {
719 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops(N->getNumOperands());
720 for (unsigned i = 0, e = N->getNumOperands(); i < e; ++i)
721 Ops[i] = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(i));
722 return DAG.getBuildVector(N->getValueType(0), SDLoc(N), Ops);
723}
724
725/// If the input is a vector that needs to be scalarized, it must be <1 x ty>,
726/// so just return the element, ignoring the index.
727SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecOp_EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(SDNode *N) {
728 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
729 SDValue Res = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(0));
730 if (Res.getValueType() != VT)
731 Res = VT.isFloatingPoint()
732 ? DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_EXTEND, SDLoc(N), VT, Res)
733 : DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, SDLoc(N), VT, Res);
734 return Res;
735}
736
737/// If the input condition is a vector that needs to be scalarized, it must be
738/// <1 x i1>, so just convert to a normal ISD::SELECT
739/// (still with vector output type since that was acceptable if we got here).
740SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecOp_VSELECT(SDNode *N) {
741 SDValue ScalarCond = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(0));
742 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
743
744 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, SDLoc(N), VT, ScalarCond, N->getOperand(1),
745 N->getOperand(2));
746}
747
748/// If the operand is a vector that needs to be scalarized then the
749/// result must be v1i1, so just convert to a scalar SETCC and wrap
750/// with a scalar_to_vector since the res type is legal if we got here
751SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecOp_VSETCC(SDNode *N) {
752 assert(N->getValueType(0).isVector() &&
753 N->getOperand(0).getValueType().isVector() &&
754 "Operand types must be vectors");
755 assert(N->getValueType(0) == MVT::v1i1 && "Expected v1i1 type");
756
757 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
758 SDValue LHS = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(0));
759 SDValue RHS = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(1));
760
761 EVT OpVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
762 EVT NVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
763 SDLoc DL(N);
764 // Turn it into a scalar SETCC.
765 SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::SETCC, DL, MVT::i1, LHS, RHS,
766 N->getOperand(2));
767
768 // Vectors may have a different boolean contents to scalars. Promote the
769 // value appropriately.
770 ISD::NodeType ExtendCode =
771 TargetLowering::getExtendForContent(TLI.getBooleanContents(OpVT));
772
773 Res = DAG.getNode(ExtendCode, DL, NVT, Res);
774
775 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, DL, VT, Res);
776}
777
778/// If the value to store is a vector that needs to be scalarized, it must be
779/// <1 x ty>. Just store the element.
780SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecOp_STORE(StoreSDNode *N, unsigned OpNo){
781 assert(N->isUnindexed() && "Indexed store of one-element vector?");
782 assert(OpNo == 1 && "Do not know how to scalarize this operand!");
783 SDLoc dl(N);
784
785 if (N->isTruncatingStore())
786 return DAG.getTruncStore(
787 N->getChain(), dl, GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(1)),
788 N->getBasePtr(), N->getPointerInfo(),
789 N->getMemoryVT().getVectorElementType(), N->getOriginalAlign(),
790 N->getMemOperand()->getFlags(), N->getAAInfo());
791
792 return DAG.getStore(N->getChain(), dl, GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(1)),
793 N->getBasePtr(), N->getPointerInfo(),
794 N->getOriginalAlign(), N->getMemOperand()->getFlags(),
795 N->getAAInfo());
796}
797
798/// If the value to round is a vector that needs to be scalarized, it must be
799/// <1 x ty>. Convert the element instead.
800SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecOp_FP_ROUND(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
801 assert(OpNo == 0 && "Wrong operand for scalarization!");
802 SDValue Elt = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(0));
803 SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_ROUND, SDLoc(N),
804 N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType(), Elt,
805 N->getOperand(1));
806 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0), Res);
807}
808
809SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecOp_STRICT_FP_ROUND(SDNode *N,
810 unsigned OpNo) {
811 assert(OpNo == 1 && "Wrong operand for scalarization!");
812 SDValue Elt = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(1));
813 SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::STRICT_FP_ROUND, SDLoc(N),
814 { N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType(),
815 MVT::Other },
816 { N->getOperand(0), Elt, N->getOperand(2) });
817 // Legalize the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to
818 // use the new one.
819 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Res.getValue(1));
820
821 Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0), Res);
822
823 // Do our own replacement and return SDValue() to tell the caller that we
824 // handled all replacements since caller can only handle a single result.
825 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 0), Res);
826 return SDValue();
827}

829/// If the value to extend is a vector that needs to be scalarized, it must be
830/// <1 x ty>. Convert the element instead.
831SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecOp_FP_EXTEND(SDNode *N) {
832 SDValue Elt = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(0));
833 SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_EXTEND, SDLoc(N),
834 N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType(), Elt);
835 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0), Res);
836}

838/// If the value to extend is a vector that needs to be scalarized, it must be
839/// <1 x ty>. Convert the element instead.
840SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecOp_STRICT_FP_EXTEND(SDNode *N) {
841 SDValue Elt = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(1));
842 SDValue Res =
843 DAG.getNode(ISD::STRICT_FP_EXTEND, SDLoc(N),
844 {N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType(), MVT::Other},
845 {N->getOperand(0), Elt});
846 // Legalize the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to
847 // use the new one.
848 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Res.getValue(1));
849
850 Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0), Res);
851
852 // Do our own replacement and return SDValue() to tell the caller that we
853 // handled all replacements since caller can only handle a single result.
854 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 0), Res);
855 return SDValue();
856}
857
858SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecOp_VECREDUCE(SDNode *N) {
859 SDValue Res = GetScalarizedVector(N->getOperand(0));
860 // Result type may be wider than element type.
861 if (Res.getValueType() != N->getValueType(0))
862 Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0), Res);
863 return Res;
864}
865
866SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ScalarizeVecOp_VECREDUCE_SEQ(SDNode *N) {
867 SDValue AccOp = N->getOperand(0);
868 SDValue VecOp = N->getOperand(1);
869
870 unsigned BaseOpc = ISD::getVecReduceBaseOpcode(N->getOpcode());
871
872 SDValue Op = GetScalarizedVector(VecOp);
873 return DAG.getNode(BaseOpc, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0),
874 AccOp, Op, N->getFlags());
875}

877//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
878// Result Vector Splitting
879//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
880
881/// This method is called when the specified result of the specified node is
882/// found to need vector splitting. At this point, the node may also have
883/// invalid operands or may have other results that need legalization, we just
884/// know that (at least) one result needs vector splitting.
885void DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVectorResult(SDNode *N, unsigned ResNo) {
886 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Split node result: "; N->dump(&DAG); dbgs() << "\n");
887 SDValue Lo, Hi;
888
889 // See if the target wants to custom expand this node.
890 if (CustomLowerNode(N, N->getValueType(ResNo), true))
891 return;
892
893 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
894 default:
895#ifndef NDEBUG
896 dbgs() << "SplitVectorResult #" << ResNo << ": ";
897 N->dump(&DAG);
898 dbgs() << "\n";
899#endif
900 report_fatal_error("Do not know how to split the result of this "
901 "operator!\n");
902
903 case ISD::MERGE_VALUES: SplitRes_MERGE_VALUES(N, ResNo, Lo, Hi); break;
904 case ISD::VSELECT:
905 case ISD::SELECT: SplitRes_SELECT(N, Lo, Hi); break;
906 case ISD::SELECT_CC: SplitRes_SELECT_CC(N, Lo, Hi); break;
907 case ISD::UNDEF: SplitRes_UNDEF(N, Lo, Hi); break;
908 case ISD::BITCAST: SplitVecRes_BITCAST(N, Lo, Hi); break;
909 case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR: SplitVecRes_BUILD_VECTOR(N, Lo, Hi); break;
910 case ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS: SplitVecRes_CONCAT_VECTORS(N, Lo, Hi); break;
911 case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR: SplitVecRes_EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR(N, Lo, Hi); break;
912 case ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR: SplitVecRes_INSERT_SUBVECTOR(N, Lo, Hi); break;
913 case ISD::FPOWI: SplitVecRes_FPOWI(N, Lo, Hi); break;
914 case ISD::FCOPYSIGN: SplitVecRes_FCOPYSIGN(N, Lo, Hi); break;
915 case ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT: SplitVecRes_INSERT_VECTOR_ELT(N, Lo, Hi); break;
916 case ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR:
917 case ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR:
918 SplitVecRes_ScalarOp(N, Lo, Hi);
919 break;
920 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG: SplitVecRes_InregOp(N, Lo, Hi); break;
921 case ISD::LOAD:
922 SplitVecRes_LOAD(cast<LoadSDNode>(N), Lo, Hi);
923 break;
924 case ISD::MLOAD:
925 SplitVecRes_MLOAD(cast<MaskedLoadSDNode>(N), Lo, Hi);
926 break;
927 case ISD::MGATHER:
928 SplitVecRes_MGATHER(cast<MaskedGatherSDNode>(N), Lo, Hi);
929 break;
930 case ISD::SETCC:
931 SplitVecRes_SETCC(N, Lo, Hi);
932 break;
933 case ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE:
934 SplitVecRes_VECTOR_SHUFFLE(cast<ShuffleVectorSDNode>(N), Lo, Hi);
935 break;
936 case ISD::VAARG:
937 SplitVecRes_VAARG(N, Lo, Hi);
938 break;
939
940 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
941 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
942 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
943 SplitVecRes_ExtVecInRegOp(N, Lo, Hi);
944 break;
945
946 case ISD::ABS:
947 case ISD::BITREVERSE:
948 case ISD::BSWAP:
949 case ISD::CTLZ:
950 case ISD::CTTZ:
951 case ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
952 case ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
953 case ISD::CTPOP:
954 case ISD::FABS:
955 case ISD::FCEIL:
956 case ISD::FCOS:
957 case ISD::FEXP:
958 case ISD::FEXP2:
959 case ISD::FFLOOR:
960 case ISD::FLOG:
961 case ISD::FLOG10:
962 case ISD::FLOG2:
963 case ISD::FNEARBYINT:
964 case ISD::FNEG:
965 case ISD::FREEZE:
966 case ISD::FP_EXTEND:
967 case ISD::FP_ROUND:
968 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT:
969 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT:
970 case ISD::FRINT:
971 case ISD::FROUND:
972 case ISD::FROUNDEVEN:
973 case ISD::FSIN:
974 case ISD::FSQRT:
975 case ISD::FTRUNC:
976 case ISD::SINT_TO_FP:
977 case ISD::TRUNCATE:
978 case ISD::UINT_TO_FP:
979 case ISD::FCANONICALIZE:
980 SplitVecRes_UnaryOp(N, Lo, Hi);
981 break;
982
983 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND:
984 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
985 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
986 SplitVecRes_ExtendOp(N, Lo, Hi);
987 break;
988
989 case ISD::ADD:
990 case ISD::SUB:
991 case ISD::MUL:
992 case ISD::MULHS:
993 case ISD::MULHU:
994 case ISD::FADD:
995 case ISD::FSUB:
996 case ISD::FMUL:
997 case ISD::FMINNUM:
998 case ISD::FMAXNUM:
999 case ISD::FMINIMUM:
1000 case ISD::FMAXIMUM:
1001 case ISD::SDIV:
1002 case ISD::UDIV:
1003 case ISD::FDIV:
1004 case ISD::FPOW:
1005 case ISD::AND:
1006 case ISD::OR:
1007 case ISD::XOR:
1008 case ISD::SHL:
1009 case ISD::SRA:
1010 case ISD::SRL:
1011 case ISD::UREM:
1012 case ISD::SREM:
1013 case ISD::FREM:
1014 case ISD::SMIN:
1015 case ISD::SMAX:
1016 case ISD::UMIN:
1017 case ISD::UMAX:
1018 case ISD::SADDSAT:
1019 case ISD::UADDSAT:
1020 case ISD::SSUBSAT:
1021 case ISD::USUBSAT:
1022 case ISD::SSHLSAT:
1023 case ISD::USHLSAT:
1024 case ISD::ROTL:
1025 case ISD::ROTR:
1026 SplitVecRes_BinOp(N, Lo, Hi);
1027 break;
1028 case ISD::FMA:
1029 case ISD::FSHL:
1030 case ISD::FSHR:
1031 SplitVecRes_TernaryOp(N, Lo, Hi);
1032 break;
1033
1034#define DAG_INSTRUCTION(NAME, NARG, ROUND_MODE, INTRINSIC, DAGN) \
1035 case ISD::STRICT_##DAGN:
1036#include "llvm/IR/ConstrainedOps.def"
1037 SplitVecRes_StrictFPOp(N, Lo, Hi);
1038 break;
1039
1040 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT_SAT:
1041 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT:
1042 SplitVecRes_FP_TO_XINT_SAT(N, Lo, Hi);
1043 break;
1044
1045 case ISD::UADDO:
1046 case ISD::SADDO:
1047 case ISD::USUBO:
1048 case ISD::SSUBO:
1049 case ISD::UMULO:
1050 case ISD::SMULO:
1051 SplitVecRes_OverflowOp(N, ResNo, Lo, Hi);
1052 break;
1053 case ISD::SMULFIX:
1054 case ISD::SMULFIXSAT:
1055 case ISD::UMULFIX:
1056 case ISD::UMULFIXSAT:
1057 case ISD::SDIVFIX:
1058 case ISD::SDIVFIXSAT:
1059 case ISD::UDIVFIX:
1060 case ISD::UDIVFIXSAT:
1061 SplitVecRes_FIX(N, Lo, Hi);
1062 break;
1063 }
1064
1065 // If Lo/Hi is null, the sub-method took care of registering results etc.
1066 if (Lo.getNode())
1067 SetSplitVector(SDValue(N, ResNo), Lo, Hi);
1068}
1069
1070void DAGTypeLegalizer::IncrementPointer(MemSDNode *N, EVT MemVT,
1071 MachinePointerInfo &MPI, SDValue &Ptr,
1072 uint64_t *ScaledOffset) {
1073 SDLoc DL(N);
1074 unsigned IncrementSize = MemVT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinSize() / 8;
1075
1076 if (MemVT.isScalableVector()) {
1077 SDNodeFlags Flags;
1078 SDValue BytesIncrement = DAG.getVScale(
1079 DL, Ptr.getValueType(),
1080 APInt(Ptr.getValueSizeInBits().getFixedSize(), IncrementSize));
1081 MPI = MachinePointerInfo(N->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
1082 Flags.setNoUnsignedWrap(true);
1083 if (ScaledOffset)
1084 *ScaledOffset += IncrementSize;
1085 Ptr = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, Ptr.getValueType(), Ptr, BytesIncrement,
1086 Flags);
1087 } else {
1088 MPI = N->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(IncrementSize);
1089 // Increment the pointer to the other half.
1090 Ptr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(DL, Ptr, TypeSize::Fixed(IncrementSize));
1091 }
1092}
1093
1094void DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecRes_BinOp(SDNode *N, SDValue &Lo,
1095 SDValue &Hi) {
1096 SDValue LHSLo, LHSHi;
1097 GetSplitVector(N->getOperand(0), LHSLo, LHSHi);
1098 SDValue RHSLo, RHSHi;
1099 GetSplitVector(N->getOperand(1), RHSLo, RHSHi);
1100 SDLoc dl(N);
1101
1102 const SDNodeFlags Flags = N->getFlags();
1103 unsigned Opcode = N->getOpcode();
1104 Lo = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, LHSLo.getValueType(), LHSLo, RHSLo, Flags);
1105 Hi = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, LHSHi.getValueType(), LHSHi, RHSHi, Flags);
1106}
1107
1108void DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecRes_TernaryOp(SDNode *N, SDValue &Lo,
1109 SDValue &Hi) {
1110 SDValue Op0Lo, Op0Hi;
1111 GetSplitVector(N->getOperand(0), Op0Lo, Op0Hi);
1112 SDValue Op1Lo, Op1Hi;
1113 GetSplitVector(N->getOperand(1), Op1Lo, Op1Hi);
1114 SDValue Op2Lo, Op2Hi;
1115 GetSplitVector(N->getOperand(2), Op2Lo, Op2Hi);
1116 SDLoc dl(N);
1117
1118 Lo = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, Op0Lo.getValueType(), Op0Lo, Op1Lo,
1119 Op2Lo, N->getFlags());
1120 Hi = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, Op0Hi.getValueType(), Op0Hi, Op1Hi,
1121 Op2Hi, N->getFlags());
1122}
1123
1124void DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecRes_FIX(SDNode *N, SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
1125 SDValue LHSLo, LHSHi;
1126 GetSplitVector(N->getOperand(0), LHSLo, LHSHi);
1127 SDValue RHSLo, RHSHi;
1128 GetSplitVector(N->getOperand(1), RHSLo, RHSHi);
1129 SDLoc dl(N);
1130 SDValue Op2 = N->getOperand(2);
1131
1132 unsigned Opcode = N->getOpcode();
1133 Lo = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, LHSLo.getValueType(), LHSLo, RHSLo, Op2,
1134 N->getFlags());
1135 Hi = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, LHSHi.getValueType(), LHSHi, RHSHi, Op2,
1136 N->getFlags());
1137}
1138
1139void DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecRes_BITCAST(SDNode *N, SDValue &Lo,
1140 SDValue &Hi) {
1141 // We know the result is a vector. The input may be either a vector or a
1142 // scalar value.
1143 EVT LoVT, HiVT;
1144 std::tie(LoVT, HiVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(N->getValueType(0));
1145 SDLoc dl(N);
1146
1147 SDValue InOp = N->getOperand(0);
1148 EVT InVT = InOp.getValueType();
1149
1150 // Handle some special cases efficiently.
1151 switch (getTypeAction(InVT)) {
1152 case TargetLowering::TypeLegal:
1153 case TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger:
1154 case TargetLowering::TypePromoteFloat:
1155 case TargetLowering::TypeSoftPromoteHalf:
1156 case TargetLowering::TypeSoftenFloat:
1157 case TargetLowering::TypeScalarizeVector:
1158 case TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector:
1159 break;
1160 case TargetLowering::TypeExpandInteger:
1161 case TargetLowering::TypeExpandFloat:
1162 // A scalar to vector conversion, where the scalar needs expansion.
1163 // If the vector is being split in two then we can just convert the
1164 // expanded pieces.
1165 if (LoVT == HiVT) {
1166 GetExpandedOp(InOp, Lo, Hi);
1167 if (DAG.getDataLayout().isBigEndian())
1168 std::swap(Lo, Hi);
1169 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, LoVT, Lo);
1170 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, HiVT, Hi);
1171 return;
1172 }
1173 break;
1174 case TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector:
1175 // If the input is a vector that needs to be split, convert each split
1176 // piece of the input now.
1177 GetSplitVector(InOp, Lo, Hi);
1178 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, LoVT, Lo);
1179 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, HiVT, Hi);
1180 return;
1181 case TargetLowering::TypeScalarizeScalableVector:
1182 report_fatal_error("Scalarization of scalable vectors is not supported.");
1183 }
1184
1185 // In the general case, convert the input to an integer and split it by hand.
1186 EVT LoIntVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), LoVT.getSizeInBits());
1187 EVT HiIntVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), HiVT.getSizeInBits());
1188 if (DAG.getDataLayout().isBigEndian())
1189 std::swap(LoIntVT, HiIntVT);
1190
1191 SplitInteger(BitConvertToInteger(InOp), LoIntVT, HiIntVT, Lo, Hi);
1192
1193 if (DAG.getDataLayout().isBigEndian())
1194 std::swap(Lo, Hi);
1195 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, LoVT, Lo);
1196 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, HiVT, Hi);
1197}

1200 SDValue &Hi) {

1205 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> LoOps(N->op_begin(), N->op_begin()+LoNumElts);
1206 Lo = DAG.getBuildVector(LoVT, dl, LoOps);

1249void DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecRes_INSERT_SUBVECTOR(SDNode *N, SDValue &Lo,
1250 SDValue &Hi) {
1251 SDValue Vec = N->getOperand(0);
1252 SDValue SubVec = N->getOperand(1);
1253 SDValue Idx = N->getOperand(2);
1254 SDLoc dl(N);
1255 GetSplitVector(Vec, Lo, Hi);
1256
1257 EVT VecVT = Vec.getValueType();
1258 unsigned VecElems = VecVT.getVectorNumElements();
1259 unsigned SubElems = SubVec.getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
1260
1261 // If we know the index is 0, and we know the subvector doesn't cross the
1262 // boundary between the halves, we can avoid spilling the vector, and insert
1263 // into the lower half of the split vector directly.
1264 // TODO: The IdxVal == 0 constraint is artificial, we could do this whenever
1265 // there is no boundary crossing. But those cases don't seem to get hit in
1266 // practice.
1267 unsigned IdxVal = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Idx)->getZExtValue();
1268 if ((IdxVal == 0) && (IdxVal + SubElems <= VecElems / 2)) {
1269 EVT LoVT, HiVT;
1270 std::tie(LoVT, HiVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(N->getValueType(0));
1271 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, dl, LoVT, Lo, SubVec, Idx);
1272 return;
1273 }
1274
1275 // Spill the vector to the stack.
1276 // In cases where the vector is illegal it will be broken down into parts
1277 // and stored in parts - we should use the alignment for the smallest part.
1278 Align SmallestAlign = DAG.getReducedAlign(VecVT, /*UseABI=*/false);
1279 SDValue StackPtr =
1280 DAG.CreateStackTemporary(VecVT.getStoreSize(), SmallestAlign);
1281 auto &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
1282 auto FrameIndex = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(StackPtr.getNode())->getIndex();
1283 auto PtrInfo = MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FrameIndex);
1284
1285 SDValue Store = DAG.getStore(DAG.getEntryNode(), dl, Vec, StackPtr, PtrInfo,
1286 SmallestAlign);
1287
1288 // Store the new subvector into the specified index.
1289 SDValue SubVecPtr = TLI.getVectorElementPointer(DAG, StackPtr, VecVT, Idx);
1290 Store = DAG.getStore(Store, dl, SubVec, SubVecPtr,
1291 MachinePointerInfo::getUnknownStack(MF));
1292
1293 // Load the Lo part from the stack slot.
1294 Lo = DAG.getLoad(Lo.getValueType(), dl, Store, StackPtr, PtrInfo,
1295 SmallestAlign);
1296
1297 // Increment the pointer to the other part.
1298 unsigned IncrementSize = Lo.getValueSizeInBits() / 8;
1299 StackPtr =
1300 DAG.getMemBasePlusOffset(StackPtr, TypeSize::Fixed(IncrementSize), dl);
1301
1302 // Load the Hi part from the stack slot.
1303 Hi = DAG.getLoad(Hi.getValueType(), dl, Store, StackPtr,
1304 PtrInfo.getWithOffset(IncrementSize), SmallestAlign);
1305}

1350void DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecRes_ExtVecInRegOp(SDNode *N, SDValue &Lo,
1351 SDValue &Hi) {
1352 unsigned Opcode = N->getOpcode();
1353 SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
1354
1355 SDLoc dl(N);
1356 SDValue InLo, InHi;
1357
1358 if (getTypeAction(N0.getValueType()) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector)
1359 GetSplitVector(N0, InLo, InHi);
1360 else
1361 std::tie(InLo, InHi) = DAG.SplitVectorOperand(N, 0);
1362
1363 EVT InLoVT = InLo.getValueType();
1364 unsigned InNumElements = InLoVT.getVectorNumElements();
1365
1366 EVT OutLoVT, OutHiVT;
1367 std::tie(OutLoVT, OutHiVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(N->getValueType(0));
1368 unsigned OutNumElements = OutLoVT.getVectorNumElements();
1369 assert((2 * OutNumElements) <= InNumElements &&
1370 "Illegal extend vector in reg split");
1371
1372 // *_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG instructions extend the lowest elements of the
1373 // input vector (i.e. we only use InLo):
1374 // OutLo will extend the first OutNumElements from InLo.
1375 // OutHi will extend the next OutNumElements from InLo.
1376
1377 // Shuffle the elements from InLo for OutHi into the bottom elements to
1378 // create a 'fake' InHi.
1379 SmallVector<int, 8> SplitHi(InNumElements, -1);
1380 for (unsigned i = 0; i != OutNumElements; ++i)
1381 SplitHi[i] = i + OutNumElements;
1382 InHi = DAG.getVectorShuffle(InLoVT, dl, InLo, DAG.getUNDEF(InLoVT), SplitHi);
1383
1384 Lo = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, OutLoVT, InLo);
1385 Hi = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, OutHiVT, InHi);
1386}

1388void DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecRes_StrictFPOp(SDNode *N, SDValue &Lo,
1389 SDValue &Hi) {
1390 unsigned NumOps = N->getNumOperands();
1391 SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0);
1392 EVT LoVT, HiVT;
1393 SDLoc dl(N);
1394 std::tie(LoVT, HiVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(N->getValueType(0));
1395
1396 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> OpsLo(NumOps);
1397 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> OpsHi(NumOps);
1398
1399 // The Chain is the first operand.
1400 OpsLo[0] = Chain;
1401 OpsHi[0] = Chain;
1402
1403 // Now process the remaining operands.
1404 for (unsigned i = 1; i < NumOps; ++i) {
1405 SDValue Op = N->getOperand(i);
1406 SDValue OpLo = Op;
1407 SDValue OpHi = Op;
1408
1409 EVT InVT = Op.getValueType();
1410 if (InVT.isVector()) {
1411 // If the input also splits, handle it directly for a
1412 // compile time speedup. Otherwise split it by hand.
1413 if (getTypeAction(InVT) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector)
1414 GetSplitVector(Op, OpLo, OpHi);
1415 else
1416 std::tie(OpLo, OpHi) = DAG.SplitVectorOperand(N, i);
1417 }
1418
1419 OpsLo[i] = OpLo;
1420 OpsHi[i] = OpHi;
1421 }
1422
1423 EVT LoValueVTs[] = {LoVT, MVT::Other};
1424 EVT HiValueVTs[] = {HiVT, MVT::Other};
1425 Lo = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, DAG.getVTList(LoValueVTs), OpsLo,
1426 N->getFlags());
1427 Hi = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, DAG.getVTList(HiValueVTs), OpsHi,
1428 N->getFlags());
1429
1430 // Build a factor node to remember that this Op is independent of the
1431 // other one.
1432 Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other,
1433 Lo.getValue(1), Hi.getValue(1));
1434
1435 // Legalize the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to
1436 // use the new one.
1437 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Chain);
1438}
1439
1440SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::UnrollVectorOp_StrictFP(SDNode *N, unsigned ResNE) {
1441 SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0);
1442 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
1443 unsigned NE = VT.getVectorNumElements();
1444 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
1445 SDLoc dl(N);
1446
1447 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Scalars;
1448 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Operands(N->getNumOperands());
1449
1450 // If ResNE is 0, fully unroll the vector op.
1451 if (ResNE == 0)
1452 ResNE = NE;
1453 else if (NE > ResNE)
1454 NE = ResNE;
1455
1456 //The results of each unrolled operation, including the chain.
1457 EVT ChainVTs[] = {EltVT, MVT::Other};
1458 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Chains;
1459
1460 unsigned i;
1461 for (i = 0; i != NE; ++i) {
1462 Operands[0] = Chain;
1463 for (unsigned j = 1, e = N->getNumOperands(); j != e; ++j) {
1464 SDValue Operand = N->getOperand(j);
1465 EVT OperandVT = Operand.getValueType();
1466 if (OperandVT.isVector()) {
1467 EVT OperandEltVT = OperandVT.getVectorElementType();
1468 Operands[j] = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, OperandEltVT,
1469 Operand, DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, dl));
1470 } else {
1471 Operands[j] = Operand;
1472 }
1473 }
1474 SDValue Scalar = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, ChainVTs, Operands);
1475 Scalar.getNode()->setFlags(N->getFlags());
1476
1477 //Add in the scalar as well as its chain value to the
1478 //result vectors.
1479 Scalars.push_back(Scalar);
1480 Chains.push_back(Scalar.getValue(1));
1481 }
1482
1483 for (; i < ResNE; ++i)
1484 Scalars.push_back(DAG.getUNDEF(EltVT));
1485
1486 // Build a new factor node to connect the chain back together.
1487 Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Chains);
1488 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Chain);
1489
1490 // Create a new BUILD_VECTOR node
1491 EVT VecVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), EltVT, ResNE);
1492 return DAG.getBuildVector(VecVT, dl, Scalars);
1493}
1494
1495void DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecRes_OverflowOp(SDNode *N, unsigned ResNo,
1496 SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
1497 SDLoc dl(N);
1498 EVT ResVT = N->getValueType(0);
1499 EVT OvVT = N->getValueType(1);
1500 EVT LoResVT, HiResVT, LoOvVT, HiOvVT;
1501 std::tie(LoResVT, HiResVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(ResVT);
1502 std::tie(LoOvVT, HiOvVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(OvVT);
1503
1504 SDValue LoLHS, HiLHS, LoRHS, HiRHS;
1505 if (getTypeAction(ResVT) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector) {
1506 GetSplitVector(N->getOperand(0), LoLHS, HiLHS);
1507 GetSplitVector(N->getOperand(1), LoRHS, HiRHS);
1508 } else {
1509 std::tie(LoLHS, HiLHS) = DAG.SplitVectorOperand(N, 0);
1510 std::tie(LoRHS, HiRHS) = DAG.SplitVectorOperand(N, 1);
1511 }
1512
1513 unsigned Opcode = N->getOpcode();
1514 SDVTList LoVTs = DAG.getVTList(LoResVT, LoOvVT);
1515 SDVTList HiVTs = DAG.getVTList(HiResVT, HiOvVT);
1516 SDNode *LoNode = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, LoVTs, LoLHS, LoRHS).getNode();
1517 SDNode *HiNode = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, HiVTs, HiLHS, HiRHS).getNode();
1518 LoNode->setFlags(N->getFlags());
1519 HiNode->setFlags(N->getFlags());
1520
1521 Lo = SDValue(LoNode, ResNo);
1522 Hi = SDValue(HiNode, ResNo);
1523
1524 // Replace the other vector result not being explicitly split here.
1525 unsigned OtherNo = 1 - ResNo;
1526 EVT OtherVT = N->getValueType(OtherNo);
1527 if (getTypeAction(OtherVT) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector) {
1528 SetSplitVector(SDValue(N, OtherNo),
1529 SDValue(LoNode, OtherNo), SDValue(HiNode, OtherNo));
1530 } else {
1531 SDValue OtherVal = DAG.getNode(
1532 ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, OtherVT,
1533 SDValue(LoNode, OtherNo), SDValue(HiNode, OtherNo));
1534 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, OtherNo), OtherVal);
1535 }
1536}
1537
1538void DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecRes_INSERT_VECTOR_ELT(SDNode *N, SDValue &Lo,
1539 SDValue &Hi) {
1540 SDValue Vec = N->getOperand(0);
1541 SDValue Elt = N->getOperand(1);
1542 SDValue Idx = N->getOperand(2);
1543 SDLoc dl(N);
1544 GetSplitVector(Vec, Lo, Hi);
1545
1546 if (ConstantSDNode *CIdx = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Idx)) {
1547 unsigned IdxVal = CIdx->getZExtValue();
1548 unsigned LoNumElts = Lo.getValueType().getVectorMinNumElements();
1549 if (IdxVal < LoNumElts) {
1550 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, dl,
1551 Lo.getValueType(), Lo, Elt, Idx);
1552 return;
1553 } else if (!Vec.getValueType().isScalableVector()) {
1554 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, Hi.getValueType(), Hi, Elt,
1555 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(IdxVal - LoNumElts, dl));
1556 return;
1557 }
1558 }
1559
1560 // See if the target wants to custom expand this node.
1561 if (CustomLowerNode(N, N->getValueType(0), true))
1562 return;
1563
1564 // Make the vector elements byte-addressable if they aren't already.
1565 EVT VecVT = Vec.getValueType();
1566 EVT EltVT = VecVT.getVectorElementType();
1567 if (VecVT.getScalarSizeInBits() < 8) {
1568 EltVT = MVT::i8;
1569 VecVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), EltVT,
1570 VecVT.getVectorElementCount());
1571 Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, VecVT, Vec);
1572 // Extend the element type to match if needed.
1573 if (EltVT.bitsGT(Elt.getValueType()))
1574 Elt = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, EltVT, Elt);
1575 }
1576
1577 // Spill the vector to the stack.
1578 // In cases where the vector is illegal it will be broken down into parts
1579 // and stored in parts - we should use the alignment for the smallest part.
1580 Align SmallestAlign = DAG.getReducedAlign(VecVT, /*UseABI=*/false);
1581 SDValue StackPtr =
1582 DAG.CreateStackTemporary(VecVT.getStoreSize(), SmallestAlign);
1583 auto &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
1584 auto FrameIndex = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(StackPtr.getNode())->getIndex();
1585 auto PtrInfo = MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FrameIndex);
1586
1587 SDValue Store = DAG.getStore(DAG.getEntryNode(), dl, Vec, StackPtr, PtrInfo,
1588 SmallestAlign);
1589
1590 // Store the new element. This may be larger than the vector element type,
1591 // so use a truncating store.
1592 SDValue EltPtr = TLI.getVectorElementPointer(DAG, StackPtr, VecVT, Idx);
1593 Store = DAG.getTruncStore(
1594 Store, dl, Elt, EltPtr, MachinePointerInfo::getUnknownStack(MF), EltVT,
1595 commonAlignment(SmallestAlign,
1596 EltVT.getFixedSizeInBits() / 8));
1597
1598 EVT LoVT, HiVT;
1599 std::tie(LoVT, HiVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(VecVT);
1600
1601 // Load the Lo part from the stack slot.
1602 Lo = DAG.getLoad(LoVT, dl, Store, StackPtr, PtrInfo, SmallestAlign);
1603
1604 // Increment the pointer to the other part.
1605 auto Load = cast<LoadSDNode>(Lo);
1606 MachinePointerInfo MPI = Load->getPointerInfo();
1607 IncrementPointer(Load, LoVT, MPI, StackPtr);
1608
1609 Hi = DAG.getLoad(HiVT, dl, Store, StackPtr, MPI, SmallestAlign);
1610
1611 // If we adjusted the original type, we need to truncate the results.
1612 std::tie(LoVT, HiVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(N->getValueType(0));
1613 if (LoVT != Lo.getValueType())
1614 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, LoVT, Lo);
1615 if (HiVT != Hi.getValueType())
1616 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, HiVT, Hi);
1617}

1619void DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecRes_ScalarOp(SDNode *N, SDValue &Lo,
1620 SDValue &Hi) {
1621 EVT LoVT, HiVT;
1622 SDLoc dl(N);
1623 std::tie(LoVT, HiVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(N->getValueType(0));
1624 Lo = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, LoVT, N->getOperand(0));
1625 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR) {
1626 Hi = DAG.getUNDEF(HiVT);
1627 } else {
1628 assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR && "Unexpected opcode");
1629 Hi = Lo;
1630 }

1632
1633void DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecRes_LOAD(LoadSDNode *LD, SDValue &Lo,
1634 SDValue &Hi) {
1635 assert(ISD::isUNINDEXEDLoad(LD) && "Indexed load during type legalization!");
1636 EVT LoVT, HiVT;
1637 SDLoc dl(LD);
1638 std::tie(LoVT, HiVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(LD->getValueType(0));
1639
1640 ISD::LoadExtType ExtType = LD->getExtensionType();
1641 SDValue Ch = LD->getChain();
1642 SDValue Ptr = LD->getBasePtr();
1643 SDValue Offset = DAG.getUNDEF(Ptr.getValueType());
1644 EVT MemoryVT = LD->getMemoryVT();
1645 MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags = LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags();
1646 AAMDNodes AAInfo = LD->getAAInfo();
1647
1648 EVT LoMemVT, HiMemVT;
1649 std::tie(LoMemVT, HiMemVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(MemoryVT);
1650
1651 if (!LoMemVT.isByteSized() || !HiMemVT.isByteSized()) {
1652 SDValue Value, NewChain;
1653 std::tie(Value, NewChain) = TLI.scalarizeVectorLoad(LD, DAG);
1654 std::tie(Lo, Hi) = DAG.SplitVector(Value, dl);
1655 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(LD, 1), NewChain);
1656 return;
1657 }
1658
1659 Lo = DAG.getLoad(ISD::UNINDEXED, ExtType, LoVT, dl, Ch, Ptr, Offset,
1660 LD->getPointerInfo(), LoMemVT, LD->getOriginalAlign(),
1661 MMOFlags, AAInfo);
1662
1663 MachinePointerInfo MPI;
1664 IncrementPointer(LD, LoMemVT, MPI, Ptr);
1665
1666 Hi = DAG.getLoad(ISD::UNINDEXED, ExtType, HiVT, dl, Ch, Ptr, Offset, MPI,
1667 HiMemVT, LD->getOriginalAlign(), MMOFlags, AAInfo);
1668
1669 // Build a factor node to remember that this load is independent of the
1670 // other one.
1671 Ch = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Lo.getValue(1),
1672 Hi.getValue(1));
1673
1674 // Legalize the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to
1675 // use the new one.
1676 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(LD, 1), Ch);
1677}
1678
1679void DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecRes_MLOAD(MaskedLoadSDNode *MLD,
1680 SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
1681 assert(MLD->isUnindexed() && "Indexed masked load during type legalization!");
1682 EVT LoVT, HiVT;
1683 SDLoc dl(MLD);
1684 std::tie(LoVT, HiVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(MLD->getValueType(0));
1685
1686 SDValue Ch = MLD->getChain();
1687 SDValue Ptr = MLD->getBasePtr();
1688 SDValue Offset = MLD->getOffset();
1689 assert(Offset.isUndef() && "Unexpected indexed masked load offset");
1690 SDValue Mask = MLD->getMask();
1691 SDValue PassThru = MLD->getPassThru();
1692 Align Alignment = MLD->getOriginalAlign();
1693 ISD::LoadExtType ExtType = MLD->getExtensionType();
1694
1695 // Split Mask operand
1696 SDValue MaskLo, MaskHi;
1697 if (Mask.getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC) {
1698 SplitVecRes_SETCC(Mask.getNode(), MaskLo, MaskHi);
1699 } else {
1700 if (getTypeAction(Mask.getValueType()) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector)
1701 GetSplitVector(Mask, MaskLo, MaskHi);
1702 else
1703 std::tie(MaskLo, MaskHi) = DAG.SplitVector(Mask, dl);
1704 }
1705
1706 EVT MemoryVT = MLD->getMemoryVT();
1707 EVT LoMemVT, HiMemVT;
1708 bool HiIsEmpty = false;
1709 std::tie(LoMemVT, HiMemVT) =
1710 DAG.GetDependentSplitDestVTs(MemoryVT, LoVT, &HiIsEmpty);
1711
1712 SDValue PassThruLo, PassThruHi;
1713 if (getTypeAction(PassThru.getValueType()) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector)
1714 GetSplitVector(PassThru, PassThruLo, PassThruHi);
1715 else
1716 std::tie(PassThruLo, PassThruHi) = DAG.SplitVector(PassThru, dl);
1717
1718 unsigned LoSize = MemoryLocation::getSizeOrUnknown(LoMemVT.getStoreSize());
1719 MachineMemOperand *MMO = DAG.getMachineFunction().getMachineMemOperand(
1720 MLD->getPointerInfo(), MachineMemOperand::MOLoad, LoSize, Alignment,
1721 MLD->getAAInfo(), MLD->getRanges());
1722
1723 Lo = DAG.getMaskedLoad(LoVT, dl, Ch, Ptr, Offset, MaskLo, PassThruLo, LoMemVT,
1724 MMO, MLD->getAddressingMode(), ExtType,
1725 MLD->isExpandingLoad());
1726
1727 if (HiIsEmpty) {
1728 // The hi masked load has zero storage size. We therefore simply set it to
1729 // the low masked load and rely on subsequent removal from the chain.
1730 Hi = Lo;
1731 } else {
1732 // Generate hi masked load.
1733 Ptr = TLI.IncrementMemoryAddress(Ptr, MaskLo, dl, LoMemVT, DAG,
1734 MLD->isExpandingLoad());
1735 unsigned HiSize = MemoryLocation::getSizeOrUnknown(HiMemVT.getStoreSize());
1736
1737 MachinePointerInfo MPI;
1738 if (LoMemVT.isScalableVector())
1739 MPI = MachinePointerInfo(MLD->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
1740 else
1741 MPI = MLD->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(
1742 LoMemVT.getStoreSize().getFixedSize());
1743
1744 MMO = DAG.getMachineFunction().getMachineMemOperand(
1745 MPI, MachineMemOperand::MOLoad, HiSize, Alignment, MLD->getAAInfo(),
1746 MLD->getRanges());
1747
1748 Hi = DAG.getMaskedLoad(HiVT, dl, Ch, Ptr, Offset, MaskHi, PassThruHi,
1749 HiMemVT, MMO, MLD->getAddressingMode(), ExtType,
1750 MLD->isExpandingLoad());
1751 }
1752
1753 // Build a factor node to remember that this load is independent of the
1754 // other one.
1755 Ch = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Lo.getValue(1),
1756 Hi.getValue(1));
1757
1758 // Legalize the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to
1759 // use the new one.
1760 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(MLD, 1), Ch);
1761
1762}

1764void DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecRes_MGATHER(MaskedGatherSDNode *MGT,
1765 SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
1766 EVT LoVT, HiVT;
1767 SDLoc dl(MGT);
1768 std::tie(LoVT, HiVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(MGT->getValueType(0));
1769
1770 SDValue Ch = MGT->getChain();
1771 SDValue Ptr = MGT->getBasePtr();
1772 SDValue Mask = MGT->getMask();
1773 SDValue PassThru = MGT->getPassThru();
1774 SDValue Index = MGT->getIndex();
1775 SDValue Scale = MGT->getScale();
1776 EVT MemoryVT = MGT->getMemoryVT();
1777 Align Alignment = MGT->getOriginalAlign();
1778 ISD::LoadExtType ExtType = MGT->getExtensionType();
1779
1780 // Split Mask operand
1781 SDValue MaskLo, MaskHi;
1782 if (Mask.getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC) {
1783 SplitVecRes_SETCC(Mask.getNode(), MaskLo, MaskHi);
1784 } else {
1785 if (getTypeAction(Mask.getValueType()) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector)
1786 GetSplitVector(Mask, MaskLo, MaskHi);
1787 else
1788 std::tie(MaskLo, MaskHi) = DAG.SplitVector(Mask, dl);
1789 }
1790
1791 EVT LoMemVT, HiMemVT;
1792 // Split MemoryVT
1793 std::tie(LoMemVT, HiMemVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(MemoryVT);
1794
1795 SDValue PassThruLo, PassThruHi;
1796 if (getTypeAction(PassThru.getValueType()) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector)
1797 GetSplitVector(PassThru, PassThruLo, PassThruHi);
1798 else
1799 std::tie(PassThruLo, PassThruHi) = DAG.SplitVector(PassThru, dl);
1800
1801 SDValue IndexHi, IndexLo;
1802 if (getTypeAction(Index.getValueType()) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector)
1803 GetSplitVector(Index, IndexLo, IndexHi);
1804 else
1805 std::tie(IndexLo, IndexHi) = DAG.SplitVector(Index, dl);
1806
1807 MachineMemOperand *MMO = DAG.getMachineFunction().getMachineMemOperand(
1808 MGT->getPointerInfo(), MachineMemOperand::MOLoad,
1809 MemoryLocation::UnknownSize, Alignment, MGT->getAAInfo(),
1810 MGT->getRanges());
1811
1812 SDValue OpsLo[] = {Ch, PassThruLo, MaskLo, Ptr, IndexLo, Scale};
1813 Lo = DAG.getMaskedGather(DAG.getVTList(LoVT, MVT::Other), LoMemVT, dl, OpsLo,
1814 MMO, MGT->getIndexType(), ExtType);
1815
1816 SDValue OpsHi[] = {Ch, PassThruHi, MaskHi, Ptr, IndexHi, Scale};
1817 Hi = DAG.getMaskedGather(DAG.getVTList(HiVT, MVT::Other), HiMemVT, dl, OpsHi,
1818 MMO, MGT->getIndexType(), ExtType);
1819
1820 // Build a factor node to remember that this load is independent of the
1821 // other one.
1822 Ch = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Lo.getValue(1),
1823 Hi.getValue(1));
1824
1825 // Legalize the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to
1826 // use the new one.
1827 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(MGT, 1), Ch);
1828}

1831void DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecRes_SETCC(SDNode *N, SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
1832 assert(N->getValueType(0).isVector() &&
1833 N->getOperand(0).getValueType().isVector() &&
1834 "Operand types must be vectors");
1835
1836 EVT LoVT, HiVT;
1837 SDLoc DL(N);
1838 std::tie(LoVT, HiVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(N->getValueType(0));
1839
1840 // If the input also splits, handle it directly. Otherwise split it by hand.
1841 SDValue LL, LH, RL, RH;
1842 if (getTypeAction(N->getOperand(0).getValueType()) ==
1843 TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector)
1844 GetSplitVector(N->getOperand(0), LL, LH);
1845 else
1846 std::tie(LL, LH) = DAG.SplitVectorOperand(N, 0);
1847
1848 if (getTypeAction(N->getOperand(1).getValueType()) ==
1849 TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector)
1850 GetSplitVector(N->getOperand(1), RL, RH);
1851 else
1852 std::tie(RL, RH) = DAG.SplitVectorOperand(N, 1);
1853
1854 Lo = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), DL, LoVT, LL, RL, N->getOperand(2));
1855 Hi = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), DL, HiVT, LH, RH, N->getOperand(2));
1856}

1858void DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecRes_UnaryOp(SDNode *N, SDValue &Lo,
1859 SDValue &Hi) {
1860 // Get the dest types - they may not match the input types, e.g. int_to_fp.
1861 EVT LoVT, HiVT;
1862 SDLoc dl(N);
1863 std::tie(LoVT, HiVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(N->getValueType(0));
1864
1865 // If the input also splits, handle it directly for a compile time speedup.
1866 // Otherwise split it by hand.
1867 unsigned OpNo = N->isStrictFPOpcode() ? 1 : 0;
1868 EVT InVT = N->getOperand(OpNo).getValueType();
1869 if (getTypeAction(InVT) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector)
1870 GetSplitVector(N->getOperand(OpNo), Lo, Hi);
1871 else
1872 std::tie(Lo, Hi) = DAG.SplitVectorOperand(N, OpNo);
1873
1874 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::FP_ROUND) {
1875 Lo = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, LoVT, Lo, N->getOperand(1),
1876 N->getFlags());
1877 Hi = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, HiVT, Hi, N->getOperand(1),
1878 N->getFlags());
1879 } else {
1880 Lo = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, LoVT, Lo, N->getFlags());
1881 Hi = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, HiVT, Hi, N->getFlags());
1882 }
1883}
1884
1885void DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecRes_ExtendOp(SDNode *N, SDValue &Lo,
1886 SDValue &Hi) {
1887 SDLoc dl(N);
1888 EVT SrcVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
1889 EVT DestVT = N->getValueType(0);
1890 EVT LoVT, HiVT;
1891 std::tie(LoVT, HiVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(DestVT);
1892
1893 // We can do better than a generic split operation if the extend is doing
1894 // more than just doubling the width of the elements and the following are
1895 // true:
1896 // - The number of vector elements is even,
1897 // - the source type is legal,
1898 // - the type of a split source is illegal,
1899 // - the type of an extended (by doubling element size) source is legal, and
1900 // - the type of that extended source when split is legal.
1901 //
1902 // This won't necessarily completely legalize the operation, but it will
1903 // more effectively move in the right direction and prevent falling down
1904 // to scalarization in many cases due to the input vector being split too
1905 // far.
1906 if (SrcVT.getVectorElementCount().isKnownEven() &&
1907 SrcVT.getScalarSizeInBits() * 2 < DestVT.getScalarSizeInBits()) {
1908 LLVMContext &Ctx = *DAG.getContext();
1909 EVT NewSrcVT = SrcVT.widenIntegerVectorElementType(Ctx);
1910 EVT SplitSrcVT = SrcVT.getHalfNumVectorElementsVT(Ctx);
1911
1912 EVT SplitLoVT, SplitHiVT;
1913 std::tie(SplitLoVT, SplitHiVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(NewSrcVT);
1914 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(SrcVT) && !TLI.isTypeLegal(SplitSrcVT) &&
1915 TLI.isTypeLegal(NewSrcVT) && TLI.isTypeLegal(SplitLoVT)) {
1916 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Split vector extend via incremental extend:";
1917 N->dump(&DAG); dbgs() << "\n");
1918 // Extend the source vector by one step.
1919 SDValue NewSrc =
1920 DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, NewSrcVT, N->getOperand(0));
1921 // Get the low and high halves of the new, extended one step, vector.
1922 std::tie(Lo, Hi) = DAG.SplitVector(NewSrc, dl);
1923 // Extend those vector halves the rest of the way.
1924 Lo = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, LoVT, Lo);
1925 Hi = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, HiVT, Hi);
1926 return;
1927 }
1928 }
1929 // Fall back to the generic unary operator splitting otherwise.
1930 SplitVecRes_UnaryOp(N, Lo, Hi);
1931}
1932
1933void DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecRes_VECTOR_SHUFFLE(ShuffleVectorSDNode *N,
1934 SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
1935 // The low and high parts of the original input give four input vectors.
1936 SDValue Inputs[4];
1937 SDLoc dl(N);
1938 GetSplitVector(N->getOperand(0), Inputs[0], Inputs[1]);
1939 GetSplitVector(N->getOperand(1), Inputs[2], Inputs[3]);
1940 EVT NewVT = Inputs[0].getValueType();
1941 unsigned NewElts = NewVT.getVectorNumElements();
1942
1943 // If Lo or Hi uses elements from at most two of the four input vectors, then
1944 // express it as a vector shuffle of those two inputs. Otherwise extract the
1945 // input elements by hand and construct the Lo/Hi output using a BUILD_VECTOR.
1946 SmallVector<int, 16> Ops;
1947 for (unsigned High = 0; High < 2; ++High) {
1948 SDValue &Output = High ? Hi : Lo;
1949
1950 // Build a shuffle mask for the output, discovering on the fly which
1951 // input vectors to use as shuffle operands (recorded in InputUsed).
1952 // If building a suitable shuffle vector proves too hard, then bail
1953 // out with useBuildVector set.
1954 unsigned InputUsed[2] = { -1U, -1U }; // Not yet discovered.
1955 unsigned FirstMaskIdx = High * NewElts;
1956 bool useBuildVector = false;
1957 for (unsigned MaskOffset = 0; MaskOffset < NewElts; ++MaskOffset) {
1958 // The mask element. This indexes into the input.
1959 int Idx = N->getMaskElt(FirstMaskIdx + MaskOffset);
1960
1961 // The input vector this mask element indexes into.
1962 unsigned Input = (unsigned)Idx / NewElts;
1963
1964 if (Input >= array_lengthof(Inputs)) {
1965 // The mask element does not index into any input vector.
1966 Ops.push_back(-1);
1967 continue;
1968 }
1969
1970 // Turn the index into an offset from the start of the input vector.
1971 Idx -= Input * NewElts;
1972
1973 // Find or create a shuffle vector operand to hold this input.
1974 unsigned OpNo;
1975 for (OpNo = 0; OpNo < array_lengthof(InputUsed); ++OpNo) {
1976 if (InputUsed[OpNo] == Input) {
1977 // This input vector is already an operand.
1978 break;
1979 } else if (InputUsed[OpNo] == -1U) {
1980 // Create a new operand for this input vector.
1981 InputUsed[OpNo] = Input;
1982 break;
1983 }
1984 }
1985
1986 if (OpNo >= array_lengthof(InputUsed)) {
1987 // More than two input vectors used! Give up on trying to create a
1988 // shuffle vector. Insert all elements into a BUILD_VECTOR instead.
1989 useBuildVector = true;
1990 break;
1991 }
1992
1993 // Add the mask index for the new shuffle vector.
1994 Ops.push_back(Idx + OpNo * NewElts);
1995 }
1996
1997 if (useBuildVector) {
1998 EVT EltVT = NewVT.getVectorElementType();
1999 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> SVOps;
2000
2001 // Extract the input elements by hand.
2002 for (unsigned MaskOffset = 0; MaskOffset < NewElts; ++MaskOffset) {
2003 // The mask element. This indexes into the input.
2004 int Idx = N->getMaskElt(FirstMaskIdx + MaskOffset);
2005
2006 // The input vector this mask element indexes into.
2007 unsigned Input = (unsigned)Idx / NewElts;
2008
2009 if (Input >= array_lengthof(Inputs)) {
2010 // The mask element is "undef" or indexes off the end of the input.
2011 SVOps.push_back(DAG.getUNDEF(EltVT));
2012 continue;
2013 }
2014
2015 // Turn the index into an offset from the start of the input vector.
2016 Idx -= Input * NewElts;
2017
2018 // Extract the vector element by hand.
2019 SVOps.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, EltVT,
2020 Inputs[Input],
2021 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl)));
2022 }
2023
2024 // Construct the Lo/Hi output using a BUILD_VECTOR.
2025 Output = DAG.getBuildVector(NewVT, dl, SVOps);
2026 } else if (InputUsed[0] == -1U) {
2027 // No input vectors were used! The result is undefined.
2028 Output = DAG.getUNDEF(NewVT);
2029 } else {
2030 SDValue Op0 = Inputs[InputUsed[0]];
2031 // If only one input was used, use an undefined vector for the other.
2032 SDValue Op1 = InputUsed[1] == -1U ?
2033 DAG.getUNDEF(NewVT) : Inputs[InputUsed[1]];
2034 // At least one input vector was used. Create a new shuffle vector.
2035 Output = DAG.getVectorShuffle(NewVT, dl, Op0, Op1, Ops);
2036 }
2037
2038 Ops.clear();
2039 }
2040}

2042void DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecRes_VAARG(SDNode *N, SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {

2079//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2080// Operand Vector Splitting
2081//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2082
2083/// This method is called when the specified operand of the specified node is
2084/// found to need vector splitting. At this point, all of the result types of
2085/// the node are known to be legal, but other operands of the node may need
2086/// legalization as well as the specified one.
2087bool DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVectorOperand(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
2088 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Split node operand: "; N->dump(&DAG); dbgs() << "\n");
2089 SDValue Res = SDValue();
2090
2091 // See if the target wants to custom split this node.
2092 if (CustomLowerNode(N, N->getOperand(OpNo).getValueType(), false))
2093 return false;
2094
2095 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
2096 default:
2097#ifndef NDEBUG
2098 dbgs() << "SplitVectorOperand Op #" << OpNo << ": ";
2099 N->dump(&DAG);
2100 dbgs() << "\n";
2101#endif
2102 report_fatal_error("Do not know how to split this operator's "
2103 "operand!\n");
2104
2105 case ISD::SETCC: Res = SplitVecOp_VSETCC(N); break;
2106 case ISD::BITCAST: Res = SplitVecOp_BITCAST(N); break;
2107 case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR: Res = SplitVecOp_EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR(N); break;
2108 case ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR: Res = SplitVecOp_INSERT_SUBVECTOR(N, OpNo); break;
2109 case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT:Res = SplitVecOp_EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(N); break;
2110 case ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS: Res = SplitVecOp_CONCAT_VECTORS(N); break;
2111 case ISD::TRUNCATE:
2112 Res = SplitVecOp_TruncateHelper(N);
2113 break;
2114 case ISD::STRICT_FP_ROUND:
2115 case ISD::FP_ROUND: Res = SplitVecOp_FP_ROUND(N); break;
2116 case ISD::FCOPYSIGN: Res = SplitVecOp_FCOPYSIGN(N); break;
2117 case ISD::STORE:
2118 Res = SplitVecOp_STORE(cast<StoreSDNode>(N), OpNo);
2119 break;
2120 case ISD::MSTORE:
2121 Res = SplitVecOp_MSTORE(cast<MaskedStoreSDNode>(N), OpNo);
2122 break;
2123 case ISD::MSCATTER:
2124 Res = SplitVecOp_MSCATTER(cast<MaskedScatterSDNode>(N), OpNo);
2125 break;
2126 case ISD::MGATHER:
2127 Res = SplitVecOp_MGATHER(cast<MaskedGatherSDNode>(N), OpNo);
2128 break;
2129 case ISD::VSELECT:
2130 Res = SplitVecOp_VSELECT(N, OpNo);
2131 break;
2132 case ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP:
2133 case ISD::STRICT_UINT_TO_FP:
2134 case ISD::SINT_TO_FP:
2135 case ISD::UINT_TO_FP:
2136 if (N->getValueType(0).bitsLT(
2137 N->getOperand(N->isStrictFPOpcode() ? 1 : 0).getValueType()))
2138 Res = SplitVecOp_TruncateHelper(N);
2139 else
2140 Res = SplitVecOp_UnaryOp(N);
2141 break;
2142 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT:
2143 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT_SAT:
2144 Res = SplitVecOp_FP_TO_XINT_SAT(N);
2145 break;
2146 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT:
2147 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT:
2148 case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT:
2149 case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_UINT:
2150 case ISD::STRICT_FP_EXTEND:
2151 case ISD::FP_EXTEND:
2152 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
2153 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
2154 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND:
2155 case ISD::FTRUNC:
2156 Res = SplitVecOp_UnaryOp(N);
2157 break;
2158
2159 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
2160 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
2161 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
2162 Res = SplitVecOp_ExtVecInRegOp(N);
2163 break;
2164
2165 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FADD:
2166 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMUL:
2167 case ISD::VECREDUCE_ADD:
2168 case ISD::VECREDUCE_MUL:
2169 case ISD::VECREDUCE_AND:
2170 case ISD::VECREDUCE_OR:
2171 case ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR:
2172 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX:
2173 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN:
2174 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX:
2175 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN:
2176 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMAX:
2177 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMIN:
2178 Res = SplitVecOp_VECREDUCE(N, OpNo);
2179 break;
2180 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SEQ_FADD:
2181 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SEQ_FMUL:
2182 Res = SplitVecOp_VECREDUCE_SEQ(N);
2183 break;
2184 }
2185
2186 // If the result is null, the sub-method took care of registering results etc.
2187 if (!Res.getNode()) return false;
2188
2189 // If the result is N, the sub-method updated N in place. Tell the legalizer
2190 // core about this.
2191 if (Res.getNode() == N)
2192 return true;
2193
2194 if (N->isStrictFPOpcode())
2195 assert(Res.getValueType() == N->getValueType(0) && N->getNumValues() == 2 &&
2196 "Invalid operand expansion");
2197 else
2198 assert(Res.getValueType() == N->getValueType(0) && N->getNumValues() == 1 &&
2199 "Invalid operand expansion");
2200
2201 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 0), Res);
2202 return false;
2203}

2205SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecOp_VSELECT(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
2206 // The only possibility for an illegal operand is the mask, since result type
2207 // legalization would have handled this node already otherwise.
2208 assert(OpNo == 0 && "Illegal operand must be mask");
2209
2210 SDValue Mask = N->getOperand(0);
2211 SDValue Src0 = N->getOperand(1);
2212 SDValue Src1 = N->getOperand(2);
2213 EVT Src0VT = Src0.getValueType();
2214 SDLoc DL(N);
2215 assert(Mask.getValueType().isVector() && "VSELECT without a vector mask?");
2216
2217 SDValue Lo, Hi;
2218 GetSplitVector(N->getOperand(0), Lo, Hi);
2219 assert(Lo.getValueType() == Hi.getValueType() &&
2220 "Lo and Hi have differing types");
2221
2222 EVT LoOpVT, HiOpVT;
2223 std::tie(LoOpVT, HiOpVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(Src0VT);
2224 assert(LoOpVT == HiOpVT && "Asymmetric vector split?");
2225
2226 SDValue LoOp0, HiOp0, LoOp1, HiOp1, LoMask, HiMask;
2227 std::tie(LoOp0, HiOp0) = DAG.SplitVector(Src0, DL);
2228 std::tie(LoOp1, HiOp1) = DAG.SplitVector(Src1, DL);
2229 std::tie(LoMask, HiMask) = DAG.SplitVector(Mask, DL);
2230
2231 SDValue LoSelect =
2232 DAG.getNode(ISD::VSELECT, DL, LoOpVT, LoMask, LoOp0, LoOp1);
2233 SDValue HiSelect =
2234 DAG.getNode(ISD::VSELECT, DL, HiOpVT, HiMask, HiOp0, HiOp1);
2235
2236 return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, DL, Src0VT, LoSelect, HiSelect);
2237}

2239SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecOp_VECREDUCE(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
2240 EVT ResVT = N->getValueType(0);
2241 SDValue Lo, Hi;

2243
2244 SDValue VecOp = N->getOperand(OpNo);

2280SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecOp_UnaryOp(SDNode *N) {
2281 // The result has a legal vector type, but the input needs splitting.
2282 EVT ResVT = N->getValueType(0);
2283 SDValue Lo, Hi;
2284 SDLoc dl(N);
2285 GetSplitVector(N->getOperand(N->isStrictFPOpcode() ? 1 : 0), Lo, Hi);
2286 EVT InVT = Lo.getValueType();
2287
2288 EVT OutVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), ResVT.getVectorElementType(),
2289 InVT.getVectorElementCount());
2290
2291 if (N->isStrictFPOpcode()) {
2292 Lo = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, { OutVT, MVT::Other },
2293 { N->getOperand(0), Lo });
2294 Hi = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, { OutVT, MVT::Other },
2295 { N->getOperand(0), Hi });
2296
2297 // Build a factor node to remember that this operation is independent
2298 // of the other one.
2299 SDValue Ch = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Lo.getValue(1),
2300 Hi.getValue(1));
2301
2302 // Legalize the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to
2303 // use the new one.
2304 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Ch);
2305 } else {
2306 Lo = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, OutVT, Lo);
2307 Hi = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, OutVT, Hi);
2308 }
2309
2310 return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, ResVT, Lo, Hi);
