2313SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecOp_BITCAST(SDNode *N) {
2314 // For example, i64 = BITCAST v4i16 on alpha. Typically the vector will
2315 // end up being split all the way down to individual components. Convert the
2316 // split pieces into integers and reassemble.
2317 SDValue Lo, Hi;
2318 GetSplitVector(N->getOperand(0), Lo, Hi);
2319 Lo = BitConvertToInteger(Lo);
2320 Hi = BitConvertToInteger(Hi);
2321
2322 if (DAG.getDataLayout().isBigEndian())
2323 std::swap(Lo, Hi);
2324
2325 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0),
2326 JoinIntegers(Lo, Hi));

2355SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecOp_EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR(SDNode *N) {
2356 // We know that the extracted result type is legal.
2357 EVT SubVT = N->getValueType(0);
2358
2359 SDValue Idx = N->getOperand(1);
2360 SDLoc dl(N);
2361 SDValue Lo, Hi;
2362
2363 if (SubVT.isScalableVector() !=
2364 N->getOperand(0).getValueType().isScalableVector())
2365 report_fatal_error("Extracting a fixed-length vector from an illegal "

2367

2383SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecOp_EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(SDNode *N) {
2384 SDValue Vec = N->getOperand(0);
2385 SDValue Idx = N->getOperand(1);
2386 EVT VecVT = Vec.getValueType();
2387
2388 if (isa<ConstantSDNode>(Idx)) {
2389 uint64_t IdxVal = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Idx)->getZExtValue();
2390
2391 SDValue Lo, Hi;
2392 GetSplitVector(Vec, Lo, Hi);
2393
2394 uint64_t LoElts = Lo.getValueType().getVectorMinNumElements();
2395
2396 if (IdxVal < LoElts)
2397 return SDValue(DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(N, Lo, Idx), 0);
2398 else if (!Vec.getValueType().isScalableVector())
2399 return SDValue(DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(N, Hi,
2400 DAG.getConstant(IdxVal - LoElts, SDLoc(N),
2401 Idx.getValueType())), 0);
2402 }
2403
2404 // See if the target wants to custom expand this node.
2405 if (CustomLowerNode(N, N->getValueType(0), true))
2406 return SDValue();
2407
2408 // Make the vector elements byte-addressable if they aren't already.
2409 SDLoc dl(N);
2410 EVT EltVT = VecVT.getVectorElementType();
2411 if (VecVT.getScalarSizeInBits() < 8) {
2412 EltVT = MVT::i8;
2413 VecVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), EltVT,
2414 VecVT.getVectorElementCount());
2415 Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, VecVT, Vec);
2416 }
2417
2418 // Store the vector to the stack.
2419 // In cases where the vector is illegal it will be broken down into parts
2420 // and stored in parts - we should use the alignment for the smallest part.
2421 Align SmallestAlign = DAG.getReducedAlign(VecVT, /*UseABI=*/false);
2422 SDValue StackPtr =
2423 DAG.CreateStackTemporary(VecVT.getStoreSize(), SmallestAlign);
2424 auto &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
2425 auto FrameIndex = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(StackPtr.getNode())->getIndex();
2426 auto PtrInfo = MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FrameIndex);
2427 SDValue Store = DAG.getStore(DAG.getEntryNode(), dl, Vec, StackPtr, PtrInfo,
2428 SmallestAlign);
2429
2430 // Load back the required element.
2431 StackPtr = TLI.getVectorElementPointer(DAG, StackPtr, VecVT, Idx);
2432
2433 // FIXME: This is to handle i1 vectors with elements promoted to i8.
2434 // i1 vector handling needs general improvement.
2435 if (N->getValueType(0).bitsLT(EltVT)) {
2436 SDValue Load = DAG.getLoad(EltVT, dl, Store, StackPtr,
2437 MachinePointerInfo::getUnknownStack(DAG.getMachineFunction()));
2438 return DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(Load, dl, N->getValueType(0));
2439 }
2440
2441 return DAG.getExtLoad(
2442 ISD::EXTLOAD, dl, N->getValueType(0), Store, StackPtr,
2443 MachinePointerInfo::getUnknownStack(DAG.getMachineFunction()), EltVT,
2444 commonAlignment(SmallestAlign, EltVT.getFixedSizeInBits() / 8));
2445}

2447SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecOp_ExtVecInRegOp(SDNode *N) {
2448 SDValue Lo, Hi;
2449
2450 // *_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG only reference the lower half of the input, so
2451 // splitting the result has the same effect as splitting the input operand.
2452 SplitVecRes_ExtVecInRegOp(N, Lo, Hi);
2453
2454 return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0), Lo, Hi);

2457SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecOp_MGATHER(MaskedGatherSDNode *MGT,
2458 unsigned OpNo) {
2459 EVT LoVT, HiVT;
2460 SDLoc dl(MGT);
2461 std::tie(LoVT, HiVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(MGT->getValueType(0));
2462
2463 SDValue Ch = MGT->getChain();
2464 SDValue Ptr = MGT->getBasePtr();
2465 SDValue Index = MGT->getIndex();
2466 SDValue Scale = MGT->getScale();
2467 SDValue Mask = MGT->getMask();
2468 SDValue PassThru = MGT->getPassThru();
2469 Align Alignment = MGT->getOriginalAlign();
2470 ISD::LoadExtType ExtType = MGT->getExtensionType();
2471
2472 SDValue MaskLo, MaskHi;
2473 if (getTypeAction(Mask.getValueType()) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector)
2474 // Split Mask operand
2475 GetSplitVector(Mask, MaskLo, MaskHi);
2476 else
2477 std::tie(MaskLo, MaskHi) = DAG.SplitVector(Mask, dl);
2478
2479 EVT MemoryVT = MGT->getMemoryVT();
2480 EVT LoMemVT, HiMemVT;
2481 std::tie(LoMemVT, HiMemVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(MemoryVT);
2482
2483 SDValue PassThruLo, PassThruHi;
2484 if (getTypeAction(PassThru.getValueType()) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector)
2485 GetSplitVector(PassThru, PassThruLo, PassThruHi);
2486 else
2487 std::tie(PassThruLo, PassThruHi) = DAG.SplitVector(PassThru, dl);
2488
2489 SDValue IndexHi, IndexLo;
2490 if (getTypeAction(Index.getValueType()) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector)
2491 GetSplitVector(Index, IndexLo, IndexHi);
2492 else
2493 std::tie(IndexLo, IndexHi) = DAG.SplitVector(Index, dl);
2494
2495 MachineMemOperand *MMO = DAG.getMachineFunction().getMachineMemOperand(
2496 MGT->getPointerInfo(), MachineMemOperand::MOLoad,
2497 MemoryLocation::UnknownSize, Alignment, MGT->getAAInfo(),
2498 MGT->getRanges());
2499
2500 SDValue OpsLo[] = {Ch, PassThruLo, MaskLo, Ptr, IndexLo, Scale};
2501 SDValue Lo = DAG.getMaskedGather(DAG.getVTList(LoVT, MVT::Other), LoMemVT, dl,
2502 OpsLo, MMO, MGT->getIndexType(), ExtType);
2503
2504 SDValue OpsHi[] = {Ch, PassThruHi, MaskHi, Ptr, IndexHi, Scale};
2505 SDValue Hi = DAG.getMaskedGather(DAG.getVTList(HiVT, MVT::Other), HiMemVT, dl,
2506 OpsHi, MMO, MGT->getIndexType(), ExtType);
2507
2508 // Build a factor node to remember that this load is independent of the
2509 // other one.
2510 Ch = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Lo.getValue(1),
2511 Hi.getValue(1));
2512
2513 // Legalize the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to
2514 // use the new one.
2515 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(MGT, 1), Ch);
2516
2517 SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, MGT->getValueType(0), Lo,
2518 Hi);
2519 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(MGT, 0), Res);
2520 return SDValue();
2521}

2523SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecOp_MSTORE(MaskedStoreSDNode *N,
2524 unsigned OpNo) {
2525 assert(N->isUnindexed() && "Indexed masked store of vector?");
2526 SDValue Ch = N->getChain();
2527 SDValue Ptr = N->getBasePtr();
2528 SDValue Offset = N->getOffset();
2529 assert(Offset.isUndef() && "Unexpected indexed masked store offset");
2530 SDValue Mask = N->getMask();
2531 SDValue Data = N->getValue();
2532 Align Alignment = N->getOriginalAlign();
2533 SDLoc DL(N);
2534
2535 SDValue DataLo, DataHi;
2536 if (getTypeAction(Data.getValueType()) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector)
2537 // Split Data operand
2538 GetSplitVector(Data, DataLo, DataHi);
2539 else
2540 std::tie(DataLo, DataHi) = DAG.SplitVector(Data, DL);
2541
2542 // Split Mask operand
2543 SDValue MaskLo, MaskHi;
2544 if (OpNo == 1 && Mask.getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC) {
2545 SplitVecRes_SETCC(Mask.getNode(), MaskLo, MaskHi);
2546 } else {
2547 if (getTypeAction(Mask.getValueType()) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector)
2548 GetSplitVector(Mask, MaskLo, MaskHi);
2549 else
2550 std::tie(MaskLo, MaskHi) = DAG.SplitVector(Mask, DL);
2551 }
2552
2553 EVT MemoryVT = N->getMemoryVT();
2554 EVT LoMemVT, HiMemVT;
2555 bool HiIsEmpty = false;
2556 std::tie(LoMemVT, HiMemVT) =
2557 DAG.GetDependentSplitDestVTs(MemoryVT, DataLo.getValueType(), &HiIsEmpty);
2558
2559 SDValue Lo, Hi, Res;
2560 unsigned LoSize = MemoryLocation::getSizeOrUnknown(LoMemVT.getStoreSize());
2561 MachineMemOperand *MMO = DAG.getMachineFunction().getMachineMemOperand(
2562 N->getPointerInfo(), MachineMemOperand::MOStore, LoSize, Alignment,
2563 N->getAAInfo(), N->getRanges());
2564
2565 Lo = DAG.getMaskedStore(Ch, DL, DataLo, Ptr, Offset, MaskLo, LoMemVT, MMO,
2566 N->getAddressingMode(), N->isTruncatingStore(),
2567 N->isCompressingStore());
2568
2569 if (HiIsEmpty) {
2570 // The hi masked store has zero storage size.
2571 // Only the lo masked store is needed.
2572 Res = Lo;
2573 } else {
2574
2575 Ptr = TLI.IncrementMemoryAddress(Ptr, MaskLo, DL, LoMemVT, DAG,
2576 N->isCompressingStore());
2577
2578 MachinePointerInfo MPI;
2579 if (LoMemVT.isScalableVector()) {
2580 Alignment = commonAlignment(
2581 Alignment, LoMemVT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinSize() / 8);
2582 MPI = MachinePointerInfo(N->getPointerInfo().getAddrSpace());
2583 } else
2584 MPI = N->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(
2585 LoMemVT.getStoreSize().getFixedSize());
2586
2587 unsigned HiSize = MemoryLocation::getSizeOrUnknown(HiMemVT.getStoreSize());
2588 MMO = DAG.getMachineFunction().getMachineMemOperand(
2589 MPI, MachineMemOperand::MOStore, HiSize, Alignment, N->getAAInfo(),
2590 N->getRanges());
2591
2592 Hi = DAG.getMaskedStore(Ch, DL, DataHi, Ptr, Offset, MaskHi, HiMemVT, MMO,
2593 N->getAddressingMode(), N->isTruncatingStore(),
2594 N->isCompressingStore());
2595
2596 // Build a factor node to remember that this store is independent of the
2597 // other one.
2598 Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, DL, MVT::Other, Lo, Hi);
2599 }
2600
2601 return Res;
2602}

2604SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecOp_MSCATTER(MaskedScatterSDNode *N,
2605 unsigned OpNo) {
2606 SDValue Ch = N->getChain();
2607 SDValue Ptr = N->getBasePtr();
2608 SDValue Mask = N->getMask();
2609 SDValue Index = N->getIndex();
2610 SDValue Scale = N->getScale();
2611 SDValue Data = N->getValue();
2612 EVT MemoryVT = N->getMemoryVT();
2613 Align Alignment = N->getOriginalAlign();
2614 SDLoc DL(N);
2615
2616 // Split all operands
2617
2618 EVT LoMemVT, HiMemVT;
2619 std::tie(LoMemVT, HiMemVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(MemoryVT);
2620
2621 SDValue DataLo, DataHi;
2622 if (getTypeAction(Data.getValueType()) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector)
2623 // Split Data operand
2624 GetSplitVector(Data, DataLo, DataHi);
2625 else
2626 std::tie(DataLo, DataHi) = DAG.SplitVector(Data, DL);
2627
2628 // Split Mask operand
2629 SDValue MaskLo, MaskHi;
2630 if (OpNo == 1 && Mask.getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC) {
2631 SplitVecRes_SETCC(Mask.getNode(), MaskLo, MaskHi);
2632 } else {
2633 if (getTypeAction(Mask.getValueType()) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector)
2634 GetSplitVector(Mask, MaskLo, MaskHi);
2635 else
2636 std::tie(MaskLo, MaskHi) = DAG.SplitVector(Mask, DL);
2637 }
2638
2639 SDValue IndexHi, IndexLo;
2640 if (getTypeAction(Index.getValueType()) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector)
2641 GetSplitVector(Index, IndexLo, IndexHi);
2642 else
2643 std::tie(IndexLo, IndexHi) = DAG.SplitVector(Index, DL);
2644
2645 SDValue Lo;
2646 MachineMemOperand *MMO = DAG.getMachineFunction().getMachineMemOperand(
2647 N->getPointerInfo(), MachineMemOperand::MOStore,
2648 MemoryLocation::UnknownSize, Alignment, N->getAAInfo(), N->getRanges());
2649
2650 SDValue OpsLo[] = {Ch, DataLo, MaskLo, Ptr, IndexLo, Scale};
2651 Lo = DAG.getMaskedScatter(DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other), LoMemVT,
2652 DL, OpsLo, MMO, N->getIndexType(),
2653 N->isTruncatingStore());
2654
2655 // The order of the Scatter operation after split is well defined. The "Hi"
2656 // part comes after the "Lo". So these two operations should be chained one
2657 // after another.
2658 SDValue OpsHi[] = {Lo, DataHi, MaskHi, Ptr, IndexHi, Scale};

2664SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecOp_STORE(StoreSDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
2665 assert(N->isUnindexed() && "Indexed store of vector?");
2666 assert(OpNo == 1 && "Can only split the stored value");
2667 SDLoc DL(N);
2668
2669 bool isTruncating = N->isTruncatingStore();
2670 SDValue Ch = N->getChain();
2671 SDValue Ptr = N->getBasePtr();
2672 EVT MemoryVT = N->getMemoryVT();
2673 Align Alignment = N->getOriginalAlign();
2674 MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags = N->getMemOperand()->getFlags();
2675 AAMDNodes AAInfo = N->getAAInfo();
2676 SDValue Lo, Hi;
2677 GetSplitVector(N->getOperand(1), Lo, Hi);
2678
2679 EVT LoMemVT, HiMemVT;
2680 std::tie(LoMemVT, HiMemVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(MemoryVT);
2681
2682 // Scalarize if the split halves are not byte-sized.
2683 if (!LoMemVT.isByteSized() || !HiMemVT.isByteSized())
2684 return TLI.scalarizeVectorStore(N, DAG);
2685
2686 if (isTruncating)
2687 Lo = DAG.getTruncStore(Ch, DL, Lo, Ptr, N->getPointerInfo(), LoMemVT,
2688 Alignment, MMOFlags, AAInfo);
2689 else
2690 Lo = DAG.getStore(Ch, DL, Lo, Ptr, N->getPointerInfo(), Alignment, MMOFlags,
2691 AAInfo);
2692
2693 MachinePointerInfo MPI;
2694 IncrementPointer(N, LoMemVT, MPI, Ptr);
2695
2696 if (isTruncating)
2697 Hi = DAG.getTruncStore(Ch, DL, Hi, Ptr, MPI,
2698 HiMemVT, Alignment, MMOFlags, AAInfo);
2699 else
2700 Hi = DAG.getStore(Ch, DL, Hi, Ptr, MPI, Alignment, MMOFlags, AAInfo);
2701
2702 return DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, DL, MVT::Other, Lo, Hi);
2703}
2704
2705SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecOp_CONCAT_VECTORS(SDNode *N) {
2706 SDLoc DL(N);
2707
2708 // The input operands all must have the same type, and we know the result
2709 // type is valid. Convert this to a buildvector which extracts all the
2710 // input elements.
2711 // TODO: If the input elements are power-two vectors, we could convert this to
2712 // a new CONCAT_VECTORS node with elements that are half-wide.
2713 SmallVector<SDValue, 32> Elts;
2714 EVT EltVT = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType();
2715 for (const SDValue &Op : N->op_values()) {
2716 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Op.getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
2717 i != e; ++i) {
2718 Elts.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, EltVT, Op,
2719 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, DL)));
2720 }
2721 }
2722
2723 return DAG.getBuildVector(N->getValueType(0), DL, Elts);
2724}
2725
2726SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecOp_TruncateHelper(SDNode *N) {
2727 // The result type is legal, but the input type is illegal. If splitting
2728 // ends up with the result type of each half still being legal, just
2729 // do that. If, however, that would result in an illegal result type,
2730 // we can try to get more clever with power-two vectors. Specifically,
2731 // split the input type, but also widen the result element size, then
2732 // concatenate the halves and truncate again. For example, consider a target
2733 // where v8i8 is legal and v8i32 is not (ARM, which doesn't have 256-bit
2734 // vectors). To perform a "%res = v8i8 trunc v8i32 %in" we do:
2735 // %inlo = v4i32 extract_subvector %in, 0
2736 // %inhi = v4i32 extract_subvector %in, 4
2737 // %lo16 = v4i16 trunc v4i32 %inlo
2738 // %hi16 = v4i16 trunc v4i32 %inhi
2739 // %in16 = v8i16 concat_vectors v4i16 %lo16, v4i16 %hi16
2740 // %res = v8i8 trunc v8i16 %in16
2741 //
2742 // Without this transform, the original truncate would end up being
2743 // scalarized, which is pretty much always a last resort.
2744 unsigned OpNo = N->isStrictFPOpcode() ? 1 : 0;
2745 SDValue InVec = N->getOperand(OpNo);
2746 EVT InVT = InVec->getValueType(0);
2747 EVT OutVT = N->getValueType(0);
2748 ElementCount NumElements = OutVT.getVectorElementCount();
2749 bool IsFloat = OutVT.isFloatingPoint();
2750
2751 unsigned InElementSize = InVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
2752 unsigned OutElementSize = OutVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
2753
2754 // Determine the split output VT. If its legal we can just split dirctly.
2755 EVT LoOutVT, HiOutVT;
2756 std::tie(LoOutVT, HiOutVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(OutVT);
2757 assert(LoOutVT == HiOutVT && "Unequal split?");
2758
2759 // If the input elements are only 1/2 the width of the result elements,
2760 // just use the normal splitting. Our trick only work if there's room
2761 // to split more than once.
2762 if (isTypeLegal(LoOutVT) ||
2763 InElementSize <= OutElementSize * 2)
2764 return SplitVecOp_UnaryOp(N);
2765 SDLoc DL(N);
2766
2767 // Don't touch if this will be scalarized.
2768 EVT FinalVT = InVT;
2769 while (getTypeAction(FinalVT) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector)
2770 FinalVT = FinalVT.getHalfNumVectorElementsVT(*DAG.getContext());
2771
2772 if (getTypeAction(FinalVT) == TargetLowering::TypeScalarizeVector)
2773 return SplitVecOp_UnaryOp(N);
2774
2775 // Get the split input vector.
2776 SDValue InLoVec, InHiVec;
2777 GetSplitVector(InVec, InLoVec, InHiVec);
2778
2779 // Truncate them to 1/2 the element size.
2780 //
2781 // This assumes the number of elements is a power of two; any vector that
2782 // isn't should be widened, not split.
2783 EVT HalfElementVT = IsFloat ?
2784 EVT::getFloatingPointVT(InElementSize/2) :
2785 EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), InElementSize/2);
2786 EVT HalfVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), HalfElementVT,
2787 NumElements.divideCoefficientBy(2));
2788
2789 SDValue HalfLo;
2790 SDValue HalfHi;
2791 SDValue Chain;
2792 if (N->isStrictFPOpcode()) {
2793 HalfLo = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), DL, {HalfVT, MVT::Other},
2794 {N->getOperand(0), InLoVec});
2795 HalfHi = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), DL, {HalfVT, MVT::Other},
2796 {N->getOperand(0), InHiVec});
2797 // Legalize the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to
2798 // use the new one.
2799 Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, DL, MVT::Other, HalfLo.getValue(1),
2800 HalfHi.getValue(1));
2801 } else {
2802 HalfLo = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), DL, HalfVT, InLoVec);
2803 HalfHi = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), DL, HalfVT, InHiVec);
2804 }
2805 // Concatenate them to get the full intermediate truncation result.
2806 EVT InterVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), HalfElementVT, NumElements);
2807 SDValue InterVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, DL, InterVT, HalfLo,
2808 HalfHi);
2809 // Now finish up by truncating all the way down to the original result
2810 // type. This should normally be something that ends up being legal directly,
2811 // but in theory if a target has very wide vectors and an annoyingly
2812 // restricted set of legal types, this split can chain to build things up.
2813
2814 if (N->isStrictFPOpcode()) {
2815 SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(
2816 ISD::STRICT_FP_ROUND, DL, {OutVT, MVT::Other},
2817 {Chain, InterVec,
2818 DAG.getTargetConstant(0, DL, TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()))});
2819 // Relink the chain
2820 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), SDValue(Res.getNode(), 1));
2821 return Res;
2822 }
2823
2824 return IsFloat
2825 ? DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_ROUND, DL, OutVT, InterVec,
2826 DAG.getTargetConstant(
2827 0, DL, TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout())))
2828 : DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, OutVT, InterVec);
2829}

2831SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::SplitVecOp_VSETCC(SDNode *N) {
2832 assert(N->getValueType(0).isVector() &&
2833 N->getOperand(0).getValueType().isVector() &&
2834 "Operand types must be vectors");
2835 // The result has a legal vector type, but the input needs splitting.
2836 SDValue Lo0, Hi0, Lo1, Hi1, LoRes, HiRes;
2837 SDLoc DL(N);
2838 GetSplitVector(N->getOperand(0), Lo0, Hi0);
2839 GetSplitVector(N->getOperand(1), Lo1, Hi1);
2840 auto PartEltCnt = Lo0.getValueType().getVectorElementCount();
2841
2842 LLVMContext &Context = *DAG.getContext();
2843 EVT PartResVT = EVT::getVectorVT(Context, MVT::i1, PartEltCnt);
2844 EVT WideResVT = EVT::getVectorVT(Context, MVT::i1, PartEltCnt*2);
2845
2846 LoRes = DAG.getNode(ISD::SETCC, DL, PartResVT, Lo0, Lo1, N->getOperand(2));
2847 HiRes = DAG.getNode(ISD::SETCC, DL, PartResVT, Hi0, Hi1, N->getOperand(2));
2848 SDValue Con = DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, DL, WideResVT, LoRes, HiRes);
2849
2850 EVT OpVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
2851 ISD::NodeType ExtendCode =
2852 TargetLowering::getExtendForContent(TLI.getBooleanContents(OpVT));
2853 return DAG.getNode(ExtendCode, DL, N->getValueType(0), Con);
2854}

2880 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_ROUND, DL, OutVT, Hi, N->getOperand(1));

2884}

2913void DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVectorResult(SDNode *N, unsigned ResNo) {
2914 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Widen node result " << ResNo << ": "; N->dump(&DAG);
2915 dbgs() << "\n");
2916
2917 // See if the target wants to custom widen this node.
2918 if (CustomWidenLowerNode(N, N->getValueType(ResNo)))

2923 default:

2928#endif
2929 llvm_unreachable("Do not know how to widen the result of this operator!");

2931 case ISD::MERGE_VALUES: Res = WidenVecRes_MERGE_VALUES(N, ResNo); break;
2932 case ISD::BITCAST: Res = WidenVecRes_BITCAST(N); break;

3145// Given a vector of operations that have been broken up to widen, see
3146// if we can collect them together into the next widest legal VT. This
3147// implementation is trap-safe.
3148static SDValue CollectOpsToWiden(SelectionDAG &DAG, const TargetLowering &TLI,
3149 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &ConcatOps,
3150 unsigned ConcatEnd, EVT VT, EVT MaxVT,
3151 EVT WidenVT) {
3152 // Check to see if we have a single operation with the widen type.
3153 if (ConcatEnd == 1) {
3154 VT = ConcatOps[0].getValueType();
3155 if (VT == WidenVT)
3156 return ConcatOps[0];
3157 }
3158
3159 SDLoc dl(ConcatOps[0]);
3160 EVT WidenEltVT = WidenVT.getVectorElementType();
3161
3162 // while (Some element of ConcatOps is not of type MaxVT) {
3163 // From the end of ConcatOps, collect elements of the same type and put
3164 // them into an op of the next larger supported type
3165 // }
3166 while (ConcatOps[ConcatEnd-1].getValueType() != MaxVT) {
3167 int Idx = ConcatEnd - 1;
3168 VT = ConcatOps[Idx--].getValueType();
3169 while (Idx >= 0 && ConcatOps[Idx].getValueType() == VT)
3170 Idx--;
3171
3172 int NextSize = VT.isVector() ? VT.getVectorNumElements() : 1;
3173 EVT NextVT;
3174 do {
3175 NextSize *= 2;
3176 NextVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), WidenEltVT, NextSize);
3177 } while (!TLI.isTypeLegal(NextVT));
3178
3179 if (!VT.isVector()) {
3180 // Scalar type, create an INSERT_VECTOR_ELEMENT of type NextVT
3181 SDValue VecOp = DAG.getUNDEF(NextVT);
3182 unsigned NumToInsert = ConcatEnd - Idx - 1;
3183 for (unsigned i = 0, OpIdx = Idx+1; i < NumToInsert; i++, OpIdx++) {
3184 VecOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, NextVT, VecOp,
3185 ConcatOps[OpIdx], DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, dl));
3186 }
3187 ConcatOps[Idx+1] = VecOp;
3188 ConcatEnd = Idx + 2;
3189 } else {
3190 // Vector type, create a CONCAT_VECTORS of type NextVT
3191 SDValue undefVec = DAG.getUNDEF(VT);
3192 unsigned OpsToConcat = NextSize/VT.getVectorNumElements();
3193 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> SubConcatOps(OpsToConcat);
3194 unsigned RealVals = ConcatEnd - Idx - 1;
3195 unsigned SubConcatEnd = 0;
3196 unsigned SubConcatIdx = Idx + 1;
3197 while (SubConcatEnd < RealVals)
3198 SubConcatOps[SubConcatEnd++] = ConcatOps[++Idx];
3199 while (SubConcatEnd < OpsToConcat)
3200 SubConcatOps[SubConcatEnd++] = undefVec;
3201 ConcatOps[SubConcatIdx] = DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl,
3202 NextVT, SubConcatOps);
3203 ConcatEnd = SubConcatIdx + 1;
3204 }
3205 }
3206
3207 // Check to see if we have a single operation with the widen type.
3208 if (ConcatEnd == 1) {
3209 VT = ConcatOps[0].getValueType();
3210 if (VT == WidenVT)
3211 return ConcatOps[0];
3212 }
3213
3214 // add undefs of size MaxVT until ConcatOps grows to length of WidenVT
3215 unsigned NumOps = WidenVT.getVectorNumElements()/MaxVT.getVectorNumElements();
3216 if (NumOps != ConcatEnd ) {
3217 SDValue UndefVal = DAG.getUNDEF(MaxVT);
3218 for (unsigned j = ConcatEnd; j < NumOps; ++j)
3219 ConcatOps[j] = UndefVal;
3220 }
3221 return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, WidenVT,
3222 makeArrayRef(ConcatOps.data(), NumOps));
3223}
3224
3225SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_BinaryCanTrap(SDNode *N) {
3226 // Binary op widening for operations that can trap.
3227 unsigned Opcode = N->getOpcode();
3228 SDLoc dl(N);
3229 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
3230 EVT WidenEltVT = WidenVT.getVectorElementType();
3231 EVT VT = WidenVT;
3232 unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
3233 const SDNodeFlags Flags = N->getFlags();
3234 while (!TLI.isTypeLegal(VT) && NumElts != 1) {
3235 NumElts = NumElts / 2;
3236 VT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), WidenEltVT, NumElts);
3237 }
3238
3239 if (NumElts != 1 && !TLI.canOpTrap(N->getOpcode(), VT)) {
3240 // Operation doesn't trap so just widen as normal.
3241 SDValue InOp1 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
3242 SDValue InOp2 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(1));
3243 return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, WidenVT, InOp1, InOp2, Flags);
3244 }
3245
3246 // No legal vector version so unroll the vector operation and then widen.
3247 if (NumElts == 1)
3248 return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(N, WidenVT.getVectorNumElements());
3249
3250 // Since the operation can trap, apply operation on the original vector.
3251 EVT MaxVT = VT;
3252 SDValue InOp1 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
3253 SDValue InOp2 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(1));
3254 unsigned CurNumElts = N->getValueType(0).getVectorNumElements();
3255
3256 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> ConcatOps(CurNumElts);
3257 unsigned ConcatEnd = 0; // Current ConcatOps index.
3258 int Idx = 0; // Current Idx into input vectors.
3259
3260 // NumElts := greatest legal vector size (at most WidenVT)
3261 // while (orig. vector has unhandled elements) {
3262 // take munches of size NumElts from the beginning and add to ConcatOps
3263 // NumElts := next smaller supported vector size or 1
3264 // }
3265 while (CurNumElts != 0) {
3266 while (CurNumElts >= NumElts) {
3267 SDValue EOp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, VT, InOp1,
3268 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl));
3269 SDValue EOp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, VT, InOp2,
3270 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl));
3271 ConcatOps[ConcatEnd++] = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, VT, EOp1, EOp2, Flags);
3272 Idx += NumElts;
3273 CurNumElts -= NumElts;
3274 }
3275 do {
3276 NumElts = NumElts / 2;
3277 VT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), WidenEltVT, NumElts);
3278 } while (!TLI.isTypeLegal(VT) && NumElts != 1);
3279
3280 if (NumElts == 1) {
3281 for (unsigned i = 0; i != CurNumElts; ++i, ++Idx) {
3282 SDValue EOp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, WidenEltVT,
3283 InOp1, DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl));
3284 SDValue EOp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, WidenEltVT,
3285 InOp2, DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl));
3286 ConcatOps[ConcatEnd++] = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, WidenEltVT,
3287 EOp1, EOp2, Flags);
3288 }
3289 CurNumElts = 0;
3290 }
3291 }
3292
3293 return CollectOpsToWiden(DAG, TLI, ConcatOps, ConcatEnd, VT, MaxVT, WidenVT);
3294}
3295
3296SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_StrictFP(SDNode *N) {
3297 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
3298 case ISD::STRICT_FSETCC:
3299 case ISD::STRICT_FSETCCS:
3300 return WidenVecRes_STRICT_FSETCC(N);
3301 case ISD::STRICT_FP_EXTEND:
3302 case ISD::STRICT_FP_ROUND:
3303 case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT:
3304 case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_UINT:
3305 case ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP:
3306 case ISD::STRICT_UINT_TO_FP:
3307 return WidenVecRes_Convert_StrictFP(N);
3308 default:
3309 break;
3310 }
3311
3312 // StrictFP op widening for operations that can trap.
3313 unsigned NumOpers = N->getNumOperands();
3314 unsigned Opcode = N->getOpcode();
3315 SDLoc dl(N);
3316 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
3317 EVT WidenEltVT = WidenVT.getVectorElementType();
3318 EVT VT = WidenVT;
3319 unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
3320 while (!TLI.isTypeLegal(VT) && NumElts != 1) {
3321 NumElts = NumElts / 2;
3322 VT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), WidenEltVT, NumElts);
3323 }
3324
3325 // No legal vector version so unroll the vector operation and then widen.
3326 if (NumElts == 1)
3327 return UnrollVectorOp_StrictFP(N, WidenVT.getVectorNumElements());
3328
3329 // Since the operation can trap, apply operation on the original vector.
3330 EVT MaxVT = VT;
3331 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> InOps;
3332 unsigned CurNumElts = N->getValueType(0).getVectorNumElements();
3333
3334 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> ConcatOps(CurNumElts);
3335 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Chains;
3336 unsigned ConcatEnd = 0; // Current ConcatOps index.
3337 int Idx = 0; // Current Idx into input vectors.
3338
3339 // The Chain is the first operand.
3340 InOps.push_back(N->getOperand(0));
3341
3342 // Now process the remaining operands.
3343 for (unsigned i = 1; i < NumOpers; ++i) {
3344 SDValue Oper = N->getOperand(i);
3345
3346 if (Oper.getValueType().isVector()) {
3347 assert(Oper.getValueType() == N->getValueType(0) &&
3348 "Invalid operand type to widen!");
3349 Oper = GetWidenedVector(Oper);
3350 }
3351
3352 InOps.push_back(Oper);
3353 }
3354
3355 // NumElts := greatest legal vector size (at most WidenVT)
3356 // while (orig. vector has unhandled elements) {
3357 // take munches of size NumElts from the beginning and add to ConcatOps
3358 // NumElts := next smaller supported vector size or 1
3359 // }
3360 while (CurNumElts != 0) {
3361 while (CurNumElts >= NumElts) {
3362 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> EOps;
3363
3364 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumOpers; ++i) {
3365 SDValue Op = InOps[i];
3366
3367 if (Op.getValueType().isVector())
3368 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, VT, Op,
3369 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl));
3370
3371 EOps.push_back(Op);
3372 }
3373
3374 EVT OperVT[] = {VT, MVT::Other};
3375 SDValue Oper = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, OperVT, EOps);
3376 ConcatOps[ConcatEnd++] = Oper;
3377 Chains.push_back(Oper.getValue(1));
3378 Idx += NumElts;
3379 CurNumElts -= NumElts;
3380 }
3381 do {
3382 NumElts = NumElts / 2;
3383 VT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), WidenEltVT, NumElts);
3384 } while (!TLI.isTypeLegal(VT) && NumElts != 1);
3385
3386 if (NumElts == 1) {
3387 for (unsigned i = 0; i != CurNumElts; ++i, ++Idx) {
3388 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> EOps;
3389
3390 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumOpers; ++i) {
3391 SDValue Op = InOps[i];
3392
3393 if (Op.getValueType().isVector())
3394 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, WidenEltVT, Op,
3395 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl));
3396
3397 EOps.push_back(Op);
3398 }
3399
3400 EVT WidenVT[] = {WidenEltVT, MVT::Other};
3401 SDValue Oper = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, WidenVT, EOps);
3402 ConcatOps[ConcatEnd++] = Oper;
3403 Chains.push_back(Oper.getValue(1));
3404 }
3405 CurNumElts = 0;
3406 }
3407 }
3408
3409 // Build a factor node to remember all the Ops that have been created.
3410 SDValue NewChain;
3411 if (Chains.size() == 1)
3412 NewChain = Chains[0];
3413 else
3414 NewChain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Chains);
3415 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), NewChain);
3416
3417 return CollectOpsToWiden(DAG, TLI, ConcatOps, ConcatEnd, VT, MaxVT, WidenVT);
3418}

3420SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_OverflowOp(SDNode *N, unsigned ResNo) {
3421 SDLoc DL(N);
3422 EVT ResVT = N->getValueType(0);
3423 EVT OvVT = N->getValueType(1);
3424 EVT WideResVT, WideOvVT;
3425 SDValue WideLHS, WideRHS;
3426
3427 // TODO: This might result in a widen/split loop.
3428 if (ResNo == 0) {
3429 WideResVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), ResVT);
3430 WideOvVT = EVT::getVectorVT(
3431 *DAG.getContext(), OvVT.getVectorElementType(),
3432 WideResVT.getVectorNumElements());
3433
3434 WideLHS = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
3435 WideRHS = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(1));
3436 } else {
3437 WideOvVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), OvVT);
3438 WideResVT = EVT::getVectorVT(
3439 *DAG.getContext(), ResVT.getVectorElementType(),
3440 WideOvVT.getVectorNumElements());
3441
3442 SDValue Zero = DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL);
3443 WideLHS = DAG.getNode(
3444 ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, WideResVT, DAG.getUNDEF(WideResVT),
3445 N->getOperand(0), Zero);
3446 WideRHS = DAG.getNode(
3447 ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, WideResVT, DAG.getUNDEF(WideResVT),
3448 N->getOperand(1), Zero);
3449 }
3450
3451 SDVTList WideVTs = DAG.getVTList(WideResVT, WideOvVT);
3452 SDNode *WideNode = DAG.getNode(
3453 N->getOpcode(), DL, WideVTs, WideLHS, WideRHS).getNode();
3454
3455 // Replace the other vector result not being explicitly widened here.
3456 unsigned OtherNo = 1 - ResNo;
3457 EVT OtherVT = N->getValueType(OtherNo);
3458 if (getTypeAction(OtherVT) == TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector) {
3459 SetWidenedVector(SDValue(N, OtherNo), SDValue(WideNode, OtherNo));
3460 } else {
3461 SDValue Zero = DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL);
3462 SDValue OtherVal = DAG.getNode(
3463 ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, OtherVT, SDValue(WideNode, OtherNo), Zero);
3464 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, OtherNo), OtherVal);
3465 }
3466
3467 return SDValue(WideNode, ResNo);
3468}
3469
3470SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_Convert(SDNode *N) {
3471 LLVMContext &Ctx = *DAG.getContext();
3472 SDValue InOp = N->getOperand(0);
3473 SDLoc DL(N);
3474
3475 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(Ctx, N->getValueType(0));
3476 unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorNumElements();
3477
3478 EVT InVT = InOp.getValueType();
3479
3480 unsigned Opcode = N->getOpcode();
3481 const SDNodeFlags Flags = N->getFlags();
3482
3483 // Handle the case of ZERO_EXTEND where the promoted InVT element size does
3484 // not equal that of WidenVT.
3485 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND &&
3486 getTypeAction(InVT) == TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger &&
3487 TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(Ctx, InVT).getScalarSizeInBits() !=
3488 WidenVT.getScalarSizeInBits()) {
3489 InOp = ZExtPromotedInteger(InOp);
3490 InVT = InOp.getValueType();
3491 if (WidenVT.getScalarSizeInBits() < InVT.getScalarSizeInBits())
3492 Opcode = ISD::TRUNCATE;
3493 }
3494
3495 EVT InEltVT = InVT.getVectorElementType();
3496 EVT InWidenVT = EVT::getVectorVT(Ctx, InEltVT, WidenNumElts);
3497 unsigned InVTNumElts = InVT.getVectorNumElements();
3498
3499 if (getTypeAction(InVT) == TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector) {
3500 InOp = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
3501 InVT = InOp.getValueType();
3502 InVTNumElts = InVT.getVectorNumElements();
3503 if (InVTNumElts == WidenNumElts) {
3504 if (N->getNumOperands() == 1)
3505 return DAG.getNode(Opcode, DL, WidenVT, InOp);
3506 return DAG.getNode(Opcode, DL, WidenVT, InOp, N->getOperand(1), Flags);
3507 }
3508 if (WidenVT.getSizeInBits() == InVT.getSizeInBits()) {
3509 // If both input and result vector types are of same width, extend
3510 // operations should be done with SIGN/ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG, which
3511 // accepts fewer elements in the result than in the input.
3512 if (Opcode == ISD::ANY_EXTEND)
3513 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG, DL, WidenVT, InOp);
3514 if (Opcode == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND)
3515 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG, DL, WidenVT, InOp);
3516 if (Opcode == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND)
3517 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG, DL, WidenVT, InOp);
3518 }
3519 }
3520
3521 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(InWidenVT)) {
3522 // Because the result and the input are different vector types, widening
3523 // the result could create a legal type but widening the input might make
3524 // it an illegal type that might lead to repeatedly splitting the input
3525 // and then widening it. To avoid this, we widen the input only if
3526 // it results in a legal type.
3527 if (WidenNumElts % InVTNumElts == 0) {
3528 // Widen the input and call convert on the widened input vector.
3529 unsigned NumConcat = WidenNumElts/InVTNumElts;
3530 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(NumConcat, DAG.getUNDEF(InVT));
3531 Ops[0] = InOp;
3532 SDValue InVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, DL, InWidenVT, Ops);
3533 if (N->getNumOperands() == 1)
3534 return DAG.getNode(Opcode, DL, WidenVT, InVec);
3535 return DAG.getNode(Opcode, DL, WidenVT, InVec, N->getOperand(1), Flags);
3536 }
3537
3538 if (InVTNumElts % WidenNumElts == 0) {
3539 SDValue InVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, InWidenVT, InOp,
3540 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
3541 // Extract the input and convert the shorten input vector.
3542 if (N->getNumOperands() == 1)
3543 return DAG.getNode(Opcode, DL, WidenVT, InVal);
3544 return DAG.getNode(Opcode, DL, WidenVT, InVal, N->getOperand(1), Flags);
3545 }
3546 }
3547
3548 // Otherwise unroll into some nasty scalar code and rebuild the vector.
3549 EVT EltVT = WidenVT.getVectorElementType();
3550 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(WidenNumElts, DAG.getUNDEF(EltVT));
3551 // Use the original element count so we don't do more scalar opts than
3552 // necessary.
3553 unsigned MinElts = N->getValueType(0).getVectorNumElements();
3554 for (unsigned i=0; i < MinElts; ++i) {
3555 SDValue Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, InEltVT, InOp,
3556 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, DL));
3557 if (N->getNumOperands() == 1)
3558 Ops[i] = DAG.getNode(Opcode, DL, EltVT, Val);
3559 else
3560 Ops[i] = DAG.getNode(Opcode, DL, EltVT, Val, N->getOperand(1), Flags);
3561 }
3562
3563 return DAG.getBuildVector(WidenVT, DL, Ops);
3564}

3566SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_FP_TO_XINT_SAT(SDNode *N) {
3567 SDLoc dl(N);
3568 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
3569 ElementCount WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorElementCount();
3570
3571 SDValue Src = N->getOperand(0);
3572 EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType();
3573
3574 // Also widen the input.
3575 if (getTypeAction(SrcVT) == TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector) {
3576 Src = GetWidenedVector(Src);
3577 SrcVT = Src.getValueType();
3578 }
3579
3580 // Input and output not widened to the same size, give up.
3581 if (WidenNumElts != SrcVT.getVectorElementCount())
3582 return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(N, WidenNumElts.getKnownMinValue());
3583
3584 return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, WidenVT, Src, N->getOperand(1));
3585}

3587SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_Convert_StrictFP(SDNode *N) {
3588 SDValue InOp = N->getOperand(1);
3589 SDLoc DL(N);
3590 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> NewOps(N->op_begin(), N->op_end());
3591
3592 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
3593 unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorNumElements();
3594
3595 EVT InVT = InOp.getValueType();
3596 EVT InEltVT = InVT.getVectorElementType();
3597
3598 unsigned Opcode = N->getOpcode();
3599
3600 // FIXME: Optimizations need to be implemented here.
3601
3602 // Otherwise unroll into some nasty scalar code and rebuild the vector.
3603 EVT EltVT = WidenVT.getVectorElementType();
3604 std::array<EVT, 2> EltVTs = {{EltVT, MVT::Other}};
3605 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(WidenNumElts, DAG.getUNDEF(EltVT));
3606 SmallVector<SDValue, 32> OpChains;
3607 // Use the original element count so we don't do more scalar opts than
3608 // necessary.
3609 unsigned MinElts = N->getValueType(0).getVectorNumElements();
3610 for (unsigned i=0; i < MinElts; ++i) {
3611 NewOps[1] = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, InEltVT, InOp,
3612 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, DL));
3613 Ops[i] = DAG.getNode(Opcode, DL, EltVTs, NewOps);
3614 OpChains.push_back(Ops[i].getValue(1));
3615 }
3616 SDValue NewChain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, DL, MVT::Other, OpChains);
3617 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), NewChain);
3618
3619 return DAG.getBuildVector(WidenVT, DL, Ops);
3620}

3622SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG(SDNode *N) {
3623 unsigned Opcode = N->getOpcode();
3624 SDValue InOp = N->getOperand(0);
3625 SDLoc DL(N);
3626
3627 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
3628 EVT WidenSVT = WidenVT.getVectorElementType();
3629 unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorNumElements();
3630
3631 EVT InVT = InOp.getValueType();
3632 EVT InSVT = InVT.getVectorElementType();
3633 unsigned InVTNumElts = InVT.getVectorNumElements();
3634
3635 if (getTypeAction(InVT) == TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector) {
3636 InOp = GetWidenedVector(InOp);
3637 InVT = InOp.getValueType();
3638 if (InVT.getSizeInBits() == WidenVT.getSizeInBits()) {
3639 switch (Opcode) {
3640 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
3641 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
3642 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
3643 return DAG.getNode(Opcode, DL, WidenVT, InOp);
3644 }
3645 }
3646 }
3647
3648 // Unroll, extend the scalars and rebuild the vector.
3649 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops;
3650 for (unsigned i = 0, e = std::min(InVTNumElts, WidenNumElts); i != e; ++i) {
3651 SDValue Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, InSVT, InOp,
3652 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, DL));
3653 switch (Opcode) {
3654 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
3655 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, WidenSVT, Val);
3656 break;
3657 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
3658 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, DL, WidenSVT, Val);
3659 break;
3660 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
3661 Val = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, WidenSVT, Val);
3662 break;
3663 default:
3664 llvm_unreachable("A *_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG node was expected");
3665 }
3666 Ops.push_back(Val);
3667 }
3668
3669 while (Ops.size() != WidenNumElts)
3670 Ops.push_back(DAG.getUNDEF(WidenSVT));
3671
3672 return DAG.getBuildVector(WidenVT, DL, Ops);
3673}

3716SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_BITCAST(SDNode *N) {
3717 SDValue InOp = N->getOperand(0);
3718 EVT InVT = InOp.getValueType();
3719 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
3720 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), VT);
3721 SDLoc dl(N);
3722
3723 switch (getTypeAction(InVT)) {
3724 case TargetLowering::TypeLegal:
3725 break;
3726 case TargetLowering::TypeScalarizeScalableVector:
3727 report_fatal_error("Scalarization of scalable vectors is not supported.");
3728 case TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger: {
3729 // If the incoming type is a vector that is being promoted, then
3730 // we know that the elements are arranged differently and that we
3731 // must perform the conversion using a stack slot.
3732 if (InVT.isVector())
3733 break;
3734
3735 // If the InOp is promoted to the same size, convert it. Otherwise,
3736 // fall out of the switch and widen the promoted input.
3737 SDValue NInOp = GetPromotedInteger(InOp);
3738 EVT NInVT = NInOp.getValueType();
3739 if (WidenVT.bitsEq(NInVT)) {
3740 // For big endian targets we need to shift the input integer or the
3741 // interesting bits will end up at the wrong place.
3742 if (DAG.getDataLayout().isBigEndian()) {
3743 unsigned ShiftAmt = NInVT.getSizeInBits() - InVT.getSizeInBits();
3744 EVT ShiftAmtTy = TLI.getShiftAmountTy(NInVT, DAG.getDataLayout());
3745 assert(ShiftAmt < WidenVT.getSizeInBits() && "Too large shift amount!");
3746 NInOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, NInVT, NInOp,
3747 DAG.getConstant(ShiftAmt, dl, ShiftAmtTy));
3748 }
3749 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, WidenVT, NInOp);
3750 }
3751 InOp = NInOp;
3752 InVT = NInVT;
3753 break;
3754 }
3755 case TargetLowering::TypeSoftenFloat:
3756 case TargetLowering::TypePromoteFloat:
3757 case TargetLowering::TypeSoftPromoteHalf:
3758 case TargetLowering::TypeExpandInteger:
3759 case TargetLowering::TypeExpandFloat:
3760 case TargetLowering::TypeScalarizeVector:
3761 case TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector:
3762 break;
3763 case TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector:
3764 // If the InOp is widened to the same size, convert it. Otherwise, fall
3765 // out of the switch and widen the widened input.
3766 InOp = GetWidenedVector(InOp);
3767 InVT = InOp.getValueType();
3768 if (WidenVT.bitsEq(InVT))
3769 // The input widens to the same size. Convert to the widen value.
3770 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, WidenVT, InOp);
3771 break;
3772 }
3773
3774 unsigned WidenSize = WidenVT.getSizeInBits();
3775 unsigned InSize = InVT.getSizeInBits();
3776 // x86mmx is not an acceptable vector element type, so don't try.
3777 if (WidenSize % InSize == 0 && InVT != MVT::x86mmx) {
3778 // Determine new input vector type. The new input vector type will use
3779 // the same element type (if its a vector) or use the input type as a
3780 // vector. It is the same size as the type to widen to.
3781 EVT NewInVT;
3782 unsigned NewNumElts = WidenSize / InSize;
3783 if (InVT.isVector()) {
3784 EVT InEltVT = InVT.getVectorElementType();
3785 NewInVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), InEltVT,
3786 WidenSize / InEltVT.getSizeInBits());
3787 } else {
3788 NewInVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), InVT, NewNumElts);
3789 }
3790
3791 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(NewInVT)) {
3792 SDValue NewVec;
3793 if (InVT.isVector()) {
3794 // Because the result and the input are different vector types, widening
3795 // the result could create a legal type but widening the input might make
3796 // it an illegal type that might lead to repeatedly splitting the input
3797 // and then widening it. To avoid this, we widen the input only if
3798 // it results in a legal type.
3799 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(NewNumElts, DAG.getUNDEF(InVT));
3800 Ops[0] = InOp;
3801
3802 NewVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, NewInVT, Ops);
3803 } else {
3804 NewVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, dl, NewInVT, InOp);
3805 }
3806 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, WidenVT, NewVec);
3807 }
3808 }
3809
3810 return CreateStackStoreLoad(InOp, WidenVT);
3811}
3812
3813SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_BUILD_VECTOR(SDNode *N) {
3814 SDLoc dl(N);
3815 // Build a vector with undefined for the new nodes.
3816 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
3817
3818 // Integer BUILD_VECTOR operands may be larger than the node's vector element
3819 // type. The UNDEFs need to have the same type as the existing operands.
3820 EVT EltVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
3821 unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
3822
3823 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), VT);
3824 unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorNumElements();
3825
3826 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> NewOps(N->op_begin(), N->op_end());
3827 assert(WidenNumElts >= NumElts && "Shrinking vector instead of widening!");
3828 NewOps.append(WidenNumElts - NumElts, DAG.getUNDEF(EltVT));
3829
3830 return DAG.getBuildVector(WidenVT, dl, NewOps);
3831}
3832
3833SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_CONCAT_VECTORS(SDNode *N) {
3834 EVT InVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
3835 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
3836 SDLoc dl(N);
3837 unsigned NumOperands = N->getNumOperands();
3838
3839 bool InputWidened = false; // Indicates we need to widen the input.
3840 if (getTypeAction(InVT) != TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector) {
3841 unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorMinNumElements();
3842 unsigned NumInElts = InVT.getVectorMinNumElements();
3843 if (WidenNumElts % NumInElts == 0) {
3844 // Add undef vectors to widen to correct length.
3845 unsigned NumConcat = WidenNumElts / NumInElts;
3846 SDValue UndefVal = DAG.getUNDEF(InVT);
3847 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(NumConcat);
3848 for (unsigned i=0; i < NumOperands; ++i)
3849 Ops[i] = N->getOperand(i);
3850 for (unsigned i = NumOperands; i != NumConcat; ++i)
3851 Ops[i] = UndefVal;
3852 return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, WidenVT, Ops);
3853 }
3854 } else {
3855 InputWidened = true;
3856 if (WidenVT == TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), InVT)) {
3857 // The inputs and the result are widen to the same value.
3858 unsigned i;
3859 for (i=1; i < NumOperands; ++i)
3860 if (!N->getOperand(i).isUndef())
3861 break;
3862
3863 if (i == NumOperands)
3864 // Everything but the first operand is an UNDEF so just return the
3865 // widened first operand.
3866 return GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
3867
3868 if (NumOperands == 2) {
3869 assert(!WidenVT.isScalableVector() &&
3870 "Cannot use vector shuffles to widen CONCAT_VECTOR result");
3871 unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorNumElements();
3872 unsigned NumInElts = InVT.getVectorNumElements();
3873
3874 // Replace concat of two operands with a shuffle.
3875 SmallVector<int, 16> MaskOps(WidenNumElts, -1);
3876 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumInElts; ++i) {
3877 MaskOps[i] = i;
3878 MaskOps[i + NumInElts] = i + WidenNumElts;
3879 }
3880 return DAG.getVectorShuffle(WidenVT, dl,
3881 GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0)),
3882 GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(1)),
3883 MaskOps);
3884 }
3885 }
3886 }
3887
3888 assert(!WidenVT.isScalableVector() &&
3889 "Cannot use build vectors to widen CONCAT_VECTOR result");
3890 unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorNumElements();
3891 unsigned NumInElts = InVT.getVectorNumElements();
3892
3893 // Fall back to use extracts and build vector.
3894 EVT EltVT = WidenVT.getVectorElementType();
3895 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(WidenNumElts);
3896 unsigned Idx = 0;
3897 for (unsigned i=0; i < NumOperands; ++i) {
3898 SDValue InOp = N->getOperand(i);
3899 if (InputWidened)
3900 InOp = GetWidenedVector(InOp);
3901 for (unsigned j = 0; j < NumInElts; ++j)
3902 Ops[Idx++] = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, EltVT, InOp,
3903 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(j, dl));
3904 }
3905 SDValue UndefVal = DAG.getUNDEF(EltVT);
3906 for (; Idx < WidenNumElts; ++Idx)
3907 Ops[Idx] = UndefVal;
3908 return DAG.getBuildVector(WidenVT, dl, Ops);
3909}
3910
3911SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR(SDNode *N) {
3912 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
3913 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), VT);
3914 unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorNumElements();
3915 SDValue InOp = N->getOperand(0);
3916 SDValue Idx = N->getOperand(1);
3917 SDLoc dl(N);
3918
3919 if (getTypeAction(InOp.getValueType()) == TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector)
3920 InOp = GetWidenedVector(InOp);
3921
3922 EVT InVT = InOp.getValueType();
3923
3924 // Check if we can just return the input vector after widening.
3925 uint64_t IdxVal = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Idx)->getZExtValue();
3926 if (IdxVal == 0 && InVT == WidenVT)
3927 return InOp;
3928
3929 // Check if we can extract from the vector.
3930 unsigned InNumElts = InVT.getVectorNumElements();
3931 if (IdxVal % WidenNumElts == 0 && IdxVal + WidenNumElts < InNumElts)
3932 return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, WidenVT, InOp, Idx);
3933
3934 // We could try widening the input to the right length but for now, extract
3935 // the original elements, fill the rest with undefs and build a vector.
3936 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(WidenNumElts);
3937 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
3938 unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
3939 unsigned i;
3940 for (i = 0; i < NumElts; ++i)
3941 Ops[i] = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, EltVT, InOp,
3942 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(IdxVal + i, dl));
3943
3944 SDValue UndefVal = DAG.getUNDEF(EltVT);
3945 for (; i < WidenNumElts; ++i)
3946 Ops[i] = UndefVal;
3947 return DAG.getBuildVector(WidenVT, dl, Ops);
3948}

3950SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_INSERT_VECTOR_ELT(SDNode *N) {
3951 SDValue InOp = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
3952 return DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, SDLoc(N),
3953 InOp.getValueType(), InOp,
3954 N->getOperand(1), N->getOperand(2));

3957SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_LOAD(SDNode *N) {
3958 LoadSDNode *LD = cast<LoadSDNode>(N);
3959 ISD::LoadExtType ExtType = LD->getExtensionType();
3960
3961 // A vector must always be stored in memory as-is, i.e. without any padding
3962 // between the elements, since various code depend on it, e.g. in the
3963 // handling of a bitcast of a vector type to int, which may be done with a
3964 // vector store followed by an integer load. A vector that does not have
3965 // elements that are byte-sized must therefore be stored as an integer
3966 // built out of the extracted vector elements.
3967 if (!LD->getMemoryVT().isByteSized()) {
3968 SDValue Value, NewChain;
3969 std::tie(Value, NewChain) = TLI.scalarizeVectorLoad(LD, DAG);
3970 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(LD, 0), Value);
3971 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(LD, 1), NewChain);
3972 return SDValue();
3973 }
3974
3975 SDValue Result;
3976 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> LdChain; // Chain for the series of load
3977 if (ExtType != ISD::NON_EXTLOAD)
3978 Result = GenWidenVectorExtLoads(LdChain, LD, ExtType);
3979 else
3980 Result = GenWidenVectorLoads(LdChain, LD);
3981
3982 // If we generate a single load, we can use that for the chain. Otherwise,
3983 // build a factor node to remember the multiple loads are independent and
3984 // chain to that.
3985 SDValue NewChain;
3986 if (LdChain.size() == 1)
3987 NewChain = LdChain[0];
3988 else
3989 NewChain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, SDLoc(LD), MVT::Other, LdChain);
3990
3991 // Modified the chain - switch anything that used the old chain to use
3992 // the new one.
3993 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), NewChain);
3994
3995 return Result;
3996}

3998SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_MLOAD(MaskedLoadSDNode *N) {
3999
4000 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(),N->getValueType(0));
4001 SDValue Mask = N->getMask();
4002 EVT MaskVT = Mask.getValueType();
4003 SDValue PassThru = GetWidenedVector(N->getPassThru());
4004 ISD::LoadExtType ExtType = N->getExtensionType();
4005 SDLoc dl(N);
4006
4007 // The mask should be widened as well
4008 EVT WideMaskVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
4009 MaskVT.getVectorElementType(),
4010 WidenVT.getVectorNumElements());
4011 Mask = ModifyToType(Mask, WideMaskVT, true);
4012
4013 SDValue Res = DAG.getMaskedLoad(
4014 WidenVT, dl, N->getChain(), N->getBasePtr(), N->getOffset(), Mask,
4015 PassThru, N->getMemoryVT(), N->getMemOperand(), N->getAddressingMode(),
4016 ExtType, N->isExpandingLoad());
4017 // Legalize the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to
4018 // use the new one.
4019 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Res.getValue(1));
4020 return Res;
4021}

4023SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_MGATHER(MaskedGatherSDNode *N) {
4024
4025 EVT WideVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
4026 SDValue Mask = N->getMask();

4066// Return true is this is a SETCC node or a strict version of it.
4067static inline bool isSETCCOp(unsigned Opcode) {
4068 switch (Opcode) {
4069 case ISD::SETCC:
4070 case ISD::STRICT_FSETCC:
4071 case ISD::STRICT_FSETCCS:
4072 return true;
4073 }
4074 return false;
4075}
4076
4077// Return true if this is a node that could have two SETCCs as operands.
4078static inline bool isLogicalMaskOp(unsigned Opcode) {
4079 switch (Opcode) {
4080 case ISD::AND:
4081 case ISD::OR:
4082 case ISD::XOR:
4083 return true;
4084 }
4085 return false;
4086}

4088// If N is a SETCC or a strict variant of it, return the type
4089// of the compare operands.
4090static inline EVT getSETCCOperandType(SDValue N) {
4091 unsigned OpNo = N->isStrictFPOpcode() ? 1 : 0;
4092 return N->getOperand(OpNo).getValueType();
4093}

4095// This is used just for the assert in convertMask(). Check that this either
4096// a SETCC or a previously handled SETCC by convertMask().
4097#ifndef NDEBUG
4098static inline bool isSETCCorConvertedSETCC(SDValue N) {
4099 if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR)
4100 N = N.getOperand(0);
4101 else if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS) {
4102 for (unsigned i = 1; i < N->getNumOperands(); ++i)
4103 if (!N->getOperand(i)->isUndef())
4104 return false;
4105 N = N.getOperand(0);
4106 }
4107
4108 if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::TRUNCATE)
4109 N = N.getOperand(0);
4110 else if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND)
4111 N = N.getOperand(0);
4112
4113 if (isLogicalMaskOp(N.getOpcode()))
4114 return isSETCCorConvertedSETCC(N.getOperand(0)) &&
4115 isSETCCorConvertedSETCC(N.getOperand(1));
4116
4117 return (isSETCCOp(N.getOpcode()) ||
4118 ISD::isBuildVectorOfConstantSDNodes(N.getNode()));
4119}
4120#endif

4122// Return a mask of vector type MaskVT to replace InMask. Also adjust MaskVT
4123// to ToMaskVT if needed with vector extension or truncation.
4124SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::convertMask(SDValue InMask, EVT MaskVT,
4125 EVT ToMaskVT) {
4126 // Currently a SETCC or a AND/OR/XOR with two SETCCs are handled.
4127 // FIXME: This code seems to be too restrictive, we might consider
4128 // generalizing it or dropping it.
4129 assert(isSETCCorConvertedSETCC(InMask) && "Unexpected mask argument.");
4130
4131 // Make a new Mask node, with a legal result VT.
4132 SDValue Mask;
4133 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Ops;
4134 for (unsigned i = 0, e = InMask->getNumOperands(); i < e; ++i)
4135 Ops.push_back(InMask->getOperand(i));
4136 if (InMask->isStrictFPOpcode()) {
4137 Mask = DAG.getNode(InMask->getOpcode(), SDLoc(InMask),
4138 { MaskVT, MVT::Other }, Ops);
4139 ReplaceValueWith(InMask.getValue(1), Mask.getValue(1));
4140 }
4141 else
4142 Mask = DAG.getNode(InMask->getOpcode(), SDLoc(InMask), MaskVT, Ops);
4143
4144 // If MaskVT has smaller or bigger elements than ToMaskVT, a vector sign
4145 // extend or truncate is needed.
4146 LLVMContext &Ctx = *DAG.getContext();
4147 unsigned MaskScalarBits = MaskVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
4148 unsigned ToMaskScalBits = ToMaskVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
4149 if (MaskScalarBits < ToMaskScalBits) {
4150 EVT ExtVT = EVT::getVectorVT(Ctx, ToMaskVT.getVectorElementType(),
4151 MaskVT.getVectorNumElements());
4152 Mask = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, SDLoc(Mask), ExtVT, Mask);
4153 } else if (MaskScalarBits > ToMaskScalBits) {
4154 EVT TruncVT = EVT::getVectorVT(Ctx, ToMaskVT.getVectorElementType(),
4155 MaskVT.getVectorNumElements());
4156 Mask = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SDLoc(Mask), TruncVT, Mask);
4157 }
4158
4159 assert(Mask->getValueType(0).getScalarSizeInBits() ==
4160 ToMaskVT.getScalarSizeInBits() &&
4161 "Mask should have the right element size by now.");
4162
4163 // Adjust Mask to the right number of elements.
4164 unsigned CurrMaskNumEls = Mask->getValueType(0).getVectorNumElements();
4165 if (CurrMaskNumEls > ToMaskVT.getVectorNumElements()) {
4166 SDValue ZeroIdx = DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, SDLoc(Mask));
4167 Mask = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, SDLoc(Mask), ToMaskVT, Mask,
4168 ZeroIdx);
4169 } else if (CurrMaskNumEls < ToMaskVT.getVectorNumElements()) {
4170 unsigned NumSubVecs = (ToMaskVT.getVectorNumElements() / CurrMaskNumEls);
4171 EVT SubVT = Mask->getValueType(0);
4172 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> SubOps(NumSubVecs, DAG.getUNDEF(SubVT));
4173 SubOps[0] = Mask;
4174 Mask = DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, SDLoc(Mask), ToMaskVT, SubOps);
4175 }
4176
4177 assert((Mask->getValueType(0) == ToMaskVT) &&
4178 "A mask of ToMaskVT should have been produced by now.");
4179
4180 return Mask;
4181}
4182
4183// This method tries to handle some special cases for the vselect mask
4184// and if needed adjusting the mask vector type to match that of the VSELECT.
4185// Without it, many cases end up with scalarization of the SETCC, with many
4186// unnecessary instructions.
4187SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVSELECTMask(SDNode *N) {
4188 LLVMContext &Ctx = *DAG.getContext();
4189 SDValue Cond = N->getOperand(0);
4190
4191 if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::VSELECT)
4192 return SDValue();
4193
4194 if (!isSETCCOp(Cond->getOpcode()) && !isLogicalMaskOp(Cond->getOpcode()))
4195 return SDValue();
4196
4197 // If this is a splitted VSELECT that was previously already handled, do
4198 // nothing.
4199 EVT CondVT = Cond->getValueType(0);
4200 if (CondVT.getScalarSizeInBits() != 1)
4201 return SDValue();
4202
4203 EVT VSelVT = N->getValueType(0);
4204 // Only handle vector types which are a power of 2.
4205 if (!isPowerOf2_64(VSelVT.getSizeInBits()))
4206 return SDValue();
4207
4208 // Don't touch if this will be scalarized.
4209 EVT FinalVT = VSelVT;
4210 while (getTypeAction(FinalVT) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector)
4211 FinalVT = FinalVT.getHalfNumVectorElementsVT(Ctx);
4212
4213 if (FinalVT.getVectorNumElements() == 1)
4214 return SDValue();
4215
4216 // If there is support for an i1 vector mask, don't touch.
4217 if (isSETCCOp(Cond.getOpcode())) {
4218 EVT SetCCOpVT = getSETCCOperandType(Cond);
4219 while (TLI.getTypeAction(Ctx, SetCCOpVT) != TargetLowering::TypeLegal)
4220 SetCCOpVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(Ctx, SetCCOpVT);
4221 EVT SetCCResVT = getSetCCResultType(SetCCOpVT);
4222 if (SetCCResVT.getScalarSizeInBits() == 1)
4223 return SDValue();
4224 } else if (CondVT.getScalarType() == MVT::i1) {
4225 // If there is support for an i1 vector mask (or only scalar i1 conditions),
4226 // don't touch.
4227 while (TLI.getTypeAction(Ctx, CondVT) != TargetLowering::TypeLegal)
4228 CondVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(Ctx, CondVT);
4229
4230 if (CondVT.getScalarType() == MVT::i1)
4231 return SDValue();
4232 }
4233
4234 // Widen the vselect result type if needed.
4235 if (getTypeAction(VSelVT) == TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector)
4236 VSelVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(Ctx, VSelVT);
4237
4238 // The mask of the VSELECT should have integer elements.
4239 EVT ToMaskVT = VSelVT;
4240 if (!ToMaskVT.getScalarType().isInteger())
4241 ToMaskVT = ToMaskVT.changeVectorElementTypeToInteger();
4242
4243 SDValue Mask;
4244 if (isSETCCOp(Cond->getOpcode())) {
4245 EVT MaskVT = getSetCCResultType(getSETCCOperandType(Cond));
4246 Mask = convertMask(Cond, MaskVT, ToMaskVT);
4247 } else if (isLogicalMaskOp(Cond->getOpcode()) &&
4248 isSETCCOp(Cond->getOperand(0).getOpcode()) &&
4249 isSETCCOp(Cond->getOperand(1).getOpcode())) {
4250 // Cond is (AND/OR/XOR (SETCC, SETCC))
4251 SDValue SETCC0 = Cond->getOperand(0);
4252 SDValue SETCC1 = Cond->getOperand(1);
4253 EVT VT0 = getSetCCResultType(getSETCCOperandType(SETCC0));
4254 EVT VT1 = getSetCCResultType(getSETCCOperandType(SETCC1));
4255 unsigned ScalarBits0 = VT0.getScalarSizeInBits();
4256 unsigned ScalarBits1 = VT1.getScalarSizeInBits();
4257 unsigned ScalarBits_ToMask = ToMaskVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
4258 EVT MaskVT;
4259 // If the two SETCCs have different VTs, either extend/truncate one of
4260 // them to the other "towards" ToMaskVT, or truncate one and extend the
4261 // other to ToMaskVT.
4262 if (ScalarBits0 != ScalarBits1) {
4263 EVT NarrowVT = ((ScalarBits0 < ScalarBits1) ? VT0 : VT1);
4264 EVT WideVT = ((NarrowVT == VT0) ? VT1 : VT0);
4265 if (ScalarBits_ToMask >= WideVT.getScalarSizeInBits())
4266 MaskVT = WideVT;
4267 else if (ScalarBits_ToMask <= NarrowVT.getScalarSizeInBits())
4268 MaskVT = NarrowVT;
4269 else
4270 MaskVT = ToMaskVT;
4271 } else
4272 // If the two SETCCs have the same VT, don't change it.
4273 MaskVT = VT0;
4274
4275 // Make new SETCCs and logical nodes.
4276 SETCC0 = convertMask(SETCC0, VT0, MaskVT);
4277 SETCC1 = convertMask(SETCC1, VT1, MaskVT);
4278 Cond = DAG.getNode(Cond->getOpcode(), SDLoc(Cond), MaskVT, SETCC0, SETCC1);
4279
4280 // Convert the logical op for VSELECT if needed.
4281 Mask = convertMask(Cond, MaskVT, ToMaskVT);
4282 } else
4283 return SDValue();
4284
4285 return Mask;
4286}

4288SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_SELECT(SDNode *N) {
4289 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
4290 unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorNumElements();
4291
4292 SDValue Cond1 = N->getOperand(0);
4293 EVT CondVT = Cond1.getValueType();
4294 if (CondVT.isVector()) {
4295 if (SDValue WideCond = WidenVSELECTMask(N)) {
4296 SDValue InOp1 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(1));
4297 SDValue InOp2 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(2));
4298 assert(InOp1.getValueType() == WidenVT && InOp2.getValueType() == WidenVT);
4299 return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), SDLoc(N),
4300 WidenVT, WideCond, InOp1, InOp2);
4301 }
4302
4303 EVT CondEltVT = CondVT.getVectorElementType();
4304 EVT CondWidenVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
4305 CondEltVT, WidenNumElts);
4306 if (getTypeAction(CondVT) == TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector)
4307 Cond1 = GetWidenedVector(Cond1);
4308
4309 // If we have to split the condition there is no point in widening the
4310 // select. This would result in an cycle of widening the select ->
4311 // widening the condition operand -> splitting the condition operand ->
4312 // splitting the select -> widening the select. Instead split this select
4313 // further and widen the resulting type.
4314 if (getTypeAction(CondVT) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector) {
4315 SDValue SplitSelect = SplitVecOp_VSELECT(N, 0);
4316 SDValue Res = ModifyToType(SplitSelect, WidenVT);
4317 return Res;
4318 }
4319
4320 if (Cond1.getValueType() != CondWidenVT)
4321 Cond1 = ModifyToType(Cond1, CondWidenVT);
4322 }
4323
4324 SDValue InOp1 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(1));
4325 SDValue InOp2 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(2));
4326 assert(InOp1.getValueType() == WidenVT && InOp2.getValueType() == WidenVT);
4327 return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), SDLoc(N),
4328 WidenVT, Cond1, InOp1, InOp2);
4329}
4330
4331SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_SELECT_CC(SDNode *N) {
4332 SDValue InOp1 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(2));
4333 SDValue InOp2 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(3));
4334 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT_CC, SDLoc(N),
4335 InOp1.getValueType(), N->getOperand(0),
4336 N->getOperand(1), InOp1, InOp2, N->getOperand(4));
4337}
4338
4339SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_UNDEF(SDNode *N) {
4340 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
4341 return DAG.getUNDEF(WidenVT);
4342}
4343
4344SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_VECTOR_SHUFFLE(ShuffleVectorSDNode *N) {
4345 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
4346 SDLoc dl(N);
4347
4348 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), VT);
4349 unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
4350 unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorNumElements();
4351
4352 SDValue InOp1 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
4353 SDValue InOp2 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(1));
4354
4355 // Adjust mask based on new input vector length.
4356 SmallVector<int, 16> NewMask;
4357 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
4358 int Idx = N->getMaskElt(i);
4359 if (Idx < (int)NumElts)
4360 NewMask.push_back(Idx);
4361 else
4362 NewMask.push_back(Idx - NumElts + WidenNumElts);
4363 }
4364 for (unsigned i = NumElts; i != WidenNumElts; ++i)
4365 NewMask.push_back(-1);
4366 return DAG.getVectorShuffle(WidenVT, dl, InOp1, InOp2, NewMask);
4367}
4368
4369SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_SETCC(SDNode *N) {
4370 assert(N->getValueType(0).isVector() &&
4371 N->getOperand(0).getValueType().isVector() &&
4372 "Operands must be vectors");
4373 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
4374 unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorNumElements();
4375
4376 SDValue InOp1 = N->getOperand(0);
4377 EVT InVT = InOp1.getValueType();
4378 assert(InVT.isVector() && "can not widen non-vector type");
4379 EVT WidenInVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
4380 InVT.getVectorElementType(), WidenNumElts);
4381
4382 // The input and output types often differ here, and it could be that while
4383 // we'd prefer to widen the result type, the input operands have been split.
4384 // In this case, we also need to split the result of this node as well.
4385 if (getTypeAction(InVT) == TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector) {
4386 SDValue SplitVSetCC = SplitVecOp_VSETCC(N);
4387 SDValue Res = ModifyToType(SplitVSetCC, WidenVT);
4388 return Res;
4389 }
4390
4391 // If the inputs also widen, handle them directly. Otherwise widen by hand.
4392 SDValue InOp2 = N->getOperand(1);
4393 if (getTypeAction(InVT) == TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector) {
4394 InOp1 = GetWidenedVector(InOp1);
4395 InOp2 = GetWidenedVector(InOp2);
4396 } else {
4397 InOp1 = DAG.WidenVector(InOp1, SDLoc(N));
4398 InOp2 = DAG.WidenVector(InOp2, SDLoc(N));
4399 }
4400
4401 // Assume that the input and output will be widen appropriately. If not,
4402 // we will have to unroll it at some point.
4403 assert(InOp1.getValueType() == WidenInVT &&
4404 InOp2.getValueType() == WidenInVT &&
4405 "Input not widened to expected type!");
4406 (void)WidenInVT;
4407 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SETCC, SDLoc(N),
4408 WidenVT, InOp1, InOp2, N->getOperand(2));
4409}
4410
4411SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecRes_STRICT_FSETCC(SDNode *N) {
4412 assert(N->getValueType(0).isVector() &&
4413 N->getOperand(1).getValueType().isVector() &&
4414 "Operands must be vectors");
4415 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
4416 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), VT);
4417 unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorNumElements();
4418 unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
4419 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
4420
4421 SDLoc dl(N);
4422 SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0);
4423 SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(1);
4424 SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(2);
4425 SDValue CC = N->getOperand(3);
4426 EVT TmpEltVT = LHS.getValueType().getVectorElementType();
4427
4428 // Fully unroll and reassemble.
4429 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Scalars(WidenNumElts, DAG.getUNDEF(EltVT));
4430 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Chains(NumElts);
4431 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
4432 SDValue LHSElem = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, TmpEltVT, LHS,
4433 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, dl));
4434 SDValue RHSElem = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, TmpEltVT, RHS,
4435 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, dl));
4436
4437 Scalars[i] = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, {MVT::i1, MVT::Other},
4438 {Chain, LHSElem, RHSElem, CC});
4439 Chains[i] = Scalars[i].getValue(1);
4440 Scalars[i] = DAG.getSelect(dl, EltVT, Scalars[i],
4441 DAG.getBoolConstant(true, dl, EltVT, VT),
4442 DAG.getBoolConstant(false, dl, EltVT, VT));
4443 }
4444
4445 SDValue NewChain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Chains);
4446 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), NewChain);
4447
4448 return DAG.getBuildVector(WidenVT, dl, Scalars);
4449}
