4451//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4452// Widen Vector Operand
4453//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4454bool DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVectorOperand(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
4455 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Widen node operand " << OpNo << ": "; N->dump(&DAG);
4456 dbgs() << "\n");
4457 SDValue Res = SDValue();
4458
4459 // See if the target wants to custom widen this node.
4460 if (CustomLowerNode(N, N->getOperand(OpNo).getValueType(), false))
4461 return false;
4462
4463 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
4464 default:
4465#ifndef NDEBUG
4466 dbgs() << "WidenVectorOperand op #" << OpNo << ": ";
4467 N->dump(&DAG);
4468 dbgs() << "\n";
4469#endif
4470 llvm_unreachable("Do not know how to widen this operator's operand!");
4471
4472 case ISD::BITCAST: Res = WidenVecOp_BITCAST(N); break;
4473 case ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS: Res = WidenVecOp_CONCAT_VECTORS(N); break;
4474 case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR: Res = WidenVecOp_EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR(N); break;
4475 case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT: Res = WidenVecOp_EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(N); break;
4476 case ISD::STORE: Res = WidenVecOp_STORE(N); break;
4477 case ISD::MSTORE: Res = WidenVecOp_MSTORE(N, OpNo); break;
4478 case ISD::MGATHER: Res = WidenVecOp_MGATHER(N, OpNo); break;
4479 case ISD::MSCATTER: Res = WidenVecOp_MSCATTER(N, OpNo); break;
4480 case ISD::SETCC: Res = WidenVecOp_SETCC(N); break;
4481 case ISD::STRICT_FSETCC:
4482 case ISD::STRICT_FSETCCS: Res = WidenVecOp_STRICT_FSETCC(N); break;
4483 case ISD::VSELECT: Res = WidenVecOp_VSELECT(N); break;
4484 case ISD::FCOPYSIGN: Res = WidenVecOp_FCOPYSIGN(N); break;
4485
4486 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND:
4487 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
4488 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
4489 Res = WidenVecOp_EXTEND(N);
4490 break;
4491
4492 case ISD::FP_EXTEND:
4493 case ISD::STRICT_FP_EXTEND:
4494 case ISD::FP_ROUND:
4495 case ISD::STRICT_FP_ROUND:
4496 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT:
4497 case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT:
4498 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT:
4499 case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_UINT:
4500 case ISD::SINT_TO_FP:
4501 case ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP:
4502 case ISD::UINT_TO_FP:
4503 case ISD::STRICT_UINT_TO_FP:
4504 case ISD::TRUNCATE:
4505 Res = WidenVecOp_Convert(N);
4506 break;
4507
4508 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT:
4509 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT_SAT:
4510 Res = WidenVecOp_FP_TO_XINT_SAT(N);
4511 break;
4512
4513 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FADD:
4514 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMUL:
4515 case ISD::VECREDUCE_ADD:
4516 case ISD::VECREDUCE_MUL:
4517 case ISD::VECREDUCE_AND:
4518 case ISD::VECREDUCE_OR:
4519 case ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR:
4520 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX:
4521 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN:
4522 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX:
4523 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN:
4524 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMAX:
4525 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMIN:
4526 Res = WidenVecOp_VECREDUCE(N);
4527 break;
4528 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SEQ_FADD:
4529 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SEQ_FMUL:
4530 Res = WidenVecOp_VECREDUCE_SEQ(N);
4531 break;
4532 }
4533
4534 // If Res is null, the sub-method took care of registering the result.
4535 if (!Res.getNode()) return false;
4536
4537 // If the result is N, the sub-method updated N in place. Tell the legalizer
4538 // core about this.
4539 if (Res.getNode() == N)
4540 return true;
4541
4542
4543 if (N->isStrictFPOpcode())
4544 assert(Res.getValueType() == N->getValueType(0) && N->getNumValues() == 2 &&
4545 "Invalid operand expansion");
4546 else
4547 assert(Res.getValueType() == N->getValueType(0) && N->getNumValues() == 1 &&
4548 "Invalid operand expansion");
4549
4550 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 0), Res);
4551 return false;
4552}
4553
4554SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_EXTEND(SDNode *N) {
4555 SDLoc DL(N);
4556 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
4557
4558 SDValue InOp = N->getOperand(0);
4559 assert(getTypeAction(InOp.getValueType()) ==
4560 TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector &&
4561 "Unexpected type action");
4562 InOp = GetWidenedVector(InOp);
4563 assert(VT.getVectorNumElements() <
4564 InOp.getValueType().getVectorNumElements() &&
4565 "Input wasn't widened!");
4566
4567 // We may need to further widen the operand until it has the same total
4568 // vector size as the result.
4569 EVT InVT = InOp.getValueType();
4570 if (InVT.getSizeInBits() != VT.getSizeInBits()) {
4571 EVT InEltVT = InVT.getVectorElementType();
4572 for (int i = MVT::FIRST_VECTOR_VALUETYPE, e = MVT::LAST_VECTOR_VALUETYPE; i < e; ++i) {
4573 EVT FixedVT = (MVT::SimpleValueType)i;
4574 EVT FixedEltVT = FixedVT.getVectorElementType();
4575 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(FixedVT) &&
4576 FixedVT.getSizeInBits() == VT.getSizeInBits() &&
4577 FixedEltVT == InEltVT) {
4578 assert(FixedVT.getVectorNumElements() >= VT.getVectorNumElements() &&
4579 "Not enough elements in the fixed type for the operand!");
4580 assert(FixedVT.getVectorNumElements() != InVT.getVectorNumElements() &&
4581 "We can't have the same type as we started with!");
4582 if (FixedVT.getVectorNumElements() > InVT.getVectorNumElements())
4583 InOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR, DL, FixedVT,
4584 DAG.getUNDEF(FixedVT), InOp,
4585 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
4586 else
4587 InOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, FixedVT, InOp,
4588 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
4589 break;
4590 }
4591 }
4592 InVT = InOp.getValueType();
4593 if (InVT.getSizeInBits() != VT.getSizeInBits())
4594 // We couldn't find a legal vector type that was a widening of the input
4595 // and could be extended in-register to the result type, so we have to
4596 // scalarize.
4597 return WidenVecOp_Convert(N);
4598 }
4599
4600 // Use special DAG nodes to represent the operation of extending the
4601 // low lanes.
4602 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
4603 default:
4604 llvm_unreachable("Extend legalization on extend operation!");
4605 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND:
4606 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG, DL, VT, InOp);
4607 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
4608 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG, DL, VT, InOp);
4609 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
4610 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG, DL, VT, InOp);
4611 }
4612}
4613
4614SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_FCOPYSIGN(SDNode *N) {
4615 // The result (and first input) is legal, but the second input is illegal.
4616 // We can't do much to fix that, so just unroll and let the extracts off of
4617 // the second input be widened as needed later.
4618 return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(N);
4619}
4620
4621SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_Convert(SDNode *N) {
4622 // Since the result is legal and the input is illegal.
4623 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
4624 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
4625 SDLoc dl(N);
4626 unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
4627 SDValue InOp = N->getOperand(N->isStrictFPOpcode() ? 1 : 0);
4628 assert(getTypeAction(InOp.getValueType()) ==
4629 TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector &&
4630 "Unexpected type action");
4631 InOp = GetWidenedVector(InOp);
4632 EVT InVT = InOp.getValueType();
4633 unsigned Opcode = N->getOpcode();
4634
4635 // See if a widened result type would be legal, if so widen the node.
4636 // FIXME: This isn't safe for StrictFP. Other optimization here is needed.
4637 EVT WideVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), EltVT,
4638 InVT.getVectorNumElements());
4639 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(WideVT) && !N->isStrictFPOpcode()) {
4640 SDValue Res;
4641 if (N->isStrictFPOpcode()) {
4642 if (Opcode == ISD::STRICT_FP_ROUND)
4643 Res = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, { WideVT, MVT::Other },
4644 { N->getOperand(0), InOp, N->getOperand(2) });
4645 else
4646 Res = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, { WideVT, MVT::Other },
4647 { N->getOperand(0), InOp });
4648 // Legalize the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to
4649 // use the new one.
4650 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Res.getValue(1));
4651 } else {
4652 if (Opcode == ISD::FP_ROUND)
4653 Res = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, WideVT, InOp, N->getOperand(1));
4654 else
4655 Res = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, WideVT, InOp);
4656 }
4657 return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, VT, Res,
4658 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, dl));
4659 }
4660
4661 EVT InEltVT = InVT.getVectorElementType();
4662
4663 // Unroll the convert into some scalar code and create a nasty build vector.
4664 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(NumElts);
4665 if (N->isStrictFPOpcode()) {
4666 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> NewOps(N->op_begin(), N->op_end());
4667 SmallVector<SDValue, 32> OpChains;
4668 for (unsigned i=0; i < NumElts; ++i) {
4669 NewOps[1] = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, InEltVT, InOp,
4670 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, dl));
4671 Ops[i] = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, { EltVT, MVT::Other }, NewOps);
4672 OpChains.push_back(Ops[i].getValue(1));
4673 }
4674 SDValue NewChain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, OpChains);
4675 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), NewChain);
4676 } else {
4677 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumElts; ++i)
4678 Ops[i] = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, EltVT,
4679 DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, InEltVT,
4680 InOp, DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, dl)));
4681 }
4682
4683 return DAG.getBuildVector(VT, dl, Ops);
4684}
4685
4686SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_FP_TO_XINT_SAT(SDNode *N) {
4687 EVT DstVT = N->getValueType(0);
4688 SDValue Src = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
4689 EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType();
4690 ElementCount WideNumElts = SrcVT.getVectorElementCount();
4691 SDLoc dl(N);
4692
4693 // See if a widened result type would be legal, if so widen the node.
4694 EVT WideDstVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
4695 DstVT.getVectorElementType(), WideNumElts);
4696 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(WideDstVT)) {
4697 SDValue Res =
4698 DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, WideDstVT, Src, N->getOperand(1));
4699 return DAG.getNode(
4700 ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, DstVT, Res,
4701 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
4702 }
4703
4704 // Give up and unroll.
4705 return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(N);
4706}
4707
4708SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_BITCAST(SDNode *N) {
4709 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
4710 SDValue InOp = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
4711 EVT InWidenVT = InOp.getValueType();
4712 SDLoc dl(N);
4713
4714 // Check if we can convert between two legal vector types and extract.
4715 unsigned InWidenSize = InWidenVT.getSizeInBits();
4716 unsigned Size = VT.getSizeInBits();
4717 // x86mmx is not an acceptable vector element type, so don't try.
4718 if (InWidenSize % Size == 0 && !VT.isVector() && VT != MVT::x86mmx) {
4719 unsigned NewNumElts = InWidenSize / Size;
4720 EVT NewVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), VT, NewNumElts);
4721 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(NewVT)) {
4722 SDValue BitOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NewVT, InOp);
4723 return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, VT, BitOp,
4724 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, dl));
4725 }
4726 }
4727
4728 // Handle a case like bitcast v12i8 -> v3i32. Normally that would get widened
4729 // to v16i8 -> v4i32, but for a target where v3i32 is legal but v12i8 is not,
4730 // we end up here. Handling the case here with EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR avoids
4731 // having to copy via memory.
4732 if (VT.isVector()) {
4733 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
4734 unsigned EltSize = EltVT.getSizeInBits();
4735 if (InWidenSize % EltSize == 0) {
4736 unsigned NewNumElts = InWidenSize / EltSize;
4737 EVT NewVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), EltVT, NewNumElts);
4738 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(NewVT)) {
4739 SDValue BitOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NewVT, InOp);
4740 return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, VT, BitOp,
4741 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, dl));
4742 }
4743 }
4744 }
4745
4746 return CreateStackStoreLoad(InOp, VT);
4747}
4748
4749SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_CONCAT_VECTORS(SDNode *N) {
4750 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
4751 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
4752 EVT InVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
4753 SDLoc dl(N);
4754
4755 // If the widen width for this operand is the same as the width of the concat
4756 // and all but the first operand is undef, just use the widened operand.
4757 unsigned NumOperands = N->getNumOperands();
4758 if (VT == TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), InVT)) {
4759 unsigned i;
4760 for (i = 1; i < NumOperands; ++i)
4761 if (!N->getOperand(i).isUndef())
4762 break;
4763
4764 if (i == NumOperands)
4765 return GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
4766 }
4767
4768 // Otherwise, fall back to a nasty build vector.
4769 unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
4770 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(NumElts);
4771
4772 unsigned NumInElts = InVT.getVectorNumElements();
4773
4774 unsigned Idx = 0;
4775 for (unsigned i=0; i < NumOperands; ++i) {
4776 SDValue InOp = N->getOperand(i);
4777 assert(getTypeAction(InOp.getValueType()) ==
4778 TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector &&
4779 "Unexpected type action");
4780 InOp = GetWidenedVector(InOp);
4781 for (unsigned j = 0; j < NumInElts; ++j)
4782 Ops[Idx++] = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, EltVT, InOp,
4783 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(j, dl));
4784 }
4785 return DAG.getBuildVector(VT, dl, Ops);
4786}
4787
4788SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR(SDNode *N) {
4789 SDValue InOp = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));

4800SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_STORE(SDNode *N) {
4801 // We have to widen the value, but we want only to store the original
4802 // vector type.
4803 StoreSDNode *ST = cast<StoreSDNode>(N);
4804
4805 if (!ST->getMemoryVT().getScalarType().isByteSized())
4806 return TLI.scalarizeVectorStore(ST, DAG);
4807
4808 if (ST->isTruncatingStore())
4809 return TLI.scalarizeVectorStore(ST, DAG);
4810
4811 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> StChain;
4812 GenWidenVectorStores(StChain, ST);
4813
4814 if (StChain.size() == 1)
4815 return StChain[0];
4816 else
4817 return DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, SDLoc(ST), MVT::Other, StChain);
4818}

4820SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_MSTORE(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
4821 assert((OpNo == 1 || OpNo == 3) &&
4822 "Can widen only data or mask operand of mstore");
4823 MaskedStoreSDNode *MST = cast<MaskedStoreSDNode>(N);
4824 SDValue Mask = MST->getMask();
4825 EVT MaskVT = Mask.getValueType();
4826 SDValue StVal = MST->getValue();
4827 SDLoc dl(N);
4828
4829 if (OpNo == 1) {
4830 // Widen the value.
4831 StVal = GetWidenedVector(StVal);
4832
4833 // The mask should be widened as well.
4834 EVT WideVT = StVal.getValueType();
4835 EVT WideMaskVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
4836 MaskVT.getVectorElementType(),
4837 WideVT.getVectorNumElements());
4838 Mask = ModifyToType(Mask, WideMaskVT, true);
4839 } else {
4840 // Widen the mask.
4841 EVT WideMaskVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), MaskVT);
4842 Mask = ModifyToType(Mask, WideMaskVT, true);
4843
4844 EVT ValueVT = StVal.getValueType();
4845 EVT WideVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
4846 ValueVT.getVectorElementType(),
4847 WideMaskVT.getVectorNumElements());
4848 StVal = ModifyToType(StVal, WideVT);
4849 }
4850
4851 assert(Mask.getValueType().getVectorNumElements() ==
4852 StVal.getValueType().getVectorNumElements() &&
4853 "Mask and data vectors should have the same number of elements");
4854 return DAG.getMaskedStore(MST->getChain(), dl, StVal, MST->getBasePtr(),
4855 MST->getOffset(), Mask, MST->getMemoryVT(),
4856 MST->getMemOperand(), MST->getAddressingMode(),
4857 false, MST->isCompressingStore());
4858}

4881SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_MSCATTER(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
4882 MaskedScatterSDNode *MSC = cast<MaskedScatterSDNode>(N);
4883 SDValue DataOp = MSC->getValue();
4884 SDValue Mask = MSC->getMask();
4885 SDValue Index = MSC->getIndex();
4886 SDValue Scale = MSC->getScale();
4887 EVT WideMemVT = MSC->getMemoryVT();
4888
4889 if (OpNo == 1) {

4892

4906 WideMemVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
4907 MSC->getMemoryVT().getScalarType(), NumElts);
4908 } else if (OpNo == 4) {
4909 // Just widen the index. It's allowed to have extra elements.
4910 Index = GetWidenedVector(Index);
4911 } else

4913
4914 SDValue Ops[] = {MSC->getChain(), DataOp, Mask, MSC->getBasePtr(), Index,

4918 MSC->isTruncatingStore());

4921SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_SETCC(SDNode *N) {
4922 SDValue InOp0 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
4923 SDValue InOp1 = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(1));
4924 SDLoc dl(N);
4925 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
4926
4927 // WARNING: In this code we widen the compare instruction with garbage.
4928 // This garbage may contain denormal floats which may be slow. Is this a real
4929 // concern ? Should we zero the unused lanes if this is a float compare ?
4930
4931 // Get a new SETCC node to compare the newly widened operands.
4932 // Only some of the compared elements are legal.
4933 EVT SVT = getSetCCResultType(InOp0.getValueType());
4934 // The result type is legal, if its vXi1, keep vXi1 for the new SETCC.
4935 if (VT.getScalarType() == MVT::i1)
4936 SVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), MVT::i1,
4937 SVT.getVectorNumElements());
4938
4939 SDValue WideSETCC = DAG.getNode(ISD::SETCC, SDLoc(N),
4940 SVT, InOp0, InOp1, N->getOperand(2));
4941
4942 // Extract the needed results from the result vector.
4943 EVT ResVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
4944 SVT.getVectorElementType(),
4945 VT.getVectorNumElements());
4946 SDValue CC = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, ResVT, WideSETCC,
4947 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, dl));
4948
4949 EVT OpVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
4950 ISD::NodeType ExtendCode =
4951 TargetLowering::getExtendForContent(TLI.getBooleanContents(OpVT));
4952 return DAG.getNode(ExtendCode, dl, VT, CC);
4953}

4955SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_STRICT_FSETCC(SDNode *N) {
4956 SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0);
4957 SDValue LHS = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(1));
4958 SDValue RHS = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(2));
4959 SDValue CC = N->getOperand(3);
4960 SDLoc dl(N);
4961
4962 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
4963 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
4964 EVT TmpEltVT = LHS.getValueType().getVectorElementType();
4965 unsigned NumElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
4966
4967 // Unroll into a build vector.
4968 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Scalars(NumElts);
4969 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Chains(NumElts);
4970
4971 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
4972 SDValue LHSElem = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, TmpEltVT, LHS,
4973 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, dl));
4974 SDValue RHSElem = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, TmpEltVT, RHS,
4975 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(i, dl));
4976
4977 Scalars[i] = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, {MVT::i1, MVT::Other},
4978 {Chain, LHSElem, RHSElem, CC});
4979 Chains[i] = Scalars[i].getValue(1);
4980 Scalars[i] = DAG.getSelect(dl, EltVT, Scalars[i],
4981 DAG.getBoolConstant(true, dl, EltVT, VT),
4982 DAG.getBoolConstant(false, dl, EltVT, VT));
4983 }
4984
4985 SDValue NewChain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Chains);
4986 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), NewChain);
4987
4988 return DAG.getBuildVector(VT, dl, Scalars);
4989}

4991SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::WidenVecOp_VECREDUCE(SDNode *N) {
4992 SDLoc dl(N);
4993 SDValue Op = GetWidenedVector(N->getOperand(0));
4994 EVT OrigVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
4995 EVT WideVT = Op.getValueType();
4996 EVT ElemVT = OrigVT.getVectorElementType();
4997 SDNodeFlags Flags = N->getFlags();
4998
4999 unsigned Opc = N->getOpcode();
5000 unsigned BaseOpc = ISD::getVecReduceBaseOpcode(Opc);
5001 SDValue NeutralElem = DAG.getNeutralElement(BaseOpc, dl, ElemVT, Flags);
5002 assert(NeutralElem && "Neutral element must exist");
5003
5004 // Pad the vector with the neutral element.
5005 unsigned OrigElts = OrigVT.getVectorNumElements();
5006 unsigned WideElts = WideVT.getVectorNumElements();
5007 for (unsigned Idx = OrigElts; Idx < WideElts; Idx++)
5008 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, WideVT, Op, NeutralElem,
5009 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl));
5010
5011 return DAG.getNode(Opc, dl, N->getValueType(0), Op, Flags);
5012}

5056
5057//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5058// Vector Widening Utilities
5059//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5060
5061// Utility function to find the type to chop up a widen vector for load/store
5062// TLI: Target lowering used to determine legal types.
5063// Width: Width left need to load/store.
5064// WidenVT: The widen vector type to load to/store from
5065// Align: If 0, don't allow use of a wider type
5066// WidenEx: If Align is not 0, the amount additional we can load/store from.
5067
5068static EVT FindMemType(SelectionDAG& DAG, const TargetLowering &TLI,
5069 unsigned Width, EVT WidenVT,
5070 unsigned Align = 0, unsigned WidenEx = 0) {
5071 EVT WidenEltVT = WidenVT.getVectorElementType();
5072 const bool Scalable = WidenVT.isScalableVector();
5073 unsigned WidenWidth = WidenVT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinSize();
5074 unsigned WidenEltWidth = WidenEltVT.getSizeInBits();
5075 unsigned AlignInBits = Align*8;
5076
5077 // If we have one element to load/store, return it.
5078 EVT RetVT = WidenEltVT;
5079 if (!Scalable && Width == WidenEltWidth)
5080 return RetVT;
5081
5082 // See if there is larger legal integer than the element type to load/store.
5083 unsigned VT;
5084 // Don't bother looking for an integer type if the vector is scalable, skip
5085 // to vector types.
5086 if (!Scalable) {
5087 for (VT = (unsigned)MVT::LAST_INTEGER_VALUETYPE;
5088 VT >= (unsigned)MVT::FIRST_INTEGER_VALUETYPE; --VT) {
5089 EVT MemVT((MVT::SimpleValueType) VT);
5090 unsigned MemVTWidth = MemVT.getSizeInBits();
5091 if (MemVT.getSizeInBits() <= WidenEltWidth)
5092 break;
5093 auto Action = TLI.getTypeAction(*DAG.getContext(), MemVT);
5094 if ((Action == TargetLowering::TypeLegal ||
5095 Action == TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger) &&
5096 (WidenWidth % MemVTWidth) == 0 &&
5097 isPowerOf2_32(WidenWidth / MemVTWidth) &&
5098 (MemVTWidth <= Width ||
5099 (Align!=0 && MemVTWidth<=AlignInBits && MemVTWidth<=Width+WidenEx))) {
5100 if (MemVTWidth == WidenWidth)
5101 return MemVT;
5102 RetVT = MemVT;
5103 break;
5104 }
5105 }
5106 }
5107
5108 // See if there is a larger vector type to load/store that has the same vector
5109 // element type and is evenly divisible with the WidenVT.
5110 for (VT = (unsigned)MVT::LAST_VECTOR_VALUETYPE;
5111 VT >= (unsigned)MVT::FIRST_VECTOR_VALUETYPE; --VT) {
5112 EVT MemVT = (MVT::SimpleValueType) VT;
5113 // Skip vector MVTs which don't match the scalable property of WidenVT.
5114 if (Scalable != MemVT.isScalableVector())
5115 continue;
5116 unsigned MemVTWidth = MemVT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinSize();
5117 auto Action = TLI.getTypeAction(*DAG.getContext(), MemVT);
5118 if ((Action == TargetLowering::TypeLegal ||
5119 Action == TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger) &&
5120 WidenEltVT == MemVT.getVectorElementType() &&
5121 (WidenWidth % MemVTWidth) == 0 &&
5122 isPowerOf2_32(WidenWidth / MemVTWidth) &&
5123 (MemVTWidth <= Width ||
5124 (Align!=0 && MemVTWidth<=AlignInBits && MemVTWidth<=Width+WidenEx))) {
5125 if (RetVT.getFixedSizeInBits() < MemVTWidth || MemVT == WidenVT)
5126 return MemVT;
5127 }
5128 }
5129
5130 if (Scalable)
5131 report_fatal_error("Using element-wise loads and stores for widening "
5132 "operations is not supported for scalable vectors");
5133 return RetVT;
5134}
5135
5136// Builds a vector type from scalar loads
5137// VecTy: Resulting Vector type
5138// LDOps: Load operators to build a vector type
5139// [Start,End) the list of loads to use.
5140static SDValue BuildVectorFromScalar(SelectionDAG& DAG, EVT VecTy,
5141 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &LdOps,
5142 unsigned Start, unsigned End) {
5143 SDLoc dl(LdOps[Start]);
5144 EVT LdTy = LdOps[Start].getValueType();
5145 unsigned Width = VecTy.getSizeInBits();
5146 unsigned NumElts = Width / LdTy.getSizeInBits();
5147 EVT NewVecVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), LdTy, NumElts);
5148
5149 unsigned Idx = 1;
5150 SDValue VecOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, dl, NewVecVT,LdOps[Start]);
5151
5152 for (unsigned i = Start + 1; i != End; ++i) {
5153 EVT NewLdTy = LdOps[i].getValueType();
5154 if (NewLdTy != LdTy) {
5155 NumElts = Width / NewLdTy.getSizeInBits();
5156 NewVecVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), NewLdTy, NumElts);
5157 VecOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NewVecVT, VecOp);
5158 // Readjust position and vector position based on new load type.
5159 Idx = Idx * LdTy.getSizeInBits() / NewLdTy.getSizeInBits();
5160 LdTy = NewLdTy;
5161 }
5162 VecOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, NewVecVT, VecOp, LdOps[i],
5163 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx++, dl));
5164 }
5165 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, VecTy, VecOp);
5166}
5167
5168SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::GenWidenVectorLoads(SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &LdChain,
5169 LoadSDNode *LD) {
5170 // The strategy assumes that we can efficiently load power-of-two widths.
5171 // The routine chops the vector into the largest vector loads with the same
5172 // element type or scalar loads and then recombines it to the widen vector
5173 // type.
5174 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(),LD->getValueType(0));
5175 EVT LdVT = LD->getMemoryVT();
5176 SDLoc dl(LD);
5177 assert(LdVT.isVector() && WidenVT.isVector());
5178 assert(LdVT.isScalableVector() == WidenVT.isScalableVector());
5179 assert(LdVT.getVectorElementType() == WidenVT.getVectorElementType());
5180
5181 // Load information
5182 SDValue Chain = LD->getChain();
5183 SDValue BasePtr = LD->getBasePtr();
5184 MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags = LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags();
5185 AAMDNodes AAInfo = LD->getAAInfo();
5186
5187 TypeSize LdWidth = LdVT.getSizeInBits();
5188 TypeSize WidenWidth = WidenVT.getSizeInBits();
5189 TypeSize WidthDiff = WidenWidth - LdWidth;
5190 // Allow wider loads if they are sufficiently aligned to avoid memory faults
5191 // and if the original load is simple.
5192 unsigned LdAlign = (!LD->isSimple()) ? 0 : LD->getAlignment();
5193
5194 // Find the vector type that can load from.
5195 EVT NewVT = FindMemType(DAG, TLI, LdWidth.getKnownMinSize(), WidenVT, LdAlign,
5196 WidthDiff.getKnownMinSize());
5197 TypeSize NewVTWidth = NewVT.getSizeInBits();
5198 SDValue LdOp = DAG.getLoad(NewVT, dl, Chain, BasePtr, LD->getPointerInfo(),
5199 LD->getOriginalAlign(), MMOFlags, AAInfo);
5200 LdChain.push_back(LdOp.getValue(1));
5201
5202 // Check if we can load the element with one instruction.
5203 if (TypeSize::isKnownLE(LdWidth, NewVTWidth)) {
5204 if (!NewVT.isVector()) {
5205 unsigned NumElts = WidenWidth.getFixedSize() / NewVTWidth.getFixedSize();
5206 EVT NewVecVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), NewVT, NumElts);
5207 SDValue VecOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, dl, NewVecVT, LdOp);
5208 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, WidenVT, VecOp);
5209 }
5210 if (NewVT == WidenVT)
5211 return LdOp;
5212
5213 // TODO: We don't currently have any tests that exercise this code path.
5214 assert(WidenWidth.getFixedSize() % NewVTWidth.getFixedSize() == 0);
5215 unsigned NumConcat = WidenWidth.getFixedSize() / NewVTWidth.getFixedSize();
5216 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> ConcatOps(NumConcat);
5217 SDValue UndefVal = DAG.getUNDEF(NewVT);
5218 ConcatOps[0] = LdOp;
5219 for (unsigned i = 1; i != NumConcat; ++i)
5220 ConcatOps[i] = UndefVal;
5221 return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, WidenVT, ConcatOps);
5222 }
5223
5224 // Load vector by using multiple loads from largest vector to scalar.
5225 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> LdOps;
5226 LdOps.push_back(LdOp);
5227
5228 uint64_t ScaledOffset = 0;
5229 MachinePointerInfo MPI = LD->getPointerInfo();
5230 do {
5231 LdWidth -= NewVTWidth;
5232 IncrementPointer(cast<LoadSDNode>(LdOp), NewVT, MPI, BasePtr,
5233 &ScaledOffset);
5234
5235 if (TypeSize::isKnownLT(LdWidth, NewVTWidth)) {
5236 // The current type we are using is too large. Find a better size.
5237 NewVT = FindMemType(DAG, TLI, LdWidth.getKnownMinSize(), WidenVT, LdAlign,
5238 WidthDiff.getKnownMinSize());
5239 NewVTWidth = NewVT.getSizeInBits();
5240 }
5241
5242 Align NewAlign = ScaledOffset == 0
5243 ? LD->getOriginalAlign()
5244 : commonAlignment(LD->getAlign(), ScaledOffset);
5245 SDValue L =
5246 DAG.getLoad(NewVT, dl, Chain, BasePtr, MPI, NewAlign, MMOFlags, AAInfo);
5247 LdChain.push_back(L.getValue(1));
5248
5249 LdOps.push_back(L);
5250 LdOp = L;
5251 } while (TypeSize::isKnownGT(LdWidth, NewVTWidth));
5252
5253 // Build the vector from the load operations.
5254 unsigned End = LdOps.size();
5255 if (!LdOps[0].getValueType().isVector())
5256 // All the loads are scalar loads.
5257 return BuildVectorFromScalar(DAG, WidenVT, LdOps, 0, End);
5258
5259 // If the load contains vectors, build the vector using concat vector.
5260 // All of the vectors used to load are power-of-2, and the scalar loads can be
5261 // combined to make a power-of-2 vector.
5262 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> ConcatOps(End);
5263 int i = End - 1;
5264 int Idx = End;
5265 EVT LdTy = LdOps[i].getValueType();
5266 // First, combine the scalar loads to a vector.
5267 if (!LdTy.isVector()) {
5268 for (--i; i >= 0; --i) {
5269 LdTy = LdOps[i].getValueType();
5270 if (LdTy.isVector())
5271 break;
5272 }
5273 ConcatOps[--Idx] = BuildVectorFromScalar(DAG, LdTy, LdOps, i + 1, End);
5274 }
5275
5276 ConcatOps[--Idx] = LdOps[i];
5277 for (--i; i >= 0; --i) {
5278 EVT NewLdTy = LdOps[i].getValueType();
5279 if (NewLdTy != LdTy) {
5280 // Create a larger vector.
5281 TypeSize LdTySize = LdTy.getSizeInBits();
5282 TypeSize NewLdTySize = NewLdTy.getSizeInBits();
5283 assert(NewLdTySize.isScalable() == LdTySize.isScalable() &&
5284 NewLdTySize.isKnownMultipleOf(LdTySize.getKnownMinSize()));
5285 unsigned NumOps =
5286 NewLdTySize.getKnownMinSize() / LdTySize.getKnownMinSize();
5287 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> WidenOps(NumOps);
5288 unsigned j = 0;
5289 for (; j != End-Idx; ++j)
5290 WidenOps[j] = ConcatOps[Idx+j];
5291 for (; j != NumOps; ++j)
5292 WidenOps[j] = DAG.getUNDEF(LdTy);
5293
5294 ConcatOps[End-1] = DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, NewLdTy,
5295 WidenOps);
5296 Idx = End - 1;
5297 LdTy = NewLdTy;
5298 }
5299 ConcatOps[--Idx] = LdOps[i];
5300 }
5301
5302 if (WidenWidth == LdTy.getSizeInBits() * (End - Idx))
5303 return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, WidenVT,
5304 makeArrayRef(&ConcatOps[Idx], End - Idx));
5305
5306 // We need to fill the rest with undefs to build the vector.
5307 unsigned NumOps =
5308 WidenWidth.getKnownMinSize() / LdTy.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinSize();
5309 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> WidenOps(NumOps);
5310 SDValue UndefVal = DAG.getUNDEF(LdTy);
5311 {
5312 unsigned i = 0;
5313 for (; i != End-Idx; ++i)
5314 WidenOps[i] = ConcatOps[Idx+i];
5315 for (; i != NumOps; ++i)
5316 WidenOps[i] = UndefVal;
5317 }
5318 return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, WidenVT, WidenOps);
5319}

5321SDValue
5322DAGTypeLegalizer::GenWidenVectorExtLoads(SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &LdChain,
5323 LoadSDNode *LD,
5324 ISD::LoadExtType ExtType) {
5325 // For extension loads, it may not be more efficient to chop up the vector
5326 // and then extend it. Instead, we unroll the load and build a new vector.
5327 EVT WidenVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(),LD->getValueType(0));
5328 EVT LdVT = LD->getMemoryVT();
5329 SDLoc dl(LD);
5330 assert(LdVT.isVector() && WidenVT.isVector());
5331 assert(LdVT.isScalableVector() == WidenVT.isScalableVector());
5332
5333 // Load information
5334 SDValue Chain = LD->getChain();
5335 SDValue BasePtr = LD->getBasePtr();
5336 MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags = LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags();
5337 AAMDNodes AAInfo = LD->getAAInfo();
5338
5339 if (LdVT.isScalableVector())
5340 report_fatal_error("Generating widen scalable extending vector loads is "
5341 "not yet supported");
5342
5343 EVT EltVT = WidenVT.getVectorElementType();
5344 EVT LdEltVT = LdVT.getVectorElementType();
5345 unsigned NumElts = LdVT.getVectorNumElements();
5346
5347 // Load each element and widen.
5348 unsigned WidenNumElts = WidenVT.getVectorNumElements();
5349 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(WidenNumElts);
5350 unsigned Increment = LdEltVT.getSizeInBits() / 8;
5351 Ops[0] =
5352 DAG.getExtLoad(ExtType, dl, EltVT, Chain, BasePtr, LD->getPointerInfo(),
5353 LdEltVT, LD->getOriginalAlign(), MMOFlags, AAInfo);
5354 LdChain.push_back(Ops[0].getValue(1));
5355 unsigned i = 0, Offset = Increment;
5356 for (i=1; i < NumElts; ++i, Offset += Increment) {
5357 SDValue NewBasePtr =
5358 DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, BasePtr, TypeSize::Fixed(Offset));
5359 Ops[i] = DAG.getExtLoad(ExtType, dl, EltVT, Chain, NewBasePtr,
5360 LD->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(Offset), LdEltVT,
5361 LD->getOriginalAlign(), MMOFlags, AAInfo);
5362 LdChain.push_back(Ops[i].getValue(1));
5363 }
5364
5365 // Fill the rest with undefs.
5366 SDValue UndefVal = DAG.getUNDEF(EltVT);
5367 for (; i != WidenNumElts; ++i)
5368 Ops[i] = UndefVal;
5369
5370 return DAG.getBuildVector(WidenVT, dl, Ops);
5371}
5372
5373void DAGTypeLegalizer::GenWidenVectorStores(SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &StChain,
5374 StoreSDNode *ST) {
5375 // The strategy assumes that we can efficiently store power-of-two widths.
5376 // The routine chops the vector into the largest vector stores with the same
5377 // element type or scalar stores.
5378 SDValue Chain = ST->getChain();
5379 SDValue BasePtr = ST->getBasePtr();
5380 MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags = ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags();
5381 AAMDNodes AAInfo = ST->getAAInfo();
5382 SDValue ValOp = GetWidenedVector(ST->getValue());
5383 SDLoc dl(ST);
5384
5385 EVT StVT = ST->getMemoryVT();
5386 TypeSize StWidth = StVT.getSizeInBits();
5387 EVT ValVT = ValOp.getValueType();
5388 TypeSize ValWidth = ValVT.getSizeInBits();
5389 EVT ValEltVT = ValVT.getVectorElementType();
5390 unsigned ValEltWidth = ValEltVT.getFixedSizeInBits();
5391 assert(StVT.getVectorElementType() == ValEltVT);
5392 assert(StVT.isScalableVector() == ValVT.isScalableVector() &&
5393 "Mismatch between store and value types");
5394
5395 int Idx = 0; // current index to store
5396
5397 MachinePointerInfo MPI = ST->getPointerInfo();
5398 uint64_t ScaledOffset = 0;
5399 while (StWidth.isNonZero()) {
5400 // Find the largest vector type we can store with.
5401 EVT NewVT = FindMemType(DAG, TLI, StWidth.getKnownMinSize(), ValVT);
5402 TypeSize NewVTWidth = NewVT.getSizeInBits();
5403
5404 if (NewVT.isVector()) {
5405 unsigned NumVTElts = NewVT.getVectorMinNumElements();
5406 do {
5407 Align NewAlign = ScaledOffset == 0
5408 ? ST->getOriginalAlign()
5409 : commonAlignment(ST->getAlign(), ScaledOffset);
5410 SDValue EOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, NewVT, ValOp,
5411 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl));
5412 SDValue PartStore = DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, EOp, BasePtr, MPI, NewAlign,
5413 MMOFlags, AAInfo);
5414 StChain.push_back(PartStore);
5415
5416 StWidth -= NewVTWidth;
5417 Idx += NumVTElts;
5418
5419 IncrementPointer(cast<StoreSDNode>(PartStore), NewVT, MPI, BasePtr,
5420 &ScaledOffset);
5421 } while (StWidth.isNonZero() && TypeSize::isKnownGE(StWidth, NewVTWidth));
5422 } else {
5423 // Cast the vector to the scalar type we can store.
5424 unsigned NumElts = ValWidth.getFixedSize() / NewVTWidth.getFixedSize();
5425 EVT NewVecVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), NewVT, NumElts);
5426 SDValue VecOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NewVecVT, ValOp);
5427 // Readjust index position based on new vector type.
5428 Idx = Idx * ValEltWidth / NewVTWidth.getFixedSize();
5429 do {
5430 SDValue EOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, NewVT, VecOp,
5431 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx++, dl));
5432 SDValue PartStore =
5433 DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, EOp, BasePtr, MPI, ST->getOriginalAlign(),
5434 MMOFlags, AAInfo);
5435 StChain.push_back(PartStore);
5436
5437 StWidth -= NewVTWidth;
5438 IncrementPointer(cast<StoreSDNode>(PartStore), NewVT, MPI, BasePtr);
5439 } while (StWidth.isNonZero() && TypeSize::isKnownGE(StWidth, NewVTWidth));
5440 // Restore index back to be relative to the original widen element type.
5441 Idx = Idx * NewVTWidth.getFixedSize() / ValEltWidth;
5442 }
5443 }
5444}

5446/// Modifies a vector input (widen or narrows) to a vector of NVT. The
5447/// input vector must have the same element type as NVT.
5448/// FillWithZeroes specifies that the vector should be widened with zeroes.
5449SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ModifyToType(SDValue InOp, EVT NVT,
5450 bool FillWithZeroes) {
5451 // Note that InOp might have been widened so it might already have
5452 // the right width or it might need be narrowed.
5453 EVT InVT = InOp.getValueType();
5454 assert(InVT.getVectorElementType() == NVT.getVectorElementType() &&
5455 "input and widen element type must match");
5456 SDLoc dl(InOp);
5457
5458 // Check if InOp already has the right width.
5459 if (InVT == NVT)
5460 return InOp;
5461
5462 unsigned InNumElts = InVT.getVectorNumElements();
5463 unsigned WidenNumElts = NVT.getVectorNumElements();
5464 if (WidenNumElts > InNumElts && WidenNumElts % InNumElts == 0) {
5465 unsigned NumConcat = WidenNumElts / InNumElts;
5466 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(NumConcat);
5467 SDValue FillVal = FillWithZeroes ? DAG.getConstant(0, dl, InVT) :
5468 DAG.getUNDEF(InVT);
5469 Ops[0] = InOp;
5470 for (unsigned i = 1; i != NumConcat; ++i)
5471 Ops[i] = FillVal;
5472
5473 return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, NVT, Ops);
5474 }
5475
5476 if (WidenNumElts < InNumElts && InNumElts % WidenNumElts)
5477 return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, NVT, InOp,
5478 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, dl));
5479
5480 // Fall back to extract and build.
5481 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops(WidenNumElts);
5482 EVT EltVT = NVT.getVectorElementType();
5483 unsigned MinNumElts = std::min(WidenNumElts, InNumElts);
5484 unsigned Idx;
5485 for (Idx = 0; Idx < MinNumElts; ++Idx)
5486 Ops[Idx] = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, EltVT, InOp,
5487 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl));
5488
5489 SDValue FillVal = FillWithZeroes ? DAG.getConstant(0, dl, EltVT) :
5490 DAG.getUNDEF(EltVT);
5491 for ( ; Idx < WidenNumElts; ++Idx)
5492 Ops[Idx] = FillVal;
5493 return DAG.getBuildVector(NVT, dl, Ops);
5494}
